Subject: Small Acts on Online Kindness For our Kids and Teens (and us)
Description: By Delaney Ruston, MD  Screenagers Contact: lisa@screenagersmovie.com, or 415-450-9585 For more tech time/screen time topics go to >> www.screenagersmovie.com/tech-talk-tuesdays (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQB2T05ChQ-2BjwYEa1hyN0b6axeviFynNIHo-2B-2FNfz0kChi0TmmNpwcg1MI9khDR5jFp9g-3D-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs0ONb1SFdGQ9PKNQR-2B17gUhfkJ2HUrnk4ipXp1afMZgQwYuCgUNipZbOO4oiaxY7xnqQxvw9TeIU3bJOejPwVE7Fz4ybZByATthnFZYqVezH-2BColhYH4FjC-2BQQ03OWaSdi6yVLKV1Jkgp-2BvFDiFWBl4QI6M295U49sA8Y6JLxaz-2B-2FDHXsegxWUNPIS0qY3FCj5O3FGpq5dMQ7PIQZ-2BQn1DAu9ocKUZVP-2BgPRcfcV7s45uwDIcrCBKde5Ph2YnwfUPk-3D  **Tech Talk Tuesday is Screenagers' (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQB2T05ChQ-2BjwYEa1hyN0b6axeviFynNIHo-2B-2FNfz0kChi0TmmNpwcg1MI9khDR5jFp9g-3D-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs0ONb1SFdGQ9PKNQR-2B17gUhfkJ2HUrnk4ipXp1afMZgQwYuCgUNipZbOO4oiaxY7xnqQxvw9TeIU3bJOejPwVE7Fz4ybZByATthnFZYqVezH8JS6nIaY5Bo-2BEn6vfkkXmhVqAk9UBwYVXhvrNuTxcABKxCPZaZIVHc1GNE76mz57bgiVe3rqFov0JyCnq7TJDCvQHj6hyRuI4iewdqO6HuWLI9AW-2Bi5SOLoyygfmCy9hKPdbiElyYz72rulwuz2bDM-3D weekly column that Delaney Ruston, MD, the filmmaker/physician from the movie SCREENAGERS writes to help families manage and decrease struggles around screen time.  Small Acts on Online Kindness For our Kids and Teens (and us)   Not all screen time is created equal. The more we, and our kids, use screen time for good, the better. There are wonderful things we can do with financial donations, and that is crucial—but I want to focus on what we can do with our kids that uses tech's power — and costs no money.  One thing we can do is support businesses or social causes through tech with acts such as posting reviews on Yelp, giving stars and sharing recommendations. Having moved back recently to Seattle, I was so happy to see that the little café down the street from me, Fat Ducks, is still going strong. The owner is an incredible baker, and she is always working so hard to make everyone’s cafe experience enjoyable. It felt great to share her cafe with others online by giving her and her cafe a good review on Yelp. I made sure to include specific reasons why I like it so much because I know I like examples when I look at reviews. I did not expect it, but one day when I stopped in for some outstanding carrot cake, the owner thanked me for posting a review. I also love sharing links to friends’ work, such as their online talks, published books and articles.   I remind myself to involve my kids in these tiny acts. For example, if we go to a local Vietnamese Pho cafe, I will say, “Hey let's do a rating on this.”  When they read books they like, we talk about how writing a review can help the author’s work be appreciated by more readers.  My family tries to spread the word about organizations we love via social media and, of course, in face-to-face conversations.   What organizations do you love?  For this TTT, here are some questions to start a conversation:  · What are ways you perform small acts of kindness online towards people, businesses, etc. that you appreciate?  · Do you think liking a photo is a small act of kindness?  · What are causes and organizations that inspire you?  · In what ways do you contribute to your community and causes you care about?    ______________________  If you would rather not receive future communications from SCREENAGERS, please go to https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=0jpVdUjq4pKnFqr34rWqKKGkHD-2Bg5902lbRFo5HyB99-2FOFtKa8JtkDXqAzYpBcdSQeIfwTI5UiFzIA3vu0hRi8vPwMsw3BGsZHQ9FuKqVIsy5C9RPJ1WAl5LF5bsLSw1lUSBaMssDtmIXmVtT8liDwbwe6wSAuZdwBcdEmCQHXA-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs0ONb1SFdGQ9PKNQR-2B17gUhfkJ2HUrnk4ipXp1afMZgQwYuCgUNipZbOO4oiaxY7xnqQxvw9TeIU3bJOejPwVE7Fz4ybZByATthnFZYqVezH4RJvz01heBopEsFwKV143zsejBOZZp4xZDMcJzZ-2Fhd69Bh383KoilXJFJYqmYD87rZWAs3l3Xnu11oa8LwsP6B-2BJy9gITo6ZxDlVYkT54EEb6tM6GUu-2Fm6JymhQEXD-2B-2BRsLOeLnbe5bMobqqGDR7Hk-3D  SCREENAGERS, 735 Center Blvd Suite C, Fairfax, CA 94930 United States  --  To unsubscribe from this group and stop receiving emails from it, send an email to customerservice+unsubscribe@csps.com.

Description: Hi Stephanie????,  An article in the August 5 issue of The New Yorker (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQByMDhLpviQi9ox5VE-2F1HH4IJtmrGXEWdn0MB8atqnCh6D7J2dB-2Bi-2FQuuc73ZzV6vdp6w4eb3iWMBlQcP6L19ewARDXQAjHzl-2BaYxSD7a83xlV57uTDLR4QfV2spYxITFD2bvNT-2BdpOOjDtnv4UW-2FLejzGLvxZx1SUUO7xIxCU4upaTZIsTcUQXA-2Bi-2B5IpcU8tw-3D-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs0uc85rFSBFSBs-2BlN1-2FE9He3DqEBAttUUT3ItrkbN0uVHqlZLNcbJwnp4C2vRSgRoj5bndYGDJaS0mXvq2G3XXZjLEdOVY5DnE3fD-2F2Fw4zCbVOkO3QjILDMVGkRG-2BPAy72WaPVIZmCBKg9n7de73efjLKwaF0EvBsiw2bVPjOUUyWYbC8a3uMPbCoa3SRgLDE6XgZvhHG-2FMtUP0Nd2IXA-2F0UytsnwQ9dkQv1F0O2Eo3Id2vw6Ql3X0E5lbvczhzGw-3D boldly claims that the American Heart Association's 'endorsements-for-sale policy' has directly contributed to skyrocketing obesity epidemic in the U.S. But what is the byproduct of a fat country? The answer is disease. Right now 1-in-3 Americans either have type 2 diabetes or are in a state of pre-diabetes and it is on track to be a $1 trillion annual industry by 2026. Sobering statistics but there is a light at the end of that tunnel: type 2 diabetes is completely reversible AND curable and doing so can increase life expectancy by 50%. The book gives readers the steps to take to reverse and cure the disease including a procedure many of us consider a "shame" surgery for the particularly lazy without ever realizing that it is, in fact, a lifesaver. I'd like to send a copy of the book in hopes you'll consider covering it on your blog. If you decide to include it in a post, in addition to a free giveaway copy for one of your readers, we can offer you three options for easy, available content :  · An exclusive pre-written interview with 4-6 questions and answers by Dr. Sasse — print-ready for you to post · A phone or email interview with Dr. Sasse with questions of your own · An excerpt from the book of up to 1,000 words  Dr. Sasse is one of the United States’ most compelling authorities on type 2 diabetes working specifically within the community of adults and adolescents whose pre-diabetes or type 2 onset as a result of obesity. But the science tells us a shockingly different story. In his new book THE TYPE II DIABETES CURE (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQB383h7yl3-2BW3XXkpDfkO8ZjVw3DiIa72ye4p8eVU2XCOCwWIDBPsA2YG58jh0xRU2GUcD-2Bm-2BdPN48kNpV5zJHGnhWpP6mvmLopnTF0dsbuiJvBZyyTzhVDZQqpQyPBkdmiabvzs70K6PaoGi843oinPaTgXZY2T-2BCdk2WBrOT9DgFn-2B2SfjHERJR2NTbhqURbQ-3D-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs0uc85rFSBFSBs-2BlN1-2FE9He3DqEBAttUUT3ItrkbN0uVHqlZLNcbJwnp4C2vRSgRoj5bndYGDJaS0mXvq2G3XXZjLEdOVY5DnE3fD-2F2Fw4zCcXz0zck1FquksUOvNvvBSSRp0PuiLhN3NeyhGpv-2FZZy77F7AIxHOvKvhbYzILdsBc3NZGeDmWE3x9k7lwjtNNSLoyRth2KMZFtRz-2FjVvNMIyPm5wRE2ZPy5rmPJdwk419ZzVjYoRTLN83X6Q51Y-2Fnk-3D  [September 10, 2019] Dr. Kent Sasse reveals the latest clinical research showing that the shots-and-pills trap us into a cycle of weight gain, worsening diabetes, and alarming risks of heart attack, kidney failure, and amputations.  The goal of the experts around the globe is to cure the type 2 diabetes outright – not settle for managing a number – and metabolic surgery combined with regular exercise does just that. The safe, 45-minute procedure with 4 Band-aids is quietly transforming the landscape of diabetes care, curing people of type 2 diabetes with a safer approach than pharmaceuticals.  This book will help you move from managing the serum glucose to reversing the type 2 diabetes and living a longer, healthier life. The alarming data about type 2 diabetes makes it imperative to do so. Dr. Kent C. Subject: Whip Up Seasonal Eats & Treats with Kidstir!
Description: Good morning, Stephanie,  Whipping up tasty snacks, meals and desserts is simple with the help of Kidstir! Children will adore receiving the three holiday-themed kits during the months of October, November and December to get them excited and involved with the festivities!  More information is below on each of the three kits, and we would love to tuck samples in the mail for editorial consideration for any upcoming holiday stories! Thanks!   Spooky Celebration Kit  Planning a spooktacular Halloween party? Head to the kitchen and scare up some treats for your ghoulish guests! In this Subscriber Exclusive kit from Kidstir, you’ll find out how to make three Halloween recipes for fiendish food. You’ll also discover fun facts about kitchen witches and mummies, make mini jack-o’-lanterns, and play spooky food games. Start by making Witch’s Brew. Use your new Freaky Freeze Mold to make skulls and bones for spiced apple cider. Then cook up some Scary-oli with the Pasta Press included in this kit. For dessert, bake Yummy Mummies for your party guests, then send them home with treat bags decorated with Spooky Stickers.   Gobbling Good Fixings Kit  Children will love tearing open the Gobbling Good Fixings kit to start cooking! With ideas to help your family make memories in the kitchen at this time of the year, the kit contains three simple, easy recipes that kids can whip up for the Thanksgiving Feast, including Zesty Cranberry Sauce, Popcorn Bread and Awesome Apple Stuffing. Plus, encourage gratitude this season by playing the Gratitude Game at the table. It’s a simple way for kids and grown-ups to take a step back, soak up the moment, and revel in all that we have right here, right now.   Winter Wonderland Cookies Kit  Let it snow in your kitchen with a flurry of treats this winter! Snow or no snow, you can bring winter fun indoors with the Winter Wonderland Cookies kit from Kidstir! In this engaging Subscriber Exclusive kit for budding foodies and chefs, you’ll find three fun-to-make cookie recipes. Children will have fun learning how to mix up buttercream frosting, decorate sugar cookies, and make a snow globe in a jar as a gift.  Start by mixing up Snowball Truffles and roll them in powdered sugar. Then, cut cookie dough with Starry Night Cutters, and bake Hot Cocoa Cookies. Use your new Cookie Decorating Kit to make Shortbread Snowflakes. Package up your goodies with the Holiday Gift Tags. What a great way to enjoy the holidays!  A Kidstir subscription makes an excellent gift that is educational, entertaining, and gets the whole family involved! http://kidstir.com/  To request information, samples or high res images, please contact Tana Siebold at Tana@orcapr.com. Looking forward to hearing from you! Thank you!  Warmly,  Tana Siebold | Publicist  Orca PR  Email: Tana@orcapr.com    If you are receiving this email in error or wish to be removed from our mailing list please visit: Opt-Out   -- To unsubscribe from this group and stop receiving emails from it, send an email to customerservice+unsubscribe@csps.com.

Subject: SOURCE/ shootings: When children witness violence & hatred it affects society as a whole
Description: Even from a distance, violence and hate cause children stress that can lead to future violent behavior, says esteemed social scientist and international bestselling author  Hi Stephanie? -  Thought this might be of interest as a feature or interview as given recent events:  Esteemed social scientist, cultural historian and international bestselling author Riane Eisler (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQBwbNA2Pbmihm2FEsQv2cUtGL3MxeH1OHys8bPrePzXJv_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs1-2F91Rwb9MFH74m2USQ203UPGE1QNCjMVf-2BhpTdiAv8jJ1beMWJDrmSbzaBygvTvuZuFmCEf1DBR-2FSdrPktrTtwbb0NQX0gsfFTej6E-2FW6dYkiv-2Fchvt0MQT-2BxZ0zj0ZL1PYIaQ-2FF1gyxHieXRgxOkIS4AKiT7zw0IiZrEAE41fIEqBH1LcUp0y0fXe2xIvVKb-2Fmn-2BqgY2QNmbuiHWSbSUUnqHsSWOjm3xzpLPXhVpcU43niGepMUXRnOuh9-2FcOTY8-3D ’s research demonstrates the fact that the tragic shootings of the past several days may well stem from the impact of growing up in a “domination” culture or family that supports rigid, top-down rankings and is held together by fear and force.  And merely observing this type of violence or participating in duck-and-cover active shooter drills at school can, in turn, leave a powerful psychic imprint on children: witnessing or experiencing violence causes significant stress, which in turn can lead to violent behavior.  This trickles out into society as a whole.  Riane has tons of research-based evidence supporting her position, all of which is found in her new book Nurturing Our Humanity (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQB5rCyr8YhvvmcS26fVShb1W0O70-2B4VVpdbGrM6osgz4PHapCx5FXZ8NdzVmVn8f8d0UTn89kHdtUa9xovPsr4Cn6kvRb5sZjip8Qji7qSAcZZFH4TAlhTYvBDhtpf-2B6coA-3D-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs1-2F91Rwb9MFH74m2USQ203UPGE1QNCjMVf-2BhpTdiAv8jJ1beMWJDrmSbzaBygvTvuZuFmCEf1DBR-2FSdrPktrTtwbb0NQX0gsfFTej6E-2FW6dYloiWB1nfDpNp4fiwg-2F1ORwHNMzaMvvk-2BPz7qOVKCNitS5PJulJwFSGFV6cMCo-2Fgp2eLqsi2I9II2ezfaUkDBhew40aKgr8oTvVVql222q3UmrTjx7eSP5Z-2BH-2Ffg9HJWawzIbaa85uyEg-2BgpQwogw7Y-3D .  The antidote, she explains, is to take concrete steps to end domination and violence at home and in society at large, beginning with a focus on parent-child and gender relations, so that we can weave non-violent behavior patterns into our individual and social fabric over time.  I’d be glad to put you in touch for an interview, explore an article submission or send a copy of the book.  - Emily    ______________________  If you would rather not receive future communications from BSPR, please go to https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=mAHw-2B8ZZluKmvldupnv96uLo9Y9fajlVzzV3E2AQMMy3o0jRx7vDS35Oho-2BRYwxVM-2F-2BL7LaoyWUUZGT3ACwSPGpQiAU2KYEgLHab0Mh-2Bp6nVns6HZlFyGGsQTe9PiAecpb080VdUbpNc-2BJ92158PJ99xsUPpcSgUV0waJHdzzVY-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs1-2F91Rwb9MFH74m2USQ203UPGE1QNCjMVf-2BhpTdiAv8jJ1beMWJDrmSbzaBygvTvuZuFmCEf1DBR-2FSdrPktrTtwbb0NQX0gsfFTej6E-2FW6dYj77uZyw4jKu8pTrCLwKshkYN5-2BZKLJriknMLL0mWOh0HKc7aXrfUKZY3zL-2BsEfGbtTpS-2BoYgh8EWZynwGzTNVHpQQft-2FwUp52qHGU2N4AI-2BrO-2BwlyvtUf8DxJwYCw-2Fo0oFh0HP1GB-2FLhbbKh2q7-2B64-3D  BSPR, 18 Main Street, Extension, Suite 409, Plymouth, MA 02360 United States  --  To unsubscribe from this group and stop receiving emails from it, send an email to customerservice+unsubscribe@csps.com.

Subject: Editorial comments and corrections
Description: The following information was collected:  Name: John  Email: robledoint@yahoo.com  Subscriber: No  Subject: Ohio Shooter reportedly supported Elizabeth Warren, Self- identified as "Lefist"  Product: csmonitor.com  Message: Ohio shooter reportedly supported Elizabeth Warren, self-identified as ‘leftist’ August 5, 2019 by Patriot News Alerts Democrats are doing their best to blame their opponents for the horrific violence of the last week.  However, you can’t run from reality. The revelation that the Dayton shooter was a socialist who supported Elizabeth Warren for president has sent Dems into a panic.  Social media profile The insights into the politics of the shooter come from his social media. He identified his preferred pronouns as he/him. The 24-year-old also prominently displayed on his twitter that he was a “leftist.”  Connor Betts described himself as a pro-Satan leftist who hates Joe Biden’s generation, President Trump, and law enforcement.  Twitter has since suspended his account, but not before many of his tweets were recorded. Betts said in a tweet: “I want socialism, and I’ll not wait for the idiots to finally come round to understanding.”  It cannot be denied that he had a leftist worldview and goal. Other tweets made this clear: “Vote blue for [G]od’s sake,” “F*** John McCain.”  This contrasts heavily to the white supremacist shooter in El Paso, Texas, proving that senseless violence is not a partisan issue.  Culture needs reform As much as Democrats have attempted to pin the blame on Donald Trump, he isn’t responsible for the El Paso shooter. Conversely, Elizabeth Warren is also not responsible for the Dayton shooter.  Guns also cannot be blamed for the recent rise in mass shootings. We have always had guns. In fact, the further you go back in American history, the more guns the American people have typically had.  We live in a culture that encourages angry, emotionally immature people to act out. Kids grow up in a public school system where they are at best ignored, and at worst, drugged and mercilessly bullied.  Nihilism runs rampant and our children are taught that life is meaningless. Mental health resources are few and far between.  Until we change our culture, violence will only grow worse. As political division intensifies, mass shootings will just be another outlet for misdirected anger.

Description: View this email in your browser (https://mailchi.mp/10186f0b5408/alyssa-milano-sorry-not-sorry-podcast-episode-16?e=1acc59e421) FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE   Alyssa Milano: Sorry Not Sorry Podcast  Interviews with Attorney John Bonifaz and  Former Federal Prosecutor Renato Mariotti   EXCLUSIVE Impeachment Statements from Debra Messing,  Rep. Joe Kennedy III, Rep. Ted Lieu, Jon Cryer, and More   https://truepublicrelations.us12.list-manage.com/track/click?u=12625cf9000644aef0f718377&id=700b9adaba&e=1acc59e421 Download JPEG (https://truepublicrelations.us12.list-manage.com/track/click?u=12625cf9000644aef0f718377&id=828d00c97a&e=1acc59e421)   What happens in an impeachment inquiry? Is this the best thing to do ahead of the 2020 election? On today’s episode of Alyssa Milano: Sorry Not Sorry, Alyssa Milano and guests explore why now is the time to call for the impeachment of President Donald Trump and what this would mean for the country. Alyssa is joined by John Bonifaz, an attorney who specializes in constitutional law and voting rights, and Renato Mariotti, a former federal prosecutor, who help break it all down. Additionally, you’ll hear exclusive statements on impeachment from Debra Messing, Rep. Joe Kennedy III, Rep. Ted Lieu, Jon Cryer, Piper Perabo, Amee Vanderpool, Rep. Dan Kildee, Mike Levin, Rep. Jamie Raskin, Rep. Harley Rouda and Sen. Michael Gianaris.   The episode title is To Impeach or Not to Impeach? and is available now on Apple Podcasts (https://truepublicrelations.us12.list-manage.com/track/click?u=12625cf9000644aef0f718377&id=bb112f1ab2&e=1acc59e421) , Spotify (https://truepublicrelations.us12.list-manage.com/track/click?u=12625cf9000644aef0f718377&id=4a6645a697&e=1acc59e421) , Google Play (https://truepublicrelations.us12.list-manage.com/track/click?u=12625cf9000644aef0f718377&id=28dd86359e&e=1acc59e421)  and Stitcher (https://truepublicrelations.us12.list-manage.com/track/click?u=12625cf9000644aef0f718377&id=0699773fd5&e=1acc59e421)  Please click on the links below for EXCLUSIVE statements: John Bonifaz (https://truepublicrelations.us12.list-manage.com/track/click?u=12625cf9000644aef0f718377&id=b358b23e32&e=1acc59e421)  Renato Mariotti (https://truepublicrelations.us12.list-manage.com/track/click?u=12625cf9000644aef0f718377&id=575abb62a5&e=1acc59e421)  Debra Messing (https://truepublicrelations.us12.list-manage.com/track/click?u=12625cf9000644aef0f718377&id=30aff7c748&e=1acc59e421)  Rep. Michael Gianaris (https://truepublicrelations.us12.list-manage.com/track/click?u=12625cf9000644aef0f718377&id=6322668416&e=1acc59e421)   ABOUT ALYSSA MILANO: SORRY NOT SORRY (https://truepublicrelations.us12.list-manage.com/track/click?u=12625cf9000644aef0f718377&id=dba46ac260&e=1acc59e421)  The weekly podcast tackles social, political and cultural issues from the perspective of unapologetic guests while highlighting activists doing amazing work and grassroots efforts throughout the country. It focuses on shaping narratives and changing hearts and minds to bridge the ideologies of a divided nation.  Additional guests include VP Joe Biden, Tarana Burke, Congressman Ro Khanna, Frances Fisher, Manuel Oliver, Erin Brockovich, Dr. Sanjay Gupta, AG Josh Shapiro and many more.  Throughout her nearly 40-year career, Milano has used her platform to advance causes that matter deeply to her.  As a teenager, she helped to destigmatize and reduce the irrational fears surrounding HIV/AIDS by kissing Ryan White on national television. Her advancement of #MeToo sparked a viral movement of women fighting against sexual harassment and assault and she has been involved in TimesUp since its inception.  She recently joined the ERA Coalition’s Advisory Council. She is also the ACLU’s Ambassador for Reproductive Rights. In the wake of the mass shooting at Stoneman Douglas High School, Alyssa became one of the founders of NoRA, a coalition dedicated to combatting the NRA money in political campaigns so that common sense gun reform can be enacted. For 15 years, she has been a UNICEF National Ambassador.  In 2016, she received their Spirit of Compassion Award for her dedication to their mission of advocating for the protection of children's rights, helping meet their basic needs and expanding their opportunities to reach their full potential. She has lobbied members of congress for greater rights for immigrants as well as education reform and has been on the forefront of efforts to protect health coverage for all Americans.  She continues to use her voice and platform to advocate for social justice, fairness and equality. “Sorry Not Sorry,” is a natural outgrowth of her passion for so many important causes. Subject: Williamson Says We Need to Pray and Act
Description: View this email in your browser (https://mailchi.mp/marianne2020/p_a_100_8_5_19-245973?e=86750cd953) https://www.marianne2020.com/ FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE August 5, 2019 Patricia Ewing Communications Director Press@marianne2020.com (mailto:Press@marianne2020.com) 443-906-1495   Williamson Says We Need to Pray and Act Will Take Action in First Hundred Days   Democratic Presidential candidate Marianne Williamson said that "We need to say prayers for the people of El Paso, Dayton, and Chicago in this agonizing moment. And prayers for all the rest of us as well, that we might summon the courage to remove this scourge of gun violence from our midst." She said, “Let us pray and let us act.”  Williamson promised action, “As a candidate for the Democratic nomination for president, I hereby pledge to introduce, within the first 100 days of my presidency, comprehensive firearm legislation to establish universal background checks, outlawing of bump stocks, closing of gun show and boyfriend loopholes, plus outlawing of assault weapons as well as the bullets needed to shoot them.”  When Williamson was asked about this subject in last Tuesday's debate, she said, "The issue of gun safety, of course, is that the NRA has us in a chokehold. But so do the pharmaceutical companies, the health insurance companies, the fossil fuel companies, and the defense contractors. None of this will change until we either pass a constitutional amendment or legislation that establishes public funding for federal campaigns."  Williamson said that at a certain point in life, "It isn’t about what happened; it’s about who we choose to be in response to what happened. Each of us must rise to the occasion now, committing to the electoral defeat of any politician who supports the NRA's political agenda. Gun safety legislation must be the cry of our generation. I applaud the Senators who have called upon Mitch McConnell to call the Senate into session to act on Gun Safety legislation.”  “America can either behave responsibly towards our common good, or we can acquiesce to the economic tyranny of gun manufacturers. We cannot do both,” emphasized Williamson.  Williamson gun safety plans can be found here. (https://www.marianne2020.com/issues/gun-control)  Williamson supports: * Eliminating the sale of assault rifles and semi-automatic weapons * Banning bump stocks and high capacity magazines * Strict control of gun use among children and access to guns among children * Required universal background checks, including at gun shows * Mandatory waiting periods for all gun dealers, including gun shows and sporting retailers * Reinstatement of Obama era restrictions on the ability of the mentally ill to purchase a gun * Child safety locks on all guns * Passage of Extreme Risk Protection Order Laws nationwide, allowing family members and law enforcement to seek court permission to temporarily remove guns from a person in danger of harming himself or others * Removing current limits on the Center for Disease Control’s (CDC) ability to track and record gun ownership numbers in America (vital information which helps in researching the overwhelming amount of gun deaths and underlying causes)  ###  ============================================================ ** (https://twitter.com/marwilliamson) ** (https://www.facebook.com/williamsonmarianne/) ** (https://www.instagram.com/mariannewilliamson/) ** (https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCXAMXGAP0YnBxtc8brSSbjg) ** (https://www.marianne2020.com) Copyright © 2019 Marianne Williamson for President, All rights reserved. Subject: Inmate Request
Calling all inspirational womxn photographers!
Description: Creating space for inspiration, knowledge and power.   Inspiration, knowledge & community. View this email in your browser (https://mailchi.mp/lasfotosproject/its-our-most-anticipated-arts-event-of-the-year-3457005?e=eef305b22e) https://lasfotosproject.networkforgood.com/projects/59604-thank-you-for-supporting-las-fotos-project   ** Nominate Your Favorite Womxn Photographers! ------------------------------------------------------------  The Foto Awards (http://www.lasfotosproject.org/thefotoawards)  presented by Las Fotos Project (http://www.lasfotosproject.org/thefotoawards) is the first event of its kind, uplifting the incredible contributions womxn make to the photographic world. The one-night-only celebration features a silent auction of never-before-seen work by 50 photographers, and an award ceremony spotlighting artistic innovators, community advocates and entrepreneurs.  Nominations for awardees are being accepted through August 9, 2019 (https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfgNGkhBE28k9UHY67mDhwMhJiZPLTGrBu_UnMFMwwZ7cuA0A/viewform)  The Foto Awards will present awards in three categories: * Self-Expression Award: For bravery in creative expression or personal narratives in photography. * Advocacy Award: For power in photojournalism or use of photography for community advocacy & social justice. * Editorial Award: For inspirational entrepreneurs or innovators.  Nominations are open to all womxn-identified photographers. Nominated photographers will be reviewed by our Host Committee and Youth Advisory Council on August 12, 2019. One Awardee for each category will be selected and announced on September 3, 2019.  The Foto Awards Nomination Deadline: August 9, 2019 Award Celebration: October 4, 2019 For tickets & info, visit: www.lasfotosproject.org/thefotoawards http://www.lasfotosproject.org/thefotoawards NOMINATE A PHOTOGRAPHER (https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfgNGkhBE28k9UHY67mDhwMhJiZPLTGrBu_UnMFMwwZ7cuA0A/viewform?usp=sf_link)   ** Her Choice: Facts, Freedom & Justice ------------------------------------------------------------  Join us for the Opening Reception of Her Choice, Facts, Freedom & Justice (https://www.facebook.com/events/509479556259961/) , a solo show by 17-year old Maya Rosado.  Living in a society constantly at-war over women’s rights, Maya Rosado questions the stigma around reproductive health and the extent to which women have freedom in deciding what to do with their bodies. While exploring the many components of reproductive health by looking at its history and the stories of four unique women, Maya highlights how they take back ownership of their reproductive rights.  Her Choice: Facts, Freedom & Justice Opening Reception August 10, 2019 7 pm - 9 pm Las Fotos Project 2658 Pasadena Ave, Lincoln Heights, CA (https://goo.gl/maps/L7JM8DFmAvPPYv3s6)  90031 (https://goo.gl/maps/L7JM8DFmAvPPYv3s6) https://www.facebook.com/events/509479556259961/  HER CHOICE RSVP (http://www.lasfotosproject.org/rsvp)   ** Our Home Collage Workshop ------------------------------------------------------------ With the work in Adia Millett: Breaking Patterns (https://caamuseum.org/exhibitions/2019/adia-millet-breaking-patterns) in mind, this hands-on workshop presented by the California African-American Museum considers the theme of gentrification and the home. Led by Las Fotos Project teaching artist Ana Rivas (pictured), participants will use a variety of techniques, including photo collage, to envision their ideal home. This family workshop is free to the public.  Our Home Collage Workshop Saturday, August 10, 2019 from 2 pm to 4 pm California African American Museum 600 State Drive, Exposition Park, Los Angeles, CA 90037 (https://caamuseum.org/visit/hours-directions) https://caamuseum.org/programs/kids-teens-and-families/our-home-collage-workshop OUR HOME RSVP (https://www.eventbrite.com/e/our-home-collage-workshop-tickets-62069723213)   ** Fall Semester begins September 16th! ------------------------------------------------------------  Las Fotos Project fall semester begins on September 16, 2019! Current and wait-listed students will be notified of their application status within the next two weeks. Are you a teenage girl between the ages of 13 - 18 and want to join our program? Be sure to fill out our Student Interest form to be placed on the priority list of prospective students. Las Fotos Project Fall Semester Student Programming September - December 2019 Fill out the Student Interest Form to be placed on our list! (https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSebGm_0wrvSa_X_fnw6tt2eDX6zt1SV1L7fNpiDmJ-pOrPaDw/viewform?usp=sf_link) http://www.lasfotosproject.org Student Interest Form (https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSebGm_0wrvSa_X_fnw6tt2eDX6zt1SV1L7fNpiDmJ-pOrPaDw/viewform?usp=sf_link)   ** From Our Archives ------------------------------------------------------------  Ningun Ser Humano es Ilegal By: Christina Montaya, at age 19 International Women's Day March, 2017  https://lasfotosproject.networkforgood.com/projects/59604-thank-you-for-supporting-las-fotos-project  ============================================================ ** Instagram (http://instagram.com/lasfotosproject) ** Twitter (http://www.twitter.com/lasfotosproject) ** Facebook (http://www.facebook.com/lasfotosproject) ** Website (http://www.lasfotosproject.org) ** Tumblr (http://www.tumblr.com/lasfotosproject) ** YouTube (http://www.youtube.com/lasfotosproject) ** Email (mailto:info@lasfotosproject.org) ** Vimeo (https://vimeo.com/lasfotosproject) Copyright © 2019 Las Fotos Project, All rights reserved.  Las Fotos Project is a community-based organization whose mission is to  inspire teenage girls through photography, mentorship, and self-expression.  Our year-round programs teach girls to use cameras in order to explore their  identity, learn about new cultures, build leadership and advocacy skills, and  strengthen their social and emotional wellbeing. We act as a platform that  elevates the voices of girls by creating a space for their ideas to be shared  with their peers and the world.  Our mailing address is: Las Fotos Project 1000 N. Alameda Street, Suite 240 Los Angeles, CA 90012 USA Want to change how you receive these emails? Graham Brown's biggest hits and most memorable stories from more than 3 decades of music  Plus, Country Rebel premieres Brown's 'Church Sessions' performances  Nashville, Tenn. – Country hit-maker T. Graham Brown is set to perform on SiriusXM's Prime County with host Storme Warren on Channel 58 starting Friday, August 9th at 12pm ET / 11am CT. This one hour interview and performance will be aired throughout the week for fans to enjoy. Throughout the show, T. Graham Brown will discuss his career highlights and perform several of his biggest hits including "Darlene," "I Tell It Like It Used To Be," "Wine Into Water" and more.  "Big thanks to brother Storme Warren for being with us and hosting our live show at SiriusXM's Music City Theatre," says T. Graham Brown. "He is such a pro and good friend. He made us all feel like part of the family."  Schedule for T. Graham Brown on Prime Country with Storme Warren: 8/09 12pm ET / 11am CT 8/09 3pm ET / 2pm CT 8/09 11pm ET / 10pm CT 8/10 9am ET / 8am CT 8/11 11am ET / 10am CT 8/11 11pm ET / 10pm CT 8/13 9pm ET / 8pm CT 8/15 6pm ET / 5pm CT  T. Graham Brown Receives Arkansas Traveler Award Recently, T. Graham Brown was surprised at the Independence County Fair in Batesville, Arkansas with the 'Arkansas Traveler' award. This award is an honorary title given to notable individuals who serve as goodwill ambassadors of Arkansas. The honor, bestowed upon Brown by Governor Asa Hutchinson, was presented by Senator James Sturch. Past recipients of this prestigious award include Muhammad Ali, Garth Brooks, Gene Autry, Roy Rogers, Dale Evans, Billy Graham, Bob Hope along with Presidents Franklin D. Roosevelt, Ronald Reagan and Donald Trump.  T. Graham Brown Featured in Country Rebel's 'Church Sessions' As part of the 'Church Sessions' series, produced and presented by Country Rebel (https://2911.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=bf141dbbd818f4f933816b13a&id=79165ea998&e=08cf6d68c7) , T. Graham Brown's acoustic performance of "Hell And High Water" recently premiered and was preceded by "Wine Into Water" on July 21st, and "Darlene" on July 18th. "I Tell It Like It Used To Be" premiered August 1st. Country Rebel's 'Church Sessions' were filmed earlier this year at the Nashville Vineyard Church and include over thirty artists. The series has accrued over 20 million total views to date. Subject: Donation For Your Church
Description: Hello & Greetings,     My name is Henri Prillerman and I am a Program Coordinator for The Child Safety Matters http://www.thechildsafetymatters.com. <http://www.thechildsafetymatters.com.%20>   Our organization donates free child safety kits to schools, churches, and day care centers.  We would like to donate these complimentary child safety kits to the families whose children attend  Christian Science Reading Room .  There is absolutely no cost to you.  We will typically have a local Pediatrician, Dentist, or other community-minded business sponsor the cost of the kits, but for your organization, there will be absolutely no cost at all.     The child safety kits include the following items:     -A fingerprint chart with a safe, non-toxic ink strip  - Instructions for obtaining a DNA hair sample with a heavy gauge storage bag  - Two Safe Shoes Child IDÔ labels  - Two pages of comprehensive safety tips  - A chart to denote any unique physical features  - Forms for parents to document their child’s personal and medical information including their birth date, height, weight, hair and eye color, blood type, allergies and medications  - A dental chart for primary and secondary teeth.     SAMPLE OF KIT CONTENTS:  CLICK HERE <https://drive.google.com/open?id=1El6tn7qLffAf1QiZ0mR9J0yAsn1nCrJ3>      The child safety kits that we will provide to you are widely considered to be the highest quality child safety kits that are available in the United States.  These kits are presently used by thousands of Law Enforcement and Government Agencies throughout the country, including the NYPD, the US National Coast Guard, and the Utah Bureau of Criminal Investigation.     Our child safety kits allow parents to record important information about their child and provide potentially life-saving talking points, which foster meaningful safety discussions between parents and children.     We would like to provide you with enough kits for all of the children that attend your location, as well as your staff’s children, and the non-attending siblings of children who are enrolled at your location. Please provide me with the quantity of kits that we can send to you, at no cost to your location, as well as the best address where we can ship the kits.  Also, please just specify a contact person whom we can ship the kits to the attention of.        Sincerely,  Henri Prillerman  Program Coordinator  www.thechildsafetymatters.com  (520) 276-3621

Subject: Customer Feedback Form [#3043]
Description: Representative's Email *   gonzaleza@csps.com Caller's Name    Jobin Suthergreen Caller's Phone Number 360-376-3293 Publication / Product * Other Comments/Feedback *  Jobin bought a CD (Embraced) through our online shop. When she received the confirmation email she was shocked that it included her name, the last 4 of her credit card and date of expiration. She feels this information should be private and covered by privacy laws. She feels that privacy is a big deal today and TMC/CSPS needs to act accordingly and not email confirmation emails with any cc information. She said that she will not be ordering from the Pub House any longer because of breech of security.  She also ordered Embraced which she could not download. Downloading the CD was incredibly frustrating. She spent a half hour on the phone with Apple following the download instructions and they couldn't get it to work. She had to cancel it and hopes her credit card information will not show up in the cancellation confirmation email.  Action/Answers given * I let her know that I would submit a report of her feedback.

Thanks so much for your kind consideration and I look forward to hearing back from you soon!  Peter Berk (contact info below)  “Nothing You Wear Is More Important Than Your SMILE!”  New SMILE! SOX^™ Brand Lets Kids Express Their Inner Joy, Goofiness, Grumpiness & Happiness with Colorful, Fun & Versatile Collection of Affordably Durable Socks  SMILE! SOX Family Includes Smiley, Goofy, Grumpy, Happy, Jolly & Winky; New Collection Created By Sock Industry Leader Keepers International   CHATSWORTH, CA., JULY 29, 2019 – Taking the phrase “Nothing You Wear Is More Important Than Your SMILE!” to boldly expressive new heights, an innovative new brand calledSMILE! SOX^™ is being introduced to help everyone from little kids to young tweens and women share their innermost feelings in the most creative, colorful, and eye-catching manner possible. Quite A Feat!                                                                                                                                                              Based in Southern California, SMILE! SOX™ is independently owned and part of the Keepers International family. Founded in 1954, Keepers is a pioneering wholesale distributor of premium-quality, high-fashion socks that began by serving independent apparel and shoe stores along with larger regional department and sporting goods stores located on the West Coast. Today Keepers’ socks are sold in Dress, Casual, and Sport styles for men, women and kids at stores all around the world.    Commenting on the launch of the new SMILE! SOX^™ brand, Paul Hockley, President of Keepers International, said, “For more than 65 years we’ve dressed your feet with fashion, comfort and function but we wanted to do something more – something FUN. That’s where the idea of SMILE! SOX^™ was born. Why not make socks that bring joy to people and inspire happiness? If putting on your socks in the morning brings a smile to your face, what better way to start the day and make the world a happier place? SMILE! SOX^™ lift your spirits, promote happiness and brighten everyone’s day. In a world that isn’t always rosy, we all need more reasons to SMILE!”  ###  READY TO WEAR A SMILE!? — SAMPLES UPON REQUEST! Subject: August Newsletter
Description: Fall may be just around the corner, but we’re still enjoying warm days here at Longyear Museum and the Mary Baker Eddy Historic Houses. From a glimpse of our recent all-staff field trip, to a gem from our Research Archive on a favorite vacation spot for early Christian Scientists, to an upcoming book talk in Northern Michigan, we have a summery line-up for you this month! Sermons in Stones New Hampshire's White Mountains were a favorite summer vacation destination for many early Christian Scientists. Learn more in an article from our Research Archive about the building of a Christian Science church in a quaint holiday town. READ NOW Book Talks Book talks by Heather Vogel Frederick, author of our new publication, Life at 400 Beacon Street: Working in Mary Baker Eddy's Household, are still underway!  This month, the Longyear team will travel to Traverse City, Michigan. We hope to see you there! LEARN MORE Staff Field Trip Every summer, the Longyear Museum ?staff takes a field trip. This year's destination: the Spencer-Peirce-Little Farm in Newbury, Massachusetts, and our own Mary Baker Eddy Historic House in Amesbury, Massachusetts. READ NOW Shop unique gifts at the Longyear Store! Paths of Pioneer Christian Scientists SHOP NOW Longyear Museum Mug ? SHOP NOW Vintage Swan Photo with Bible Verse SHOP NOW VISIT THE ONLINE STORE Stay Connected ? ? ? Albertans are frustrated at Liberal policies under Prime Minister > Justin Trudeau, at other provinces protesting the pipelines they want to > build, and more recently at activists who have made the oil sands of > Alberta one of the flashpoints of global environmental protest. > > This frustration is not particularly new. Description: Dear Friends,  Reading Room : First Church, Hoylake Merseyside, Acct no82552   As you cansee from the email below, our Reading Room has a jshonline subscription for RRuse. Last year when we first purchased it we were told by CSPS that we couldnot pay for it as a rolling subscription monthly on our RR account  as we had a debit not credit card andso we would have to buy the ‘card’ that is mailed to us and activated with a code.But this would be for a max 12 months at a time.  We did this at the stated cost of $360 and thecard for activation arrived with no additional customs costs incurred.   When we cameto renew it this year, using the same method as last year, the UK postalservice (GPO) tried to deliver the card sent by you- as your email below- to myaddress (mailing address for all our RR purchases) when I was away. I returned tofind a  GPO notification that the ‘card’was being held by them as I had to pay a £66 customs fee and an £8 Post Officefee for handling the customs matter. If I did not collect by a certain datethen it would be returned to USA. That date had expired whilst I was away. Theitem had shown up on our monthly Reading Room statement though ($360).   So, I rang CSPS on 6th June 2019. Iexplained all this and was told that you had it on your system as awaitingdelivery due to outstanding customs payment from our end. You agreed that itwould be returned to your warehouse soon as undelivered. In the conversation yourrepresentative agreed that she thought no customs duty should be due for it.  I then queried again (as I had last year) whywe could not use our bank debit card as we do use it each month to pay theReading Room account to you. Your representative was very helpful and said thata debit card can usually be used like a credit card for payments to CSPS if ithas a VISA/Mastercard logo on it and our bank has authorised its use for thatpurpose. Your rep. logged our discussion and suggested that I try andre-subscribe using the church debit card and that we would then be charged asecond time but as a monthly rolling $30.  She agreed that if this worked OK then youwould see this on the account and remove the first requested payment of $360once the activation card had been returned back to your warehouse.   Having checked with our Church Treasurer, Ifound that our Church debit card was VISA and so I tried and used itsuccessfully to open a rolling subscription to jshonline and our RR laptop has loggedinto our RR jshonline account just fine.   Since then we have been paying the monthly $30on our  RR account with you as we expectedto do. However, the $360 lump sum charged for the activation card is stillappearing on our monthly statement. Please confirm that this should now beremoved from the statement as we never received the activation card and are nowpaying for the subscription on the monthly basis. Subject: Data Reveals: Cities with the Best Work-Life Balance, Boston Ranks #7 in the US
Description: Hi Rosalee,I have a press release covering a new data-driven study determining the Best Cities for Work-Life Balance 2019 which you can find below. This dataset analyzes a shortlist of 40 U.S. cities and 23 more locations abroad, and is for immediate release. If you have any questions, or would like an exclusive quote, interview, or access to more data, please do not hesitate to contact me. If you think this index would be of interest to a peer, please feel free to pass on my message.Thanks very much,Kind regards, Ricky SuttonPress Relations Manager______________Sweet Spot PRw: sweetspotpr.com  e: ricky@sweetspotpr.com If you do not wish to receive future communications from Sweet Spot PR, please let us know by clicking here.KisiFor immediate releaseBest U.S. Cities for Work-Life Balance 2019 By comparing data on work intensity, institutional support, legislation, and livability, study reveals a ranking of cities based on their success in promoting work-life balance to their citizens.San Diego, Portland, and San Francisco top the index as the cities promoting the most holistic work-life balance in the U.S., compared to the most overworked cities in the U.S. study, Washington D.C., Houston, and Atlanta.On average, employees in Barcelona (30.5 days) and Paris (30 days) take advantage of the most amount of vacation days offered per year, whereas residents in San Francisco (9.7 days), San Diego (9.7 days), Washington D.C. (9.4 days), and Los Angeles (9.1 days) take the least.Boston, United States ranks #7 out of 40 for work-life balance worldwide.Brooklyn, NY, USA, August, 2019—Mobile access technology company Kisi has released a study examining which cities around the world promote the most holistic work-life balance. With the goal of enhancing an individual's personal and professional life through technological innovation, Kisi has endeavored to find out which coveted metropolises worldwide are meeting their residents’ lifestyle demands to make their city a more attractive place overall to work and live. In response to research on office culture, which addresses the needs of the modern employee, this study aims to go beyond generic metrics such as cost of living, nightlife and tourist attractions. Using data relating to work intensity, social well-being, and livability to analyze the interplay between work and life, the index assesses how successful residents are in achieving a healthy work-life balance in the U.S. and around the world.This index is not designed to be a city livability index, nor is it intended to highlight the best cities to work in. Instead, it aims to be a guideline for cities to benchmark their ability to support the fulfillment of residents’ lives by improving the aspects of life that help relieve work-related stress and intensity. With an ever-increasing burnout rate worldwide, self-care and time management are becoming higher priorities. This study was conducted in the hope that it will bring awareness to the multiple ways in which cities and countries can contribute to the overall happiness and well-being of the workforce. This is an excerpt from the full press release. Since this document exceeds the limit allowed via email, please visit this link to view the PDF version of the entire press release: https://sweetspotpr.com/wp-content/uploads/Kisi/WorkLifeBalanceIndex/Boston.pdf. If you prefer to receive the file as an attachment, let me know and I can send it to you in response. To view the results and full methodology of the study, please refer to the results page here: https://www.getkisi.com/work-life-balance-usa

Subject: Editorial comments and corrections
Description: The following information was collected:  Name: Don Paquin  Email: dpaquin@rochester.rr.com  Subscriber: Yes  Subject: Woodstock and the 1960s  Product: Monitor Print Edition  Message: The fiftieth anniversary of Woodstock is nothing to celebrate.  It was a gigantic cockup as most of those events were.  And the generation that grew up in the 1960s has a lot to answer for.  Some examples:  The Clintons (both Bill and Hillary) and the Obamas (both Barack and Michelle) with their disastrous presidency.   The generation that got degrees in the 1960s went on to take over the faculties of our universities and proceeded to ruin said universities.  It might take two or three generations for the surviving ones, after the inevitable bankruptcies of many, to revive real education at those universities.  So far, my children seem to have avoided the moral bankruptcy the 1960s, for which I'd like to take credit but won't as my children (5) were and are a very independent bunch of individuals.  As for my grandchildren, most are too young now to know how they will turn out but since my children seemed to have avoided it maybe they'll communicate that to their children. As for myself, having been graduated from high school in 1957, I was too busy working seven days a week and going to college four nights a week to participate in what I regard as the colossal stupidities of most of my generation.  So, please.  Don't tell me about the changes that generation foisted up our nation.  We are still paying the price.  I still hope that one of these days the nation as a whole will wake up and return to the moral base our founding fathers endowed us with. If you desire any more feedback, you have my email. Feel free to continue the discussion.

Subject: Lesson Spirit [myBibleLesson #4072]
Description: Email Address *   barbaralp@sbcglobal.net Name *    Barbara Pettersen Subject * Lesson Spirit Category * Comment/feedback Operating System Click to choose Browser Click to choose Adobe Acrobat Reader Click to choose Connection Click to choose Message: * I would like to know why you explain the word standard in Isaiah 59:19 as referring to a pole bearing a flag when it has a much deeper meaning. The phrase “shall lift up a standard” is from a Hebrew verb meaning to vanish away, escape; causatively to chase, impel, deliver. So that the verse is telling us that when we are in any trouble God, Spirit will provide an immediate means of escape. Somehow your explanation misses the point of the Bible verse.

Subject: NY Director of Common Sense available to speak to the media on important topics related to kids and media/technology
Description: ------------------------------------------------------------  Samira Sine, NY Director, Common Sense is available to speak to New York-based news outlets on topics related to kids and media/technology  ------------------------------------------------------------  We are living in a time where "new normals" are emerging.  Not all of them are going to be good for our children and our society.  We need to get involved now, in every way.  - Samira Sine, NY Director, Common Sense  ------------------------------------------------------------  Common Sense is is the most important organization today, in the lives of children, addressing:   1. Protecting children online   · Privacy / regulation of social media   · Targeting of kids for in-app purchases (without parental consent)   · Online bullying   2. Media/news literacy   · Where/how kids are getting information (and misinformation)   · Need for media literacy education   · Combating fake news   3. Screen time (digital devices and video games) 4. Helping parents set limits and understand how their kids are using their devices   · Research (or lack thereof) of effects on kids   LATEST:  · Research (July 31, 2019) The State of Kids' Privacy: Evaluating the Safety and Security of Kids' Tech (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQBzQA7sDpPszmqt5WNrGEvbSapjEZ4JlN3s9iFPRtqsGG1FCZ1FJxkSi1Sueouh4Mll7sMRZe1qdTistVr7juKZAz7EFZX2-2Byc8YL6jV55QrBrUwvsBHXO-2BOgyE0hVv-2BRMQ-3D-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs0EGlH1eLj10VGFFbhrkY65N0mmDTTJ-2FQEvY94jTa3HwL-2F3U0MOU3-2FalGvnVs-2FtARvCktJjAZutX6DcygcbTkLRF934FDO-2FfSOAvUPFc-2BN4ethyxK3LriBx-2FdFQtQejVXK7sAElb-2FurQirT-2BFaan919-2F5-2FTG-2BqNNhMSXaegJNBSIj3qadm-2FXdQTuM1Xes-2BZrNeM5PWVsIPm7EvYvOLdM8lOOKz5CjPpe5zXSq7j5ct65TnEMohcDINtrRnoTXEbf38-3D · Statement from James P. Steyer, founder and CEO of Common Sense (Aug. 5, 2019) Gun Control Laws Are Common Sense (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQBzQA7sDpPszmqt5WNrGEvbSapjEZ4JlN3s9iFPRtqsGG1FCZ1FJxkSi1Sueouh4MlnklUGI3i9fJq6HQD-2FREMdBq9ERDfUK4QTOG3C61X5GpohK955ujjC8MVHPcKALrGg-3D-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs0EGlH1eLj10VGFFbhrkY65N0mmDTTJ-2FQEvY94jTa3HwL-2F3U0MOU3-2FalGvnVs-2FtARvCktJjAZutX6DcygcbTkLRF934FDO-2FfSOAvUPFc-2BN4er2do9H6EwQOb-2BxiRd1fgPsbzh1NB4KAmmpXsJfOeqdghJQm5d966pRVLyfVb9o224OAlLg4Wq9Ww-2FoqsHc1GqWCpkI8lVui1JZ8rjwtADP-2FMzdGrgaJPUyOFVGMP2kp0vkTTgxrlO-2FleSv-2Fo0me5NA-3D  MORE RESEARCH (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQBzQA7sDpPszmqt5WNrGEvbTZhNFVILOo1OZFrsoRSxOqqPY75hCudGImLMyxYhFNCw-3D-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs0EGlH1eLj10VGFFbhrkY65N0mmDTTJ-2FQEvY94jTa3HwL-2F3U0MOU3-2FalGvnVs-2FtARvCktJjAZutX6DcygcbTkLRF934FDO-2FfSOAvUPFc-2BN4eiI-2BRIAJdiuX7gZzqCEwnH686ulrfG1n1rUP8N68RHSS9yq33tpvuA-2F4bupjcPtD5emaxvgRbBLzTpH3-2FCESgdWyi6-2F4CHz0If45OiOvdN-2BPmuCMqXBBvckJsE28zQIWUNrHbIyd8FJqOBHatmUe7q8-3D  https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQB0V-2BthcYEdgU4uwSrYfFTa5yDoRWqaX9UHXLIdozWBwjUfADsX6Mw25qR-2BqUzdSxbV-2F9S2B-2F9wBJF12PXPcmhNQ-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs0EGlH1eLj10VGFFbhrkY65N0mmDTTJ-2FQEvY94jTa3HwL-2F3U0MOU3-2FalGvnVs-2FtARvCktJjAZutX6DcygcbTkLRF934FDO-2FfSOAvUPFc-2BN4ei6eqs8p9C6yX2dZwMhFFn0lYMvv1Ownm8jAcOElZ3yEF3hOokxHk2gjKCo4UnEt4gn0EF5dvFURrLWJLfSToe4JfEFPLejdBw5JZhkCDswxtyl-2FvK3EWP3hdbgGEvZVaBeyQ06d0GXSD1ArECxIg-2BY-3D  Q & A WITH SAMIRA SINE,  NY DIRECTOR, COMMON SENSE  Why did you join Common Sense?  It was a no-brainer. Technology is changing childhood and it’s affecting children, all over the world, across socio-economic status, race and religion.  Our kids are on the front lines of a digital revolution. Common Sense is a national nonprofit organization that is devoted to the well-being of children and families as technology permeates and influences virtually every aspect of their lives. From the simplest social interactions to long-term mental health.  We rate media, educate and advocate for children, and we have an independent research arm that helps frame the public dialogue around all the pressing issues that stem from kids growing up in a digital world. While we’re 15 years old, our mission to ensure the digital well-being of children is more relevant and vital than ever.  Why is it important to have a presence in New York state, and in New York City specifically?  San Francisco is the global headquarters for Common Sense, but we have offices across the country. New York is one of the the media and financial capitals of the world and where many of the decisions are made that affect our work. It’s important to find new business and philanthropic partners to support the digital well-being of kids and families.  As the New York director, I work with schools and give "Parent Talks" around our research. I speak to many of the issues that parents and educators face, be it screens and sleep, gaming, screen time, social media and mental health. Our research findings are continually updated with thorough, independent research. We need to keep conducting this research and provide facts to parents, educators, policy makers, business leaders and the tech industry.  As a mother yourself, why is the work of Common Sense important?  I am a parent first. With a teen, tween and one young child, I see the perils of technology—and some of the benefits too. We need to empower parents and educators as the acceleration of technology is changing childhood.  We say "sanity, not censorship" when it comes to the use of technology. We produce many in-depth, independent reports on gaming, teens and social media use, and now a groundbreaking report on sleep and screens. Technology is here to stay, and we can all use our Common Sense guidelines to manage the relationship our kids have with it so that they can benefit from it.  I live this every day, and I turn to our advice columns with questions all the time, even though I work here. The challenges are real, and parents, educators, the tech industry, business leaders and policy makers all have to be part of the solutions.   With everything that Common Sense does, what are you most focused on at this time in your role in the state of New York?  Every day is different. I may moderate or speak on a panel about mental health and teens, or speak to parents in schools. I plan events, like our Common Sense Awards, this year honoring Michael Bloomberg and Sesame Street at The Shed.  Parents, teachers, the media and even leaders of tech companies are expressing concerns about the role of technology on the social and emotional well-being of young people. So I am focused on empowering everyone to take charge.   What message do you most want to get to parents, educators and all those who care about the well-being of kids?  We have more power than we think. Today's children are tomorrow's leaders, work force and the foundation of society. We cannot ignore them and we cannot say it is all bad news.  We have to work at a parent level, school level and business and policy level. We have to engage everyone to make sure that we are taking care of the digital well-being of the youngest members of society. This is not just a problem in the U.S. When I speak to friends in India, the Middle East, the U.K, you name it, parents are all facing similar issues.  As personal devices and tech create barriers and compete for our attention, parents can use our guidelines and educators can look at our free K-12 Digital Citizenship Curriculum to help.   What do you think is the news media’s role in this work?  The news media can help by making this part of the national dialogue. We are conducting a real time experiment on our youngest minds, and let’s not forget that this is the most tracked generation. I haven't even started on our privacy work yet, with Common Sense's Kids Action to create laws to protect the interests of our children.  We also want to make sure children are getting the right information from recognized news media. We live in an age of misinformation and children need to be critical thinkers. Children are being bombarded by all kinds of information, but they need to learn how to evaluate it. They are going to go out and vote, and make life-changing decisions and choices, and we need to make sure they have accurate information to guide them. We know that the way young people receive their news is from friends, family and social media. The time to intervene is now.  To request an interview, please contact:  Hannah Gregory  hbg@shoestringagency.org  914-960-4642 (texts ok)  ------------------------------------------------------------ Subject: Editorial comments and corrections
Description: The following information was collected:  Name: Clarence R Cox  Email: bobjunecox@juno.com  Subscriber: No  Subject: 2nd Amendment  Message: The 2nd amendment was written and added to our constitution in the late 1700's. At that time, arms consisted of flint lock rifles and pistols, canons, swords and bayonets. The flint lock guns and rifles were single shot and would take a minute or two to reload. We had thirteen states that were sparsely populated with a lot of distance between neighbors. Our army consisted of local militias that were not very well trained. Police forces were rare and not sophisticated. Residents might have to defend themselves from robbery or savages.  Today, none of that exists. We have sophisticated armed forces and police departments. We don't have to worry about savages. We might want a hand gun for defense against a criminal. We might want a rifle for hunting. Do we need an assault rifle for any of these purposes? Do you think the writers of the 2nd amendment would include assault rifles if they were writing it today?  Assault rifles are weapons of war and are designed for one purpose only and that is to kill people, lots of people very quickly. Assault rifles should not be legal for general public but only for our military.

Subject: Story angle : Alcohol helps sleep? Eating spiders as we sleep?
Description: Stephanie,Americans are more likely than others international to believe that alcohol before bed helps you sleep - so says an international poll on popular sleep myths.https://www.calm.com/blog/most-widely-held-sleep-myths-poll-ranks-top-10They are far more likely to do so than either the British or French, according to the survey of 4,337 American, British and French adults, conducted by pollsters YouGov on behalf of Calm, the sleep and meditation app.22% of Americans believe that pre-bed alcohol aids sleep, compared to just 10% of French and 17% of British respondents – and 17% of respondents overall.  Although folklore – and almost a quarter of Americans – holds that a “nightcap” is a useful sleep aid, science disagrees."While alcohol may calm you and speed the onset of sleep, it actually increases the number of times you awaken during the night,” says the National Sleep Foundation.On a more positive note -- Americans are LESS likely than others to believe that “You swallow a few spiders every year while you sleep”One in four (25%) Americans believe that we eat spiders while we sleep, finds Calm’s poll, compared to 32% of both French and British and 30% of respondents overall.Whatever the truth of this theory – which itself seems to lack evidence – some adherents to the spider-swallowing myth will even quote you precise numbers: that we swallow seven (or is it eight?) spiders a year (or is it a lifetime?).And whatever the original source of the notion, it is, of course, not true. A sleeping person is more likely to scare off a nearby spider than ingest one.10 common sleep myths are ranked in a survey of 4,337 American, British and French adults – conducted by Calm, the sleep and meditation app.https://www.calm.com/blog/most-widely-held-sleep-myths-poll-ranks-top-10https://calm.com/blog/the-10-most-widely-held-myths-and-why-theyre-wrong"There are so many common myths about sleep that we wanted to find out which ones are, in fact, most widely believed," says Michael Acton Smith, co-founder of Calm."Some sleep myths are fairly harmless, while others are seriously dangerous," says Alex Tew, co-founder of Calm.Can I arrange an interview or help in any way further here?Todd Brabender785.842.8909** If this topic isn't of interest simply reply with the word NO in the subject line.I look forward to working with you soon on other topics of interest to you.If you'd rather not get any future email pitches, press releases or story ideas from us, please type remove in the subject line and we won't contact you on any topic further moving forward. Thnx!  --  To unsubscribe from this group and stop receiving emails from it, send an email to customerservice+unsubscribe@csps.com.

Description: Thank you for understanding...  View this email in your browser (https://mailchi.mp/caapusa/bill-owens-of-caap-215449?e=f4925dc692) https://secure.anedot.com/coalition-of-african-american-pastors-usa/dream-derailed-sponsors?mc_cid=3306093386&mc_eid=[UNIQID] http://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fmailchi.mp%2Fcaapusa%2Fbill-owens-of-caap-215449&mc_cid=3306093386&mc_eid=[UNIQID] Share (http://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fmailchi.mp%2Fcaapusa%2Fbill-owens-of-caap-215449&mc_cid=3306093386&mc_eid=[UNIQID]) http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Ingraham+Rescheduled+and+a+Note+from+Deborah:&mc_cid=3306093386&mc_eid=[UNIQID] https%3A%2F%2Fmailchi.mp%2Fcaapusa%2Fbill-owens-of-caap-215449 Tweet (http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Ingraham+Rescheduled+and+a+Note+from+Deborah:&mc_cid=3306093386&mc_eid=[UNIQID] https%3A%2F%2Fmailchi.mp%2Fcaapusa%2Fbill-owens-of-caap-215449) http://us6.forward-to-friend.com/forward?u=92112f469785e1152be1993c1&id=3306093386&e=f4925dc692 Forward to a Friend (http://us6.forward-to-friend.com/forward?u=92112f469785e1152be1993c1&id=3306093386&e=f4925dc692)   ** Ingraham Rescheduled and a Note from Deborah... ------------------------------------------------------------ Dear Partner,  Hello. This is Deborah. I wanted to touch base with you after a tumultuous few days.  Bill's appearance on the Ingraham Angle on Monday night had to be postponed for personal reasons. Fortunately, they were able to reschedule him for tonight (Tuesday). So don't forget to tune into Fox News tonight at 10pm (EDT). He'll be talking about his CNN interview (among other things). It's very exciting!  After the horrifying events in El Paso and Dayton, I've been troubled by some of the things I've seen on social media, from "talking heads," and even from some Democratic candidates  Like so many of you, I'm saddened by the loss of innocent life. I wish I had the answers that would put an end to such violence - how to stop the hate, how to heal the troubled minds behind these acts.  What I don't like is the blame game. We didn't blame President Obama for the massacre at Sandy Hook or President Clinton for the Columbine killings. We should not be using these tragedies to point fingers or advance a political agenda. Sometimes I wonder if there are groups who have press releases already filled out, just waiting to fill in the names of the next tragedy so they can score their political points.  What we should be doing is mourning and uniting in a time of sorrow. We should be doing some soul searching. We should be listening to each other, not shouting at one another.  We have so many freedoms in America, but sometimes we take advantage of the wrong ones. We speak, but we don't hear. We value press over respect for others and even the truth. We confuse the difference between freedom of religion and try to make it freedom "from" religion.  I am so tired of seeing people leap to turn tragedy into a political weapon. I can't speak for others, but personally, I'll be tuning out the noise from the media and politicians and looking for ways I can spread unity in my own community.  For faith, family and freedom, Dr. Deborah Owens  P.S. Your prayers and financial support will help us put this country on the right path. Subject: talk to "smart people" about God
Description: Dear Editors,   After reading “How can I talk to ‘smart people’ about God?” in the August issue of the Journal, I wanted to add my own answer to the question.  I hope you don’t mind!   Q: How can I talk to my friends about God and Christian Science when they say intelligent people are too smart to have faith or believe in a higher power?   A:  With respect, humilty, and fearlessness!  Why fearlessness?  Because the question implies that atheism has a reason to feel smug, while thought accustomed to turning to God is on the defensive.  Right from the start, we don’t want to buy into that notion.  We do have something precious to share, something that humanity is deeply yearning for.   Actually, the fact is quite the opposite of that premise.  Intelligent people are too smart to be ignorant of the source of all being, and the true nature of reality.  Stated in human terms, they are too smart to believe that they already have everything all figured out, and whatever does not fit their rigid conception of reality is worthy of scorn.  That is decidedly not a scientific frame of mind!   Since evolution regards random occurences as the driver of the development of all forms of life, I like to think of atheism as faith in chance, whereas acknowledging God as Creator is faith in intelligence.  Most intelligent people would not choose to place their trust in chance over intelligence.  We can marvel at what people are willing to believe chance is capable of creating!   One of the most arresting statements I know of — and a perfect pivot for this kind of conversation — is from Science and Health, p. 313:  “Jesus of Nazareth was the most scientific man that ever trod the globe. He plunged beneath the material surface of things, and found the spiritual cause.”   And how do you know that all the works attributed to Jesus are not simple legend or pure fabrication?  Why, from your own life, and the experiences of your family members and fellow church members, of course!  You know because you have found you can turn to this Science in every situation for consistent healing results.  Sharing some of those healings with your friends, as well as the fact that you trust your health to this scientific practice, clearly shows that for you, religion is not dogma and ritual — which is generally how non-religious people view religion.   Here, the laws of aerodynamics provide a useful example.  Before these laws were understood, maybe the idea of a hot air balloon, or a light-weight glider, would be acceptable.  But a jumbo jet?  A flying machine weighing hundreds of tons, capable of carrying hundreds of people and delivering them safely to distant destinations?  What intelligent person could possibly believe such a preposterous notion as that?  Yet, an idea that would have been ridiculed and scorned has now become universally accepted, simply because the laws behind it have been understood and demonstrated.  And we feel we can trust our lives safely to an all-good God, because we are learning to understand and demonstrate His laws.    ?Sincerely,  Robin Smith  303-815-2248 3076 S Grape Way Denver, CO 80222

Subject: Re: Why El Paso is determined not to roll up the welcome mat
Description: Listening for the voice of Love, not hate I believe that we as a people are love.  That love is our deepest truth and truest part of our being.  I also believe that God's gift of free will is the source of our greatest triumphs and deepest despair.  It means to me that our current troubles will end when we have had enough of fear and hate.  When we realize that we have gone too far down a dark road and must return to our true self.  It our job to show those around us what love is.  Love is not responding to hate with more hate, yet neither is it sitting passively by waiting for a decree from the Almighty.  It is working to change the situations that are fueling the hate, it is showing the world that love is not passive, love is involved in making the world better.  In my case it is working with my Buddhist Temple to feed the homeless here in San Diego.  It is also working with people to show that there are ways to address gun violence.  In short, it is getting involved to make my part of the world a kinder and gentler place.  Bruce Higgins San Diego brucehiggins1253@gmail.com  On Wed, Aug 7, 2019 at 3:17 PM Monitor Daily <daily@csmonitor.com> wrote:  > [image: The Christian Science Monitor Daily] > > Going beyond the headlines with the ideas driving progress. > > August 07 > Full Version > > <https://www.csmonitor.com/Daily/2019/20190807?cmpid=ema:ddp:20190807&src=email> > [image: headphones icon] Listen > <https://www.csmonitor.com/Daily/2019/20190807?cmpid=ema:ddp:20190807&src=email&id=full-audio-block> > > Welcome to the Daily. Subject: MIRANDA LAMBERT RELEASES “MESS WITH MY HEAD”
Description: View this email in your browser (https://mailchi.mp/7a77ddd79a6c/miranda-lambert-releases-mess-with-my-head?e=1acc59e421) FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE August 9, 2019  MIRANDA LAMBERT RELEASES “MESS WITH MY HEAD” NEW SINGLE “IT ALL COMES OUT IN THE WASH” ACHIEVES CAREER BEST FIRST-WEEK ADDS https://truepublicrelations.us12.list-manage.com/track/click?u=12625cf9000644aef0f718377&id=399f9137c3&e=1acc59e421 (Photo Credit: Ellen von Unwerth) Download JPEG (https://truepublicrelations.us12.list-manage.com/track/click?u=12625cf9000644aef0f718377&id=a07d748400&e=1acc59e421) NASHVILLE, Tenn. – Miranda Lambert continues to fuel rampant anticipation for her upcoming studio album, releasing her latest track “Mess with My Head” today on Vanner Records/RCA Records Nashville.  “'Mess with My Head’ is a departure from anything that I’ve done before,” said Lambert. “It has a real rock edge. Part of that comes from my co-writers, Luke Dick and Natalie Hemby, and the other part of that comes from spending time in New York City. Being there has put a new energy into my music and my writing.”  Her recently-released single “It All Comes Out in the Wash” set a career high upon its release to country radio on July 21, with 112 Billboard and Mediabase/Country Aircheck stations and SiriusXM The Highway onboard in its first week. Co-written by Lambert and The Love Junkies (Hillary Lindsey, Lori McKenna, Liz Rose), critics have praised the “infectious, tongue-in-cheek tune” (Billboard) as a “delightful, sprightly rocker” (Rolling Stone) and a “cute-as-hell country bop” (NPR). The Grammy Award winner also responded to fan demand by dropping “rockabilly banger” (Stereogum) “Locomotive,” which she recently performed on “CMA Fest” and co-wrote with Ashley Monroe and K.S. Rhoads.  “It All Comes Out in the Wash,” “Mess with My Head,” and “Locomotive” are available now on all streaming platforms and digital retailers (https://truepublicrelations.us12.list-manage.com/track/click?u=12625cf9000644aef0f718377&id=fc1bfe91f6&e=1acc59e421) .  Lambert will hit the road for the Roadside Bars & Pink Guitars Tour this fall, with special guests Maren Morris and Elle King, as well as Pistol Annies, Tenille Townes, Ashley McBryde and Caylee Hammack on various dates (details below). Tickets are on sale now.  Upcoming Tour Dates:  Fairs & Festivals: Saturday, August 10 – Boots & Hearts Music Festival || Oro-Medonte, Ontario Friday, August 16 – Country Thunder Alberta || Calgary, Alberta Friday, August 30 – The Great Allentown Fair || Allentown, Penn. Saturday, August 31 – Borgata Hotel Casino & Spa || Atlantic City, N.J.  Featuring Elle King, Pistol Annies and Caylee Hammack: Friday, September 13 – Mohegan Sun Arena || Uncasville, Conn. Saturday, September 14 – Mohegan Sun Arena || Uncasville, Conn. Thursday, September 19 – Van Andel Center || Grand Rapids, Mich. Friday, September 20 – Huntington Center || Toledo, Ohio Saturday, September 21 – BB&T Arena at Northern Kentucky University || Highland Heights, Ky.  Featuring Elle King, Pistol Annies and Tenille Townes: Thursday, September 26 – Royal Farms Arena || Baltimore, Md. Friday, September 27 – Charleston Coliseum || Charleston, W.Va. Saturday, September 28 – Nationwide Arena || Columbus, Ohio  Featuring Maren Morris, Pistol Annies and Tenille Townes: Thursday, October 3 – Cajundome || Lafayette, La. Friday, October 4 – Smoothie King Center || New Orleans, La. Saturday, October 5 – Centurylink Center || Bossier City, La. Thursday, October 10 – State Farm Center || Champaign, Ill. Friday, October 11 – Pinnacle Bank Arena || Lincoln, Neb. Saturday, October 12 – Denny Sanford Premier Center || Sioux Falls, S.D.  Featuring Elle King, Pistol Annies and Ashley McBryde: Thursday, October 17 – Fargo Dome || Fargo, N.D. Friday, October 18 – Fiserv Forum || Milwaukee, Wisc. Saturday, October 19 – Xcel Energy Center || Saint Paul, Minn. Thursday, October 24 – TaxSlayer Center || Moline, Ill. Friday, October 25 – JQH Arena || Springfield, Mo. Saturday, October 26 – INTRUST Bank Arena || Wichita, Kan.  Featuring Maren Morris, Pistol Annies and Tenille Townes: Thursday, November 7 – John Paul Jones Arena || Charlottesville, Va. Friday, November 8 – Colonial Life Arena || Columbia, S.C. Saturday, November 9 – Amway Center || Orlando, Fla.  Featuring Maren Morris, Pistol Annies and Ashley McBryde: Thursday, November 21 – VyStar Veterans Memorial Arena || Jacksonville, Fla. Friday, November 22 – Infinite Energy Arena || Duluth, Ga. Saturday, November 23 – Greensboro Coliseum || Greensboro, N.C.  About Miranda Lambert: Vanner Records/RCA recording artist Miranda Lambert just released her highly anticipated new country radio single, “It All Comes Out in the Wash.” This fall, with the impending release of a new album, Miranda will embark on her rotating, all-girl “Roadside Bars and Pink Guitars” tour featuring Maren Morris, Elle King, Ashley McBryde, Tenille Townes, Caylee Hammack, and the Pistol Annies. This follows two extensive tours in 2018, “Living Like Hippies” in the winter/spring and “The Bandwagon” summer tour with Little Big Town.  The most decorated artist in the history of the Academy of Country Music, Lambert is the recipient of more than 70 prestigious awards and special honors: 32 ACM Awards (including 9 ACM Female Vocalist of the Year Awards), 13 CMA Awards (Country Music Association), 2 GRAMMY Awards, the Harmony Award (Nashville Symphony), Artist in Residence (Country Music Hall of Fame), the ACM Gene Weed Milestone Award, and several others.  The acclaimed singer/songwriter released six studio albums that all debuted at No. 1 on the Billboard Country Album Charts, including the critically acclaimed double record The Weight of These Wings (2016), Platinum (2014), Four The Record (2011), Revolution (2009), Crazy Ex-Girlfriend (2007) and Kerosene (2005). In addition, she released three albums with her trio, the Pistol Annies.  Her clothing and cowboy boot collection, Idyllwind, is a private-label brand sold at all Boot Barn stores nationwide. www.idyllwind.com  MirandaLambert.com (https://truepublicrelations.us12.list-manage.com/track/click?u=12625cf9000644aef0f718377&id=5fa6a18b43&e=1acc59e421) | Facebook (https://truepublicrelations.us12.list-manage.com/track/click?u=12625cf9000644aef0f718377&id=6cc350f220&e=1acc59e421) | Twitter (https://truepublicrelations.us12.list-manage.com/track/click?u=12625cf9000644aef0f718377&id=220c3e7fa7&e=1acc59e421) | Instagram (https://truepublicrelations.us12.list-manage.com/track/click?u=12625cf9000644aef0f718377&id=64e39b886a&e=1acc59e421) | YouTube (https://truepublicrelations.us12.list-manage.com/track/click?u=12625cf9000644aef0f718377&id=45691491f5&e=1acc59e421)  Media Contacts: Allen Brown, Courtney Beebe Sony Music Nashville Allen.brown@sonymusic.com (mailto:Allen.brown@sonymusic.com) / Courtney.beebe@sonymusic.com (mailto:Courtney.beebe@sonymusic.com)  Marcel Pariseau TRUE Public Relations marcel@truepublicrelations.com (mailto:marcel@truepublicrelations.com)  ============================================================ Copyright © 2019 True Public Relations, All rights reserved.
