Subject: Win MDA Wednesdays 2020 Golden Pass
Description: WE NEED YOUR HELP! NOMINATE "MDA WEDNESDAYS at LA CAVE" for OC WEEKLY'S BEST NIGHTCLUB 2019  Thank you to all who helped us win this category last year. We would love to keep the momentum going for our 11 year anniversary.  Please help support us by nominating "MDA Wednesdays at La Cave" for BEST NIGHTCLUB now thru August 23. Subject: INTERVIEW Mom Making A Difference
Description: Hi Stephanie?,  Can we schedule an interview next week with mompreneur, Joyce Dales (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQByU94IP3l-2BxvYE2nOqAXdDo-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs1BHFPaVY1pA3wD3v84CYIYHLKCedKIInfMKv6vW-2FPwxsq4gIUmj8Hrjfe6fH1VmF94sLD7P89YI9UVrBdS2gyhFP0TmV3vzDoAFig9NP3ZVV8xrFWeNHepSCCZbhXkfXmxWJ1i9IBmkuU6Rd6ovxJd9w4TV2yypRxi7EosvKoCqBDKCEhyCL5bfTOqQLib06H5iWJwrFmYD9KHjwCVYZxZcoUBrh6NRh-2BzqkLWm-2FGd7CmXPp6jo3mbf4TnaEhnugE-3D ?  National Honey Bee Day is on August 17th  and Joyce developed Cold Bee Gone to protect her daughter during her recovery from open heart surgery.   Due to grit, passion and getting connected in the local business ecosystem Joyce has been able to get Cold Bee Gone in over 2,700 CVS Stores!  Joyce is sought after health and wellness speaker speaking on how to fight cold and flu season AND currently runs her company on the road while homeschooling her two girls from their 1972 Airstream.   Editorial Connections  August 17 National Honey  August 21 World Entrepreneur's Day   Let me know!  Warmly,  Heather  CEO of Publicity For Good  614.565.0996  heather@publicityforgood.com  HONEY-BASED REMEDY COMPANY PARTNERS WITH NEW ENGLAND NON-PROFIT GROUP FOR NATIONAL HONEY BEE DAY INITIATIVE Buzzagogo, LLC Joins Forces with Appalachian Headwaters to Help Restore Local Ecosystems  [Lewisburg, WV, August 7, 2019] — All-natural homeopathy brand Buzzagogo, LLC (coldbeegone.com (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=1khm074moDjOB00TX7z3nurpZZYgZ6gbJoihF4YwRX0-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs1BHFPaVY1pA3wD3v84CYIYHLKCedKIInfMKv6vW-2FPwxsq4gIUmj8Hrjfe6fH1VmF94sLD7P89YI9UVrBdS2gyhFP0TmV3vzDoAFig9NP3ZVTWkfIyPyJRyOjteplV-2BTd98DoEhO3wFlDRTTYzlwFD8-2FX-2B1-2FqlIbH9sLaD4LK-2F-2Fnph6h-2BIi24n0JCrdyr3S6W06h7rPRBmSZL545tOPWti-2FaFifAe4E-2FlotMbv-2B1X4SbW-2F3bqulP4I3Hk4jC1W7sGQ-3D ) announced their support of Lewisburg, WV-based non-profit group Appalachian Headwaters, which works to create local jobs and restore local honey bee ecosystems, just in time for National Honey Bee Day on August 17, 2019. National Honey Bee Day was started in 2009 by beekeepers to promote and educate the public about the bee industry, and Buzzagogo with Appalachian Headwaters are on a mission to support and train former coal miners to learn the art, science and business of earning a sustainable income through beekeeping.  “I started Cold Bee Gone in my home in a small town, so I understand how small businesses can directly affect smaller communities in positive ways. I also understand what it means when an industry that’s supporting an entire community goes under,” begins Joyce Dales, CEO and founder of Buzzagogo, LLC. “I’ve always been interested in getting involved in great causes, but Appalachian Headwaters is a bee-related organization that demonstrates measurable real-life results. The bee industry supports our ability to create our best-selling Cold Bee Gone remedy, and without that honey, I would never have been able to start my own company. This project directly helps the bee population and small, local economies, so aligning myself with them was a no-brainer.”  Joyce developed Cold Bee Gone to protect her daughter during her recovery from open heart surgery.  The product is a unique blend of homeopathic ingredients—a proprietary honey blend which includes Active Manuka honey and essential oils. Cold Bee Gone is Buzzagogo’s primary product and is currently held in over 2,700 CVS stores nationwide, is an official sponsor of the Boston Red Sox and was pitched at this year's Walmart Open Call event.  For more information on Buzzagogo and their new partnership please visit coldbeegone.com (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=1khm074moDjOB00TX7z3nurpZZYgZ6gbJoihF4YwRX0-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs1BHFPaVY1pA3wD3v84CYIYHLKCedKIInfMKv6vW-2FPwxsq4gIUmj8Hrjfe6fH1VmF94sLD7P89YI9UVrBdS2gyhFP0TmV3vzDoAFig9NP3ZVcswKTTR5XQiCZmBYY4gpc1XgG3-2Fj9SBDjYTbjwuZsW1PtfEjkrQKguYJLDNzaiST0yfVyys8-2BSc6dgzLhlFwW2MevdUk1fWxe5QWUZ9xkACrBpSlSv0F-2B5dMd0u86aNop2-2FI-2Bve8uwPps-2BaMIezhTc-3D  or contact Heather DeSantis at heather@publicityforgood.com (mailto:heather@publicityforgood.com) .  ABOUT BUZZAGOGO, LLC  Joyce Dales is the CEO of Buzzagogo and the maker of Cold Bee Gone, a homeopathic, Manuka Honey based remedy that you swab in your nose to fight cold, flu, allergies and to protect the nasal biome. Joyce is a mom to two beautiful girls through the gift of international adoption. She and her husband Jeffrey run their company while homeschooling, as they travel the country in their 1972 Airstream. Cold Bee Gone is now sold nationwide online and in CVS.    ______________________  If you would rather not receive future communications from Publicity for Good, please go to https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=mAHw-2B8ZZluKmvldupnv96thMD1zlLZCHpeDU8OrMyvXzo4sKkt7qe5rCVFdc-2FhduOXQVF9m92hBC5QAUQEtSjSO8CEweqUVJuE0km3rUWVyBYr-2B3FNA7uT-2BK40ag8sypF5PYLyBl-2BTIbpHpndZFsoVaYjpxsFTmXiCaao852uL4mp-2F5xHzklw6GQTcGnslny_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs1BHFPaVY1pA3wD3v84CYIYHLKCedKIInfMKv6vW-2FPwxsq4gIUmj8Hrjfe6fH1VmF94sLD7P89YI9UVrBdS2gyhFP0TmV3vzDoAFig9NP3ZVapeHINYA8TQV2M2vgOBDAIN-2Fdctg96CQVdXoeIHjLs8XSzX-2FHNCeL-2FtdiFT8-2Bz2nSplVTj1nrAdottitVXFGOjS3ujj6euBUOiP5Ejpxx0E7ktvV5i85FGfCpjd-2BXKRqCqdqjgJsxTnRSi-2FSgURhY4-3D  Publicity for Good, 2134 Stancrest Road, Dublin, OH 43016 United States  --  To unsubscribe from this group and stop receiving emails from it, send an email to customerservice+unsubscribe@csps.com.

William Blake "Hell, there are no rules here -- we're trying to accomplish something." Thomas A. Edison "Institutions don't respond until they have to." But nearly two > decades of civil war wiped out 95% of the park’s wildlife. > > The havoc and devastation that war brings to human communities is well > documented. But the problem of badly prepared or imposter “service” dogs > is growing ?– possibly threatening the image and acceptance of the real > thing. > > – Noelle > The 30 Sec. Read > > “Mylie” had a vest and a service dog certificate. But in a recent incident > at a Georgia beach, witnesses say she alarmed children and parents with > aggressive and out-of-control behavior that drew a police response. > > The final story of this altercation hasn’t yet been established, but in > general the issue of fake or poorly trained service dogs is a real American > problem. There aren’t many legal standards that service dogs, emotional > support dogs, and therapy dogs must meet. Nor is there a national registry > for trained animals. Vests and laminated cards don’t mean much – they can > be easily bought on the internet. The result is owners passing off badly > prepared animals or family pets as “service” dogs. > > Altercations in stores, on beaches, and at airline seats have become so > bad almost half the states have passed laws banning fake service animals in > recent years. How can you tell if that Chihuahua at the cafe table is a > real service animal? It should be calm, under control, and housebroken, > experts say. Subject: 6 Sources for Back-to-School Stories to Help Parents & Their Kids Succeed in September
Description: Hi Stephanie,  Reaching out to let you know I have clients available as sources for interviews around Back-to-School stories. Each has a different area of expertise to help children, teens/college students and even parents ease anxiety, face bullies, manage time, excel at learning and social situations, and transition into a successful school year. Please let me know if you are interested in speaking with any of them, learning more, or receiving a copy of their books.  Thanks in advance for your feedback and consideration.  Have a great day,  Joelle  ----  SOURCE: Heather Hansen (https://heatherhansenpresents.com/) , partner at O’Brien and Ryan law firm, anchor at the Law and Crime network, host of The Elegant Warrior podcast. Also has a psychology degree.  Book: The Elegant Warrior: How to Win Life’s Trials Without Losing Yourself  Topic: How students can advocate for themselves and how parents can help.  1. Parents of young children who are going to school and need to learn to advocate for themselves with other students and teachers: As your children head out for the new school year, they will face new challenges. They will need to learn to advocate for themselves effectively. You can help by teaching them the 4 Ps (pause, plan, practice, play).  2.  College students who need to advocate for themselves and stay safe.   As college students head out to their new lives without their parents, they will face new challenges. Some of those are hard, especially in the time of MeToo, frat hazing and social media bullying. Here are some ways they can advocate for themselves in tough situations, using the word DORM as guidance. Discover, Object, Recognize tone and body language, Move  3. Your Child Is Bullied—How to Advocate for Them (Like a Trial Lawyer). There’s very little research on the impact of bullying on parents. But the little we have shows us that parents are the “secondary victim” and Hansen’s advocacy tools can definitely help parents. One big factor is the relationship between parent and teacher and working to prevent animosity there. A good advocate needs to create allies and not enemies.   Links: Connect with Heather Hansen on Facebook @HeatherHansenPresents (https://www.facebook.com/heatherhansenpresents/) , Twitter @ImHeatherHansen (https://twitter.com/imheatherhansen) , Instagram @ImHeatherHansen (https://www.instagram.com/imheatherhansen/?hl=en) , LinkedIn @HeatherHansen (https://www.linkedin.com/in/heather-hansen-84243512/) , YouTube (https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC2ecu4d4mKYZuh9QE9ZWhmA) , and visit www.heatherhansenpresent.com (http://www.heatherhansenpresent.com) .  ------  SOURCE:  John J. Murphy (http://www.johnjmurphy.org/) , global business consultant, speaker, spiritual mystic, "zentrepreneur,” award-winning author, former quarterback for Notre Dame.  Book: Miracle Minded Manager: A Modern Day Parable about How to Apply A Course in Miracles in Business releases on October 22, 2019 in paperback and e-Book.  Topic: As September nears, so does fear and anxiety for parents who have to entrust the safety and well-being of their kids to schools. Murphy can share tips for parents to overcome a fear-based mindset, adopt a miracle-minded way of thinking, and find inner peace when faced with challenging situations: Let be, let go, let see, and let flow.  “People all over the world are stressed,” says Murphy. “More importantly, people are stressed and they are not aware it is a condition of their own making. The ego mindset is projecting a negative outcome or possibility onto the future and when we dwell on what could go wrong, we feel anxious and afraid. These negative assumptions, projected by the mind, are triggering fear and stress. It is like being nervous before giving a speech or taking an exam. We are nervous because we ‘think’ something might go wrong. Mindful parenting is essential to helping mothers and fathers see things differently - by teaching them to see in a different way, a miracle-minded way.”    Links: Connect with John J. Murphy on Facebook @Author.John.J.Murphy (https://www.facebook.com/Author.John.J.Murphy/?notif_t=page_new_likes) , Twitter @sageleader (https://twitter.com/sageleader) , LinkedIn @johnjmurphymystic (https://www.linkedin.com/in/johnjmurphymystic/) , YouTube @AuthorJohnJMurphy (https://www.youtube.com/user/AuthorJohnJMurphy?feature=mhum) , Instagram @jjmurphy13 (https://www.instagram.com/jjmurphy13/) and visit www.johnjmurphy.org (http://www.johnjmurphy.org) .  ------  SOURCE: Kerry Goyette, CEO & Founder of Aperio Consulting Group, Certified Professional Behavior Analyst and Certified Forensic Interviewer with postgraduate studies in psychometrics.  Book: The Non-Obvious Guide to Emotional Intelligence. Named among the Best Business Books For Summer 2019 by Forbes (https://www.forbes.com/sites/johnhall/2019/06/20/best-business-books-for-summer-2019/#4e27666a5ac6) and among 7 Books on Relationship Building Every Entrepreneur should read by Forbes (https://www.forbes.com/sites/rhettpower/2019/07/29/7-books-on-relationship-building-every-entrepreneur-should-read/#1572d0b84e7c) and featured on Bloomberg TV (https://www.bnnbloomberg.ca/video/how-emotional-intelligence-can-make-your-business-more-successful~1731090) .  Topic: Teaching Children Emotional Intelligence  IQ is increasing (24 points) while at the same time Emotional Intelligence (EQ) is declining over the past 3 decades. Raising emotionally intelligent children increases their self-confidence, performance in school, and deepens their social relationships and resilience. If emotional intelligence is such a key to a successful future, how can parents teach it to children? Kerry has the answers.  Links: Connect with Kerry Goyette on Facebook @thinkaperio (https://www.facebook.com/thinkaperio/) , Twitter @AperioCG (https://twitter.com/AperioCG) ,  and LinkedIn @aperio-business-consulting (https://www.linkedin.com/company/aperio-business-consulting/) and visit www.thinkaperio.com (http://www.thinkaperio.com/) .  -----  SOURCE: Kindra Hall, MA (http://www.kindrahall.com/) , sought-after keynote speaker trusted by global brands (including Facebook, Hilton Hotels, Tyson Foods, Target, Berkshire Hathaway and Harvard Medical School), a National Champion storyteller and former member of the Board of Directors of the National Storytelling Network.  Book: Stories That Stick: How Storytelling Can Captivate Customers, Influence Audiences, and Transform Your Business (http://www.storiesthatstick.com/) [HarperCollins Leadership September 24, 2019]  Topic: How to use stories to help your child through difficult times and how to teach your child to tell stories and excel in new social situations.  "A perfectly placed, impeccably delivered story can transport a person to a place beyond interested, straight past paying attention, and into a state of complete captivation,” says Hall. "Stories are the ultimate influencer. Stories can change how we see ourselves and lead our lives.”  Links: Connect with Kindra Hall on Instagram @kindrahall (http://www.instagram.com/kindrahall) , LinkedIn @KindraHall (http://linkedin.com/in/kindrahall) , Twitter @kindramhall (https://twitter.com/kindramhall) and Facebook @kindrahallfan (http://facebook.com/kindrahallfan) , and visit kindrahall.com (http://kindrahall.com/) .  -----  SOURCE: Robin Moriarty Ph.D., (http://www.gutsy.world/) the global business executive, and professor who has lived on four continents and traveled to over 60 countries.  Book:  What Game Are You Playing?: A Framework for Redefining Success and Achieving What Matters Most [Greenleaf Book Group, September 10, 2019]  Topic: How parents can design a career that allows them freedom to be more present in their kids lives. Moriarty empowers people to be gutsy enough to exercise agency over their lives and offers an accessible framework for achieving what matters most. She enables readers to gain awareness of the way they want to live their lives, redefine success on their own terms and map out what they will need to do to get there. Moriarty helps readers recognize—and then step away from—the expectations of others to truly soar.  Links: Connect with Robin Moriarty at www.gutsy.world (http://www.gutsy.world)  -----  SOURCE: Lisa Canning, a parenting, lifestyle and interior design expert. Lisa has become a recognizable face in the interior design and entertainment industry, as the designer on HGTV’s Marriage Under Construction, working on the design team of “Buying and Selling with the Property Brothers.”  Book: The Possibility Mom: How to be a Great Mom and Pursue Your Dream at the Same Time (https://www.amazon.com/Possibility-Mom-Great-Pursue-Dreams/dp/1642792640) [July 16, 2019],  Topic: Helping moms define their own success with motherhood, work and life, eliminate guilt, get more done and design the life of their dreams. She even designed a quiz, “What’s Your Mom Super Power (https://go.bucketquizzes.com/sf/26ec2dc6) ?” to help moms discover their strengths.  Links: Connect with Lisa Canning on Facebook @lisacanningthepossibilitymom, Instagram @lisacanning, Twiter @lisa_canning and Pinterest @lisacanning, and visit www.liscanning.ca (http://tcismith.pr-optout.com/Tracking.aspx?Data=HHL%3d9%2c%3a%2f%3b0-%3eLCE58451%40%26SDG%3c90%3a.&RE=MC&RI=5502999&Preview=False&DistributionActionID=128809&Action=Follow+Link)  ______________________ If you would rather not receive future communications from Smith Publicity, please go to http://tcismith.pr-optout.com/OptOut.aspx?519228x41334x218108x1x5080076x24000x6&Email=customerservice%40csmonitor.com. Subject: Today: Don't Miss These Talented Teens Singing to Give Hope in a Divided Nation???
Description: Free & Open to the Public  96  * *  Image  An Interracial Cast of Talented Teens Sings Songs of the 1960s  This Thursday & Friday, 5pm  Prospect Terrace, 54 Congdon Street Providence  Free & Open to the Public!  Image  INTERRACIAL CAST OF TEENS PERFORMS A TRIBUTE TO THE 1960s  A unique ensemble of 8 talented teens will perform some of America’s greatest songs from the 1960s in “Sounds of the 60s: From the Blues to the Beatles” on Thursday and Friday, August 8th & 9th, 5:00pm, at Prospect Terrace, 54 Congdon Street, Providence. The original show is free and open to the public.  The teen ensemble has spent two weeks rehearsing six hours a day preparing the show under the musical direction of internationally acclaimed musicians, Michael Palter and Lynne Jackson, and the artistic direction of Robb Dimmick of Providence, learning songs, developing vocal technique, acting skills and choreography, and the history the turbulent 60s. The show and its cast of Black and White youth give us hope in a divided nation.  Jazz is a Rainbow, now in its eighteenth year, has been acclaimed by the US Department of Education, as well as teachers, music educators, community leaders and musicians throughout the world. It is produced by Stages of Freedom and funded by the Providence Shelter for Colored Children, Opera Providence, Rhode Island School of Design, and the Providence Department of Art Culture and Tourism, Providence Parks and Recreation, Mayor Jorge O. Elorza, and Partnership for Providence Parks.  Photo: Front row: Millie Teague; middle row: Sabrie Pearl Griffin,  James Teague, Ambrose Teague, Beyanca Guilme, Roma Taitwood,  Darius Henderson, Jr.; back row: Miguel Figueroa  More About Jazz is a Subject: Can the US congress overturn the Second Amendment which protects the right of Americans to bear arms?
Description: There is a political movement brewing in the United States to try and overturn the Second Amendment   View this email in your browser (https://mailchi.mp/truthpr/can-the-us-congress-overturn-the-second-amendment-which-protects-the-right-of-americans-to-bear-arms-260953?e=21b2dde47d) http://www.TruthPR.com/guests?utm_source=News+Media+Outlets&utm_campaign=377e056095-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2019_08_08_04_02_COPY_06&utm_medium=email&utm_term=0_947852de51-377e056095-65577913 Media Contact: Jackie Jones Jackie@TruthPR.com (mailto:Jackie@TruthPR.com) 662-259-0988 Can the US congress overturn the Second Amendment which protects the right of Americans to bear arms?  Other topics: Immigration, Border Security, ICE.   ** Guest Avail LT Gov Jennifer Carroll (https://www.truthpr.com/guests/jennifer-carroll/?utm_source=News+Media+Outlets&utm_campaign=377e056095-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2019_08_08_04_02_COPY_06&utm_medium=email&utm_term=0_947852de51-377e056095-65577913) ------------------------------------------------------------ Public Speaker, Author, Political Analyst, Public Relations Consultant * First female elected as Lieutenant Governor in Florida and the first African-American and Caribbean elected Statewide. * Former Executive Director of Florida Department of Veterans’ Affairs and a Navy veteran. * Retired as a highly decorated Commander Aviation Maintenance Officer * Immigrant -Immigrated to America from the Republic of Trinidad and Tobago West Indies * Bestseller author When You Get There: An Autobiography (https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1599324997/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=1599324997&linkCode=as2&tag=tr0f8-20&linkId=d5107c7eee2c8dddd3df6412dc1951b5&utm_source=News+Media+Outlets&utm_campaign=377e056095-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2019_08_08_04_02_COPY_06&utm_medium=email&utm_term=0_947852de51-377e056095-65577913) * Florida’s 18th Lieutenant Governor * Florida State Legislator for over seven years * Small Business Owner * National Spokesperson for MaggiesList.org (http://maggieslist.org?utm_source=News+Media+Outlets&utm_campaign=377e056095-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2019_08_08_04_02_COPY_06&utm_medium=email&utm_term=0_947852de51-377e056095-65577913)  “My accomplishments in the military, in government and serving on many non-profit boards has been my way of giving back to a nation that embraced my family and opened doors that may not have been,” states Jennifer. “My role as a national spokeswoman for Maggie’s List is to encourage conservative women to take the challenge and run for congress and help further expand diversity among the congressional ranks for us to have a true representative government.  Topics:  'Serious movement' brewing to overturn entire Second Amendment (https://www.foxnews.com/media/second-amendment-red-flag-laws-mass-shootings?utm_source=News+Media+Outlets&utm_campaign=377e056095-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2019_08_08_04_02_COPY_06&utm_medium=email&utm_term=0_947852de51-377e056095-65577913) : There is a political movement brewing in the United States to try and overturn the Second Amendment (https://www.foxnews.com/category/us/personal-freedoms/second-amendment?utm_source=News+Media+Outlets&utm_campaign=377e056095-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2019_08_08_04_02_COPY_06&utm_medium=email&utm_term=0_947852de51-377e056095-65577913)  in its entirety, and do away with a citizen's right to keep and bear arms.  LEGISLATORS IN HAWAII, WHICH HAS SOME OF THE MOST RESTRICTIVE GUN LAWS IN THE UNITED STATES, MOVED TO BRING THEIR CONCERNS ABOUT THE SECOND AMENDMENT TO THE NATIONAL LEVEL. (http://preparedgunowners.com/2019/04/02/one-state-is-trying-to-overturn-the-second-amendment/?utm_source=News+Media+Outlets&utm_campaign=377e056095-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2019_08_08_04_02_COPY_06&utm_medium=email&utm_term=0_947852de51-377e056095-65577913) Rep. Kinzinger says there's a movement brewing in the U.S. to abolish the Second Amendment (http://video.foxnews.com/v/6069176120001?utm_source=News+Media+Outlets&utm_campaign=377e056095-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2019_08_08_04_02_COPY_06&utm_medium=email&utm_term=0_947852de51-377e056095-65577913)  Illinois Republican Rep. Adam Kinzinger proposes raising the age to purchase a firearm to 21, banning certain high capacity magazines and universal background checks -- but warns of overshoot.  "We have to make societal differences and changes... attitudes are turning so much against the Second Amendment that the thing that we risk is that there will be a serious movement to not just create restrictions but to overturn the whole amendment. Now, by the way, your freedom of religion is protected by the First [Amendment (https://www.foxnews.com/category/us/personal-freedoms/first-amendment?utm_source=News+Media+Outlets&utm_campaign=377e056095-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2019_08_08_04_02_COPY_06&utm_medium=email&utm_term=0_947852de51-377e056095-65577913) ]. If we begin to start to repeal the Bill of Rights, who knows where this whole thing goes."  https://www.truthpr.com/guests/jennifer-carroll/?utm_source=News+Media+Outlets&utm_campaign=377e056095-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2019_08_08_04_02_COPY_06&utm_medium=email&utm_term=0_947852de51-377e056095-65577913   ** Lt. Gov. Jennifer Carroll (https://www.truthpr.com/guests/jennifer-carroll/?utm_source=News+Media+Outlets&utm_campaign=377e056095-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2019_08_08_04_02_COPY_06&utm_medium=email&utm_term=0_947852de51-377e056095-65577913) ------------------------------------------------------------  • Former Executive Director of Florida Department of Veterans’ Affairs and a Navy veteran. • Bestseller author When You Get There: An Autobiography (https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1599324997/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=1599324997&linkCode=as2&tag=tr0f8-20&linkId=d5107c7eee2c8dddd3df6412dc1951b5&utm_source=News+Media+Outlets&utm_campaign=377e056095-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2019_08_08_04_02_COPY_06&utm_medium=email&utm_term=0_947852de51-377e056095-65577913) • Florida’s 18th Lieutenant Governor • Florida State Legislator for over seven years • Small Business Owner  Former Florida Lt. Gov. Jennifer Carroll (https://floridapolitics.com/archives/tag/jennifer-carroll?utm_source=News+Media+Outlets&utm_campaign=377e056095-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2019_08_08_04_02_COPY_06&utm_medium=email&utm_term=0_947852de51-377e056095-65577913) , once a political rising star, will ascend anew on a national stage in a spokeswoman role.  Described as a “patriot and a servant ready to elect more conservative women to office,” Carroll is the new hire by super PAC Maggie’s List (http://www.maggieslist.org/?utm_source=News+Media+Outlets&utm_campaign=377e056095-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2019_08_08_04_02_COPY_06&utm_medium=email&utm_term=0_947852de51-377e056095-65577913) .  In a statement from the group, Carroll described her role with Maggie’s List as “to encourage conservative women to take the challenge and run for congress and help further expand diversity among the Congressional ranks for us to have a true representative government.”  Carroll added that “the work of Maggie’s List in its support of conservative women running and elected to congress will help bring about greater opportunities, improvements and independence.”  “Maggie’s List is ecstatic to have a mom, grandmother, Veteran, former legislator (she was a state representative), former Lt. Governor and Maggie’s List Founding Member as our National Spokeswoman. http://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fmailchi.mp%2Ftruthpr%2Fcan-the-us-congress-overturn-the-second-amendment-which-protects-the-right-of-americans-to-bear-arms-260953&utm_source=News+Media+Outlets&utm_campaign=377e056095-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2019_08_08_04_02_COPY_06&utm_medium=email&utm_term=0_947852de51-377e056095-65577913 Share (http://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fmailchi.mp%2Ftruthpr%2Fcan-the-us-congress-overturn-the-second-amendment-which-protects-the-right-of-americans-to-bear-arms-260953&utm_source=News+Media+Outlets&utm_campaign=377e056095-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2019_08_08_04_02_COPY_06&utm_medium=email&utm_term=0_947852de51-377e056095-65577913) http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Can+the+US+congress+overturn+the+Second+Amendment+which+protects+the+right+of+Americans+to+bear+arms%3F:&utm_source=News+Media+Outlets&utm_campaign=377e056095-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2019_08_08_04_02_COPY_06&utm_medium=email&utm_term=0_947852de51-377e056095-65577913 https%3A%2F%2Fmailchi.mp%2Ftruthpr%2Fcan-the-us-congress-overturn-the-second-amendment-which-protects-the-right-of-americans-to-bear-arms-260953 Tweet (http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Can+the+US+congress+overturn+the+Second+Amendment+which+protects+the+right+of+Americans+to+bear+arms%3F:&utm_source=News+Media+Outlets&utm_campaign=377e056095-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2019_08_08_04_02_COPY_06&utm_medium=email&utm_term=0_947852de51-377e056095-65577913 https%3A%2F%2Fmailchi.mp%2Ftruthpr%2Fcan-the-us-congress-overturn-the-second-amendment-which-protects-the-right-of-americans-to-bear-arms-260953) http://us13.forward-to-friend.com/forward?u=c42848a03537a7f08765c5e4b&id=377e056095&e=21b2dde47d Forward (http://us13.forward-to-friend.com/forward?u=c42848a03537a7f08765c5e4b&id=377e056095&e=21b2dde47d) Copyright © 2019 TruthPR.com, All rights reserved. Subject: Interview Op with Theresa M. Robinson - Overcoming Gender Inequity: Real, Raw, Unapologetic Stories, Tips & Strategies
Description: Dear Stephanie Hanes :  Women who feel overlooked and overjudged as a direct result of gender bias have been given a powerful voice in Theresa M. Robinson's latest release, Overcoming Gender Inequity: Real, Raw, Unapologetic Stories, Tips & Strategies.  Offering an array of immediate, short-term and long-term tactics that can be tailored to many situations, Overcoming Gender Inequity is a must-read for all women who are ready to make their voices heard.  I would be happy to send you a complimentary copy of this thought-provoking book in consideration of an interview, review or feature. Please read the following press release, and contact me to schedule an interview. I'd also be happy to send you JPEGs of Robinson and the book cover. Thank you.  Please see Robinson at youtube.com/channel/UCAEheaz_mUB-ii23hejC6KQ/videos.  Karen Anderson Ascot Media Group, Inc. Post Office Box 2394 Friendswood, TX 77549 news@ascotmedianews.com ascotmedia.com 281.333.3507 Phone 800.854.2207 Fax  (This press release may be reprinted in part or entirety by any print or broadcast media outlet, or used by any means of social media sharing)  FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE  Overcoming Gender Inequity Gives Powerful Voice To The "Herstory” Of Systemic Gender Bias   **Houston, TX, August 6, 2019** — Are you an OVERachiever who still makes less money than her male counterparts? Do men talk OVER you at work? Do you OVERcommit your time and energy and end up OVERwhelmed?  If your answers are "yes,” you are not alone, and international speaker and corporate trainer Theresa M. Robinson has a name for this phenomenon: O-Syndrome.   While conducting research for her first book in this series, O-Syndrome: When Work is 24/7 and You're Not, Robinson observed a clear pattern that confirmed what she'd been hearing women tell her for years: gender issues were a major source of their stress.   "Specifically, women were pointing to the impact of gender bias and gender inequity both inside and outside of the workplace,” Robinson explained. "And adding to this, women of color were contextualizing the intersection of gender and race within their experiences.”   Her powerful follow-up, Overcoming Gender Inequity: Real, Raw, Unapologetic Stories, Tips & Strategies dives deeper into the unique experiences with O-Syndrome faced by a range of women from different industries, at various stages in their careers, and from diverse backgrounds with whom she conducted personal interviews. Robinson expertly — and with refreshing honesty — explores how the obstacles these women faced were informed by their shared experiences with systemic gender bias and discrimination.   "As a facilitator/speaker interacting with audiences all over the world, I am naturally drawn to women and their experiences. Once I issued the formal call about this project, the responses were immediate. Accomplished, professional women were eager to talk more about what they've experienced and what they've learned,” Robinson added. "They detailed the costs of being female in male-dominated environments.”  Overcoming Gender Inequity is divided into three parts: What We Face; What We Do to Ourselves; and What We Want from Allies, and shares stories that transcend title and industry; time and space; ethnicity and generation. Readers will glean valuable lessons from other women who've "been there,” as they share their "aha” moments, their insights, the raucous laughter, the frustrations, and yes, even the tears. This book is a must-read not only for women, but also for men who are ready to advocate for women both in and out of the workplace.   (Of note: The WarriHER's Playbook on Well-Being and Self-Advocacy, third in the series and the companion workbook to Overcoming Gender Inequity, will be released later this year and will contain activities and exercises for both individual and group use.)  Author Theresa M. Robinson is an ATD-certified Master Trainer and professional speaker with international experience in Europe, North America, South America, Australia, Asia and Africa. A seasoned professional with more than 25 years of experience, she is also the founder and president of Master Trainer TMR & Associates, a training consulting firm based in Houston, Texas, that provides corporate soft-skills training, coaching, keynotes and management consulting services in the areas of leadership, team building, communications, diversity and inclusion, and wellness. Averaging more than 50 engagements annually since 2005, Robinson has an impressive client list that includes corporate executives from Microsoft, Novartis, Procter & Gamble, GE, Allstate, ExxonMobil, KPMG, Deloitte, Mars, Nationwide, GlaxoSmithKline, Bristol-Myers Squibb and Walmart.   Married with two adult children, she enjoys reading, journaling, traveling, biking, hiking, powerwalking and yoga.  To learn more and to watch excerpts from Robinson's speaking engagements, please visit http://ascotmedianews.com/em/lt.php?c=18320&m=20681&nl=1198&s=f56e244f21aead307c5458b70ab88d81&lid=272023&l=-http--www.mastertrainertmr.com/ or youtube.com/channel/UCAEheaz_mUB-ii23hejC6KQ/videos. Connect with Robinson on LinkedIn at linkedin.com/in/theresamrobinson; on Twitter at Theresa@MasterTrainerT; and Facebook at facebook.com/MasterTrainerT.  Overcoming Gender Inequity: Real, Raw, Unapologetic Stories, Tips & Strategies Publisher: Master Trainer TMR & Assoc.  Released: March 2019 ISBN-10: 0998842044  ISBN-13: 978-0998842042 Available from Amazon.com  ###  TIP SHEET:  Q & As available upon request.  Excerpts from Reviews:  Kelly Lockwood Primus, Senior Vice President, Leading Women, LLC —  "Having been the only woman in the room for so many years, in so many companies, over the course of my career, it is my greatest hope that this book will provide guidance and strength to all women leaders…."  Shary Hauer, founder of The Hauer Group, executive advisory and coaching firm, and author of Insatiable: A Memoir of Love Addiction — "What a gift Theresa gives us — the telling of shared experiences from wise and courageous sisters … It's from healing our most painful memories that we blossom into self-actualized women. The only antidote to O-Syndrome is to be O-mnipotent! Now is our time to rise to our unlimited power!”   Joan Toth, Senior Consultant, Diversity & Inclusion, Simpactful, and advisory board member, Gender Fair — "Theresa tells it like it is — every woman will relate to O-Syndrome. Get ready to see yourself and your friends, mom, sisters and colleagues in her stories…”   Catherine Mackel, IT specialist, Federal Government — "As I've maneuvered through the information technology field, I've encountered many 'good old boy' networks of men who discriminate at all levels. Through personal examples, Theresa exposes these behaviors. I found myself relating to the indignities. Yet, Theresa left me with an optimistic view for taking charge and overcoming my unfounded feelings of inadequacy.”  Margie Warrell, women's leadership coach, speaker and best-selling author of Stop Playing Safe — "Can women get to the top like men? You bet we can. But let's face it, the climb is steeper and the juggling act that much harder. If you ever wonder if you've got what it takes to last the distance toward whatever ambitions inspire you, this book is for you.”   Possible discussion topics for Theresa M. Robinson:  1)    How to beat burnout when the pressure is on 2)    How to free yourself of giving a damn 3)    How to find fulfillment by ditching the notion of work-life balance 4)    Five tips to keep you sane at work and at home 5)    How to eliminate "mommy guilt” 6)    How to let go of the "superwoman complex” 7)    Leadership lessons to cull from your kids  Ascot Media Group is compliant with the can-spam act. Subject: Hello Anjuli and Reading Room Activities updated

Description: Respected Sir/Madam My name is Urooj Saraj, I am a born Christian and I belong to a Christian family. I born in Faisalabad (Pakistan), I used to go for tuition class in my area in a Muslim house, where I met Adnan, I was studying from Adnan sisters. Once Adnan proposed me for marriage but I refused because in Islamic Republic of Pakistan it not possible as I am I a Christian but he proposed me again and again for months and told me that he will accept Christianity and will be converted from Islam, so then I also agree to marry him, then we planned to go Rawal Pindi for marriage, Pastor Ilyas Masih performed our marriage. After marriage we returned back to Faisalabad to our homes, we were living separately, Adnan was living in his home and I was living in my home but after 2month we decided to live together as we were husband and wife. Adnan was working in a factory and with the help of his boss we got I house on rent near to his factory and stat living together, I was continuously living there and Adnan was spending much time there with me and rest he was staying in his house only, with his parents so that they don’t come to know about our marriage, Adnan father was thoughtful because most of the time after his job he was not returning at home back, so he went and asked Adnan's boss about it, he told him that Adnan got married and he is living in a house of rent with his wife. He came to know that he married me as he knows be from before that I am a Christian, he became very angry. One day I was alone at my home as Adnan was on job, somebody knocked the door I opened the door and saw Adnan parents and many other people were with them, they all beat me very badly as I was two months pregnant and because of that I had a miscarriage, they lifted me half dead and were gone, when Adnan was back he took me to hospital for treatment and we planned to run somewhere or else Muslim will kill us according to SHRIA law in Pakistan, mean that we have committed Blasphemy law and should be Killed. So we went to Sialkot to my brother house to safe our lives but my condition was very critical as i was badly beaten by them, so I went to hospital in Sialkot where I had breast operation, after some days my condition was bit stable and I was able to come back home from hospital but we heard that Muslims are in search of us to kill us, thank God that we met a Pastor in Sialkot who guided us to leave Pakistan or else Muslims will kill us, he gave us the suggestion to go Thailand and apply Asylum. Thanks God that we managed to come Thailand on 11th June 2013 and we applied for Refugee Status, after 2 years in 2015 we had our Refugee interview in UNHCR but unfortunately we got refused from UNHCR in 2017 because may be we were not able to explain them about our self. I had a Testimony also on YOUTUBE ,because of that Adnan lifted me and was gone and the video was viral everywhere and secondly we were refused from UNHCR ,Now I am alone with my two small children as I husband left me from two years, I am spending a very miserable life here as I am illegal staying here with our visa and because of that can’t work also anywhere to feed my children, police immigration is always in search to arrest people without visa to put them in jail, often I am not having money to pay my room rent and facing many problems like food, milk for children, medication etc. I request you to please help me to get out from this critical condition and will be able to live a freedom life in your country where I will be able to get job and my children will be able to go school and can have necessities of life. First of all I trust God and secondly I have hopes on you. May God bless you all, and keep you always happy. Amen.  --  To unsubscribe from this group and stop receiving emails from it, send an email to customerservice+unsubscribe@csps.com.

Subject: Hudson Announces Launch of New Podcast and Media Fellows
Description: Listen to our new podcast: The Realignment  This week, we launched a new podcast called  The Realignment [https://www.hudson.org/research/15229-the-realignment-ep-1-j-d-vance], hosted by newly named Media Fellows Saagar Enjeti and Marshall Kosloff.  The United States is in the midst of a dramatic political realignment. Events such as the unexpected election of Donald Trump, populist revolts across Europe, and the arrival of an aggressive and unapologetic China have upended conventional wisdom. The Realignment is a weekly podcast that will explore these shifting norms in national security, economics, technology, and the role of government.  In Episode 1, Marshall and Saagar sat down with best-selling author of Hillbilly Elegy J.D. Vance. They discussed whether it was a mistake to let China into the World Trade Organization, how conservatives should approach the free market, what it means to be an American Nationalist in 2019, and his skepticism of the technology industry as a venture capitalist.  Click here to listen to the episode [https://www.hudson.org/research/15229-the-realignment-ep-1-j-d-vance].  “I think that we should consider China as our nation should have considered Nazi Germany in the mid-1930's. Only we should recognize that it’s more dangerous because it’s larger and it’s more ambitious. I think that Hitler wanted to rule Europe. I think that China wants to rule over a much larger share of the world—maybe the entire world.” – J.D. Vance ( The Realignment, Episode 1 [https://www.hudson.org/research/15229-the-realignment-ep-1-j-d-vance])  On Tuesday we’ll release Episode 2, featuring an in-depth discussion with conservative thinker and author George Will. The episode covers a wide range of issues including the role government should have in regulating technological advances, how to deal with the threat of a rising China, and whether the United States should pursue a manufacturing-based national economic strategy to confront it.  We hope you join us each week as Marshall and Saagar dive in to the most important issues facing our society today. Click the buttons below to listen and subscribe.  Background on the Hosts  Marshall Kosloff [https://www.hudson.org/experts/1279-marshall-kosloff] is a media fellow at Hudson Institute where he co-hosts The Realignment podcast. Previously, he was a Researcher at PBS’s Firing Line with Margaret Hoover and participated in the Public Interest Fellowship. Marshall earned his bachelor’s degree in political science from the University of Oregon.  Saagar Enjeti [https://www.hudson.org/experts/1278-saagar-enjeti] is a media fellow at Hudson Institute where he co-hosts The Realignment podcast. He also co-hosts Rising on Hill TV. Saagar earned his master’s degree in security studies from Georgetown University and a bachelor’s degree in economics from The George Washington University. Subject: Defending Freedom, How We Can Win the Fight for an Open Society, by Ralf Fücks  - (REVIEW COPY? INTERVIEW REQUESTS?)
Description: Publishing November 1, 2019   ** ------------------------------------------------------------  We are witnessing a crisis of liberal democracy. A widespread fear of social decline, rapid globalization and uncontrolled immigration have culminated in a prevailing mood of hostility towards the established order. Confidence in democratic institutions and mainstream political parties is fast eroding, with people increasingly drawn towards the rhetoric of populist demagogues and authoritarian leaders. What are the roots of this revolt against liberalism and how can it be countered?  In this new book, the leading Green politician and thinker Ralf Fücks argues that the threat to liberal democracy lies within democracy itself. Democracy is the fundamental guarantor of freedom and it is our own failure to defend it that has led to the encroachment of an illiberal and divisive politics. In a powerful counter, Fücks outlines the foundations for an ambitious democratic renewal: greater investment in the public institutions to create a sense of belonging and political community; a focus on education as the key instrument for social advancement; the promotion of a democratic patriotism based on common political values; a better understanding of how to increase participation in the emerging digital economy; and sustainable innovation that will unleash the creative potential of liberal societies.  This robust defense of liberal democracy will be essential reading for anyone concerned about the very real threat faced by our democratic freedoms today and wondering what we can do about it.  The Author:  Ralf Fücks is Co-Founder of the Centre for Liberal Modernity, a non-partisan organization that stands up for the defense and renewal of open society and looks for answers to the key challenges of our time.  Formerly President of the Heinrich Böll Foundation, he was a leading figure in the German Green Party and Senator for Environment and Urban Development in Bremen. Subject: NEW CLIENT: BioCorRx – Offers Safe and Effective, Live-Saving Implants to Treat Those with Addiction Disorders
Description: Hi Stephanie?,  I wanted to reach out and introduce you to a new client I’m representing, BioCorRx – a leading edge healthcare solutions company focused on improving the lives of those struggling with alcohol and opioid addiction.  BioCorRx has developed a sustained-release naltrexone implant which is used to inhibit cravings associated with the utilization of alcohol and opioids. Naltrexone has been approved for use as a tablet, to help thousands of patient fight their addictions, in the United States since 1984. While the drug is very effective to treat addiction, some physicians have observed that the recommended dosage form and efficacy of the drug can present obstacles that can affect the treatment process for addicts especially in the critical early stages. Medical experts have found that the use of a long-acting naltrexone implant presents a way to overcome the hurdles that may arise with the use of the commercially available dosage forms of the drug.  Image  To further discuss BioCorRx and the innovative naltrexone implant, CEO and Founder Brady Granier, is available to be interviewed.  Warmest,  Nandi  About BioCorRx:  BioCorRx Inc. (OTCQB: BICX) is an addiction treatment company offering a unique approach to the treatment of substance abuse addiction. The BioCorRx® Recovery Program, a non-addictive, medication-assisted treatment (MAT) program, consists of two main components. The first component of the program consists of an outpatient implant procedure performed by a licensed physician. The implant delivers the non-addictive medicine, naltrexone, an opioid antagonist that can significantly reduce physical cravings for alcohol and opioids, and can prevent opioid overdose following relapse. The second component of the program developed by BioCorRx Inc. is a Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) program tailored specifically for the treatment of alcoholism and other substance abuse addictions for those receiving long-term naltrexone treatment. The Company also conducts R&D under its controlled subsidiary, BioCorRx Pharmaceuticals. Subject: Ingraham Rescheduled and a Note from Deborah
Description: Thank you for understanding...  View this email in your browser (https://mailchi.mp/caapusa/bill-owens-of-caap-215449?e=d2b3ef1fec) https://secure.anedot.com/coalition-of-african-american-pastors-usa/dream-derailed-sponsors?mc_cid=3306093386&mc_eid=[UNIQID] http://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fmailchi.mp%2Fcaapusa%2Fbill-owens-of-caap-215449&mc_cid=3306093386&mc_eid=[UNIQID] Share (http://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fmailchi.mp%2Fcaapusa%2Fbill-owens-of-caap-215449&mc_cid=3306093386&mc_eid=[UNIQID]) http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Ingraham+Rescheduled+and+a+Note+from+Deborah:&mc_cid=3306093386&mc_eid=[UNIQID] https%3A%2F%2Fmailchi.mp%2Fcaapusa%2Fbill-owens-of-caap-215449 Tweet (http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Ingraham+Rescheduled+and+a+Note+from+Deborah:&mc_cid=3306093386&mc_eid=[UNIQID] https%3A%2F%2Fmailchi.mp%2Fcaapusa%2Fbill-owens-of-caap-215449) http://us6.forward-to-friend.com/forward?u=92112f469785e1152be1993c1&id=3306093386&e=d2b3ef1fec Forward to a Friend (http://us6.forward-to-friend.com/forward?u=92112f469785e1152be1993c1&id=3306093386&e=d2b3ef1fec)   ** Ingraham Rescheduled and a Note from Deborah... ------------------------------------------------------------ Dear Partner,  Hello. This is Deborah. I wanted to touch base with you after a tumultuous few days.  Bill's appearance on the Ingraham Angle on Monday night had to be postponed for personal reasons. Fortunately, they were able to reschedule him for tonight (Tuesday). So don't forget to tune into Fox News tonight at 10pm (EDT). He'll be talking about his CNN interview (among other things). It's very exciting!  After the horrifying events in El Paso and Dayton, I've been troubled by some of the things I've seen on social media, from "talking heads," and even from some Democratic candidates  Like so many of you, I'm saddened by the loss of innocent life. I wish I had the answers that would put an end to such violence - how to stop the hate, how to heal the troubled minds behind these acts.  What I don't like is the blame game. We didn't blame President Obama for the massacre at Sandy Hook or President Clinton for the Columbine killings. We should not be using these tragedies to point fingers or advance a political agenda. Sometimes I wonder if there are groups who have press releases already filled out, just waiting to fill in the names of the next tragedy so they can score their political points.  What we should be doing is mourning and uniting in a time of sorrow. We should be doing some soul searching. We should be listening to each other, not shouting at one another.  We have so many freedoms in America, but sometimes we take advantage of the wrong ones. We speak, but we don't hear. We value press over respect for others and even the truth. We confuse the difference between freedom of religion and try to make it freedom "from" religion.  I am so tired of seeing people leap to turn tragedy into a political weapon. I can't speak for others, but personally, I'll be tuning out the noise from the media and politicians and looking for ways I can spread unity in my own community.  For faith, family and freedom, Dr. Deborah Owens  P.S. Your prayers and financial support will help us put this country on the right path. Please help us as we strengthen our grassroots network and work to educate and inspire pastors, community leaders, and politicians to defend our Christian rights. Donate to CAAP today! Subject: Expert Avail in Boston- How Students Can Advocate for Themselves
Description: Hi Stephanie,  Back to school might mean back to bullying, and other challenges for students of all ages.  Heather Hansen (https://heatherhansenpresents.com/) , partner at O’Brien and Ryan law firm, anchor at the Law and Crime network, host of The Elegant Warrior podcast and author of The Elegant Warrior: How to Win Life’s Trials Without Losing Yourself [Page Two, April 2019], is available for interviews to teach students how to advocate for themselves. She can address two audiences in particular:  1. Parents of young children who are going to school and need to learn to advocate for themselves with other students and teachers  2.  College students who need to advocate for themselves and stay safe.   Hansen’s advice for young children and parents of young children:  As your children head out for the new school year, they will face new challenges. They will need to learn to advocate for themselves effectively. You can help by teaching them the 4 Ps.   Pause—they don’t have to react right away. Most of the time if they are facing a bully or a “mean” teacher, there’s time to walk away and address it later.   Plan-then they can come home and plan for their advocacy. This is where questions come in. How could they handle the problem? What do they want to say? How do they want to say it?   Practice—playing it out with your children is a great way to make sure they are not only ready, but comfortable. I’d never step into trial without practicing, and your kids shouldn’t face their trials without practice either. (nor should adults!)  Play-when they get into the situation, all they have to do is “press play” on what they’ve prepped and practiced. They can go into the situation confident that they have the tools they need and that the conversation or interaction could even be fun!  This type of preparation also makes children much more likely to respond well when they don’t have time for the 4 Ps!  Hansen’s advice for college students:  As college students head out to their new lives without their parents, they will face new challenges. Some of those are hard, especially in the time of MeToo, frat hazing and social media bullying. Here are some ways they can advocate for themselves in tough situations, using the word DORM as guidance.   D-Discover. First, discover yourself. You can’t advocate for yourself until you know what you want and what you don’t want. Also this is the time to learn your limits with respect to drinking, relationships, and social media.   O-Object. You have to learn to object when you don’t like something. I was petrified the first time I objected in the courtroom. But no one can set your boundaries but you. When you know what you don’t want, it is time to use your voice and set those boundaries. Objections take practice so start small. Don’t be afraid to say “ I don’t like that”  R-Recognize tone and body language College kids need to know that bodies and voices can tell them as much as words do. Tone of voice is especially helpful, as studies show you can tell more about a person’s emotion from their tone of voice than their facial expressions. If they can read tone of voice, they may hear danger before they see it.   M-Move. When you feel uncomfortable, read a weird tone in a voice, don’t like someone’s body language, or don’t like the response to your objection, you can leave. Don’t be afraid to move your body. Sometimes confidence follows.   Are you interested in scheduling an interview or byline? I’m also happy to send a book your way.  More about Hansen is below.  Thanks in advance for your consideration and feedback.  Have a great day,  Joelle  HEATHER HANSEN is a trial lawyer, consultant and professional speaker. She has defended medical malpractice cases for over twenty years, was recently inducted into the American College of Trial Lawyers and is consistently named one of the Top 50 Female Attorneys in the state of Pennsylvania. Heather works as a communication consultant, combining her courtroom experience with her psychology degree and her training as a mediator to help her clients ask better questions, master objections, and use credible persuasion to succeed. She has appeared on CNN, NBC, Fox News Channel, and Good Day Philadelphia, and is the host of The Elegant Warrior podcast. Heather lives in New York City.  Connect with Heather Hansen on Facebook @HeatherHansenPresents (https://www.facebook.com/heatherhansenpresents/) , Twitter @ImHeatherHansen (https://twitter.com/imheatherhansen) , Instagram @ImHeatherHansen (https://www.instagram.com/imheatherhansen/?hl=en) , LinkedIn @HeatherHansen (https://www.linkedin.com/in/heather-hansen-84243512/) , YouTube (https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC2ecu4d4mKYZuh9QE9ZWhmA) , and visit www.heatherhansenpresent.com (http://www.heatherhansenpresent.com) .  The Elegant Warrior: How to Win Life’s Trials Without Losing Yourself is available on Amazon (https://www.amazon.com/Elegant-Warrior-Trials-Without-Yourself/dp/1989025269) and other fine booksellers. Subject: Here's how GDPR is helping your return on email
Description: GDPR, for the win!  iContact-logo-blue-500 (https://email.icontact.com/e2t/sc2/Mm-nFbkns5YW5ypsfs4JLbHsW7NqqJZ7wx_FbW8SvHvM6m9WkMf1FXffT03 )  GDPR-blog-icontact (https://email.icontact.com/e2t/sc2/Mm-nFbkns5YW5ypsfs4JLbHsW7NqqJZ7wx_FbW8SvHvM6m9WkMf1FXffT13 )  It's been a little over a year since GDPR made its debut, but we're still  seeing the ripple effect in our conversations with customers and leads on a daily basis. Subject: FEAT/INT: “Are You Raising a Liar? Key Warning Signs and What To Do About It”
Description: Dear Stephanie,  No one wants to raise a liar, but here’s the harsh truth: kids aren’t always honest. In fact, by the time they turn 4 years old, 90 percent of children have bended the truth. But how can parents avoid raising a lifelong liar?  “We punish bad behavior and we let the little lies slide, so they practice telling us what we want to hear, and they get better at it,” says Dr. Kat Shalhoub, PhD (https://katshalhoub.com/) . “We need to change the way we react to certain behavior; otherwise, it can lead to a lifetime of lying.”  Available for interviews, Q&As, and articles, Dr. Shalhoub (“Coach Kat”) can discuss:  · Why Kids Lie: Two key reasons kids bend the truth and how it can lead to permanent behavior · Seven tips for raising a more honest child and encouraging that behavior for life · There’s no such thing as a white lie: Why parents should never dismiss or laugh at small fibs · Change your tone! Make sure the way you react to poor behavior does not trigger fear  Please let me know if you’re interested in speaking with “Coach Kat” and/or receiving a copy of her new book, Futureproof. Thanks for your time, Stephanie. I look forward to hearing from you!  Have a great day,  Mallory Campoli, Publicity Manager / SMITH PUBLICITY, INC. t: 856.489.8654 ext: 313 / e: mallory.campoli@smithpublicity.com (mailto:mallory.campoli@smithpublicity.com)  I look forward to hearing your suggestions. Subject: How to Plan Meetings That Engage Millennials
Description: http://mit732.acemlnc.com/lt.php?s=8d4b440a7380625920e8b23494f80d90&i=6A26A2A116      http://mit732.acemlnc.com/lt.php?s=8d4b440a7380625920e8b23494f80d90&i=6A26A2A117      http://mit732.acemlnc.com/lt.php?s=8d4b440a7380625920e8b23494f80d90&i=6A26A2A118      http://mit732.acemlnc.com/lt.php?s=8d4b440a7380625920e8b23494f80d90&i=6A26A2A119      http://mit732.acemlnc.com/lt.php?s=8d4b440a7380625920e8b23494f80d90&i=6A26A2A120      http://mit732.acemlnc.com/lt.php?s=8d4b440a7380625920e8b23494f80d90&i=6A26A2A121      mailto:endicott-sales@mit.edu   About Us | Meetings | Upcoming Events  View this email in your browser     http://mit732.acemlnc.com/lt.php?s=8d4b440a7380625920e8b23494f80d90&i=6A26A2A122   How to Have a Millennial-Friendly Meeting  There's a common misconception in the world of business regarding millennials and their feelings about business meetings . Millennials are often thought to be easily bored by meetings, as they typically spend the entirety of meetings going through their phones or laptops. However, millennials don't necessarily hate meetings-they simply want these meetings to matter. Read on for six ways to better engage millennials in meetings. Read More     http://mit732.acemlnc.com/lt.php?s=8d4b440a7380625920e8b23494f80d90&i=6A26A2A131. Subject: Protecting Our Children  [JSH-Online #31103]
Description: Subject * Protecting Our Children Message *  August7,2019 Dear Christian Science Publishing Society, The continued killings of children and adults by young people has saddened our entire county and the world. As a longtime Christian Scientist, my heart goes out to the innocent. In prayer I have asked God what can I do? What do I need to know? I am only 1 person. Divine Love’s answer came a few days later. He told me that the children of this generation have not be been taught of the Lord. Very few if any have been taught the Ten Commandments, the beatitudes, the Golden Rule or how to pray. Gun laws can only do so much to protect children and adults. But knowledge of a Loving Creator who is with us all the time known as Immanuel will. But how do we get the word out there into the public? An idea came to me which I would love to share with you… The Christian Science Publishing Society could print a new poster with the afore mentioned ideas; The 10 commandments, The Beatitudes, The Golden Rule and the Lord’s Prayer. Maybe it could include The Children’s Prayer by Mary Baker Eddy. This idea could also be shared in pamphlet form at a reasonable price so that members could buy several copies to share with children and their parents. I would not consider this proselytizing.  The members could share it with people they know or with people Divine Mind has told them to share it with. It’s offering a cup of cold water in Christ’s name. It’s bringing the Truth to God’s little ones. It’s the best protection against evil, because it’s the Law of God-Good. For God is the preserver of man (and children). The poster and pamphlet could be available for sale through the Reading Rooms or on line. Thank you for considering this idea. We can all make a difference in this world and the future. Sincerely, Carolyn Gregory 916.747.7448  Email *   carolyngregory100@msn.com Category * General Comments/Feedback Name    Carolyn Gregory User Agent Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/64.0.3282.140 Safari/537.36 Edge/18.17763

Subject: The Japanese and Western Science
Description: The Japanese first encountered Western scientific technology around 1543, when the Portuguese drifted ashore and left them firearms. For the next few centuries Japan's policy of national isolation severely limited contact with the West. In the middle of the nineteenth century, when Commodore Perry introduced the Japanese to a few of the West's technological achievements, they realized how vulnerable their technological ignorance made them and felt great pressure to master Western science as quickly as possible.  In The Japanese and Western Science, Masao Watanabe succinctly examines the intersection of Western science and Japanese culture since Japan's opening to the West. Using case studies, including a Japanese scientist trained in the West and foreign teachers brought to Japan, he describes how the Japanese quickly and effectively accepted Western science and technology.  http://www.upenn.edu/pennpress/book/1986.html   HOW JAPAN PICKS AMERICA'S BRAINS Much of its economic success has been built on bought, borrowed, or stolen technology. Now U.S. companies are striking back -- but a two-way street is still far off.  By Joel Dreyfuss REPORTER ASSOCIATE Carrie Gottlieb  December 21, 1987  FORTUNE Magazine) – AFTER ITS DEFEAT in World War II, Japan was content to take foreign inventions -- the transistor, the laser, the videotape player -- and convert them into products that it could market around the world. Japan acquired much of its base of Western technology, most of it American, perfectly legally through licensing, careful study of scientific papers and patents, and imitation. But when the U.S. wasn't willing to share, some Japanese companies simply copied with little regard for patents and other intellectual property rights that the courts have only recently begun to define in many areas of high technology.  The U.S., confident of its technical superiority, ''sold out to the Japanese,'' says G. Steven Burrill, head of the high-technology consulting group at Arthur Young, a Big Eight accounting firm. ''We let them share our brain.'' Now, belatedly awake to the recognition that Japan has been eating their breakfast, lunch, dinner, and bedtime snack, American companies are stirring. IBM vs. Fujitsu over computer software, Honeywell vs. Minolta over automatic focusing, Corning Glass vs. Sumitomo Electric over fiber optics -- these are only the latest, best-publicized complaints that Japan has stolen American technology. Even as those legal battles are fought out, the copycat cliche is becoming obsolete. A series of studies financed by the U.S. government since 1984 warn that Japan has caught up with the U.S. or passed it in the development of integrated circuits, fiber optics, computer hardware engineering, and advanced materials like polymers. It is pressing hard in some areas of biotechnology, and lags primarily in computer software. Already there are signs that the Japanese, buoyed by their new prowess, have assumed the arrogance of the U.S. along with its technology.  http://archive.fortune.com/magazines/fortune/fortune_archive /1987/12/21/69996/index.htm   PICKING JAPAN'S RESEARCH BRAINS At last U.S. companies are overcoming the ''not invented here'' syndrome and learning how to tap Japan's vast technological resources -- just as Japan has tapped America's.  By Susan Moffat REPORTER ASSOCIATE Joshua Mendes  March 25, 1991  For years Japan has come to the U.S., bought or borrowed the best of America's technology, and sold it back to the U.S. as finished products. Japanese companies have sent thousands of engineers to be trained at American universities and set up basic research labs on American turf: Computer giant NEC located its new $25 million lab in Princeton and hired top scientists from nearby Bell Labs to help lead it. Kobe Steel and Fujitsu have research centers in Silicon Valley. Sixteen Japanese companies have endowed chairs at MIT, at about $2 million a shot. So far, the technology flow has been pretty much one way. In 1989, U.S. companies took in $2.5 billion selling technology to the Japanese but spent only $500 million to buy technology from Japan. Now, though, more and more American high-tech companies are setting up laboratories in Japan, which could start reversing the imbalance.  THESE YOUNG AMERICANS are invited by leading high-tech companies to work in the inner sanctum of some of the best, most product-oriented research labs in Japan.  Many seem not to remember that the U.S. was once the world's best commercializer of imported inventions. Henry Ford reverse-engineered German car motors; the British invented jet engines.  http://archive.fortune.com/magazines/fortune/fortune_archive /1991/03/25/74810/index.htm   What's Intellectual Property and Does China Steal It?: QuickTake - Bloomberg  What is intellectual property? It refers to creations of the mind, such as inventions, literary and artistic works, and designs, symbols, names and images used in commerce, according to the World Intellectual Property Organization. IP is protected in law by patents, copyright and trademarks, enabling people to earn recognition or financial benefit from what they invent or create. “The IP system aims to foster an environment in which creativity and innovation can flourish," the WIPO says.  https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2018-12-05/what-s-in tellectual-property-and-does-china-steal-it-quicktake   7 Military Weapons China Copied From the United States  https://m.theepochtimes.com/7-military-weapons-china-copied- from-the-united-states_1699756.html   History of the Chinese copycat car: picture gallery  https://www.autocar.co.uk/car-news/new-cars/history-chinese- copycat-car-picture-gallery   50 Copy cat cars from China  https://www.cartoq.com/50-copy-cat-cars-from-china/  --  To unsubscribe from this group and stop receiving emails from it, send an email to customerservice+unsubscribe@csps.com.

Subject: Innovative insurance cover to help drought-hit communities in Africa - 7 August 2019
Description: https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQB3Ot-2BpMc7pD4jxEXaKFDl74BcADyOY08EZMEZbJlOlf5mDvaMeBDO6geRaLe0fL6XzY5HdUG-2FSIQRKfmqjDDoKgOM4fe3XVwFE5YK5hJ-2Foy50z0XSfbqftIMxSPC68uZmw3hhbEYvU-2Fx7wCX-2Btn78qg-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs1b-2FnJGB44-2FouotZgWz8KEUSJAgGQ3cwKxsBq9IuiB-2BSKaqCJ8DQhi7Y7xf0y3w4JKC989gTQ-2FBifn-2Fo-2ByaXUxalcsE213nrPiPCogxpWQRwPdqRsLUd3iXWXKe1NACns5Et6M3hy-2FxbtaRrwMDGzSV7ITm4gT0YMmdqq4ncVkGz08j7IiJaugU1SB0hU1Z3nSWY3Mq9sx-2Fw2hRq9TXfuunBvY5rKlwMOyCI1OThJHyORPH9ulu79mJjzg-2Fm-2BA4NpU-3D  WFP and Start Network News Release  7 August 2019  INNOVATIVE INSURANCE COVER TO HELP DROUGHT-HIT COMMUNITIES IN AFRICA  ROME-LONDON – Humanitarian agencies are setting up innovative climate risk insurance policies to protect up to 1.3 million people in West Africa from catastrophic drought. The countries benefitting include Senegal, Mali, Mauritania, Burkina Faso and the Gambia.   These policies will unleash funds to assist vulnerable communities threatened by drought before it reaches catastrophic levels. Collectively, the purchased policies could release a total of US$ 49.5 million across the five countries. The World Food Programme (WFP) and the Start Network have purchased these “replica” climate risk insurance policies from the African Union’s Africa Risk Capacity (ARC), complementing those purchased by national governments.   This initiative, which is known under the name ‘ARC Replica’ allows governments and humanitarian agencies to quickly access and channel financing to vulnerable people in the event of an extreme drought.   “ARC Replica is strengthening the insurance coverage offered by ARC by increasing the sum insured for Mali,” explains WFP Country Director, Silvia Caruso. “This increases the number of people that will benefit from a payout in the case of a major drought.”  This financing helps to protect livestock and other assets, and to supplement feeding programs for undernourished children.  To ensure assistance reaches people in need quickly, Start Network and WFP have worked with each insured country to identify how resources and assistance can most efficiently be delivered.   “Many developing countries face the risk of disasters without being sufficiently prepared for them. When a disaster strikes, humanitarian organisations often respond too late, leaving affected populations vulnerable to further risk,” says KfW Development Bank project manager, Veronika Bertram-Hümmer. “We are very pleased to finance ARC Replica and work with the Start Network and the WFP to improve national preparedness and risk management efforts which ultimately allow us to help people affected by drought in West Africa and the Sahel.”  Through ARC Replica, the Start Network and WFP accompany governments in improving risk management practices, working collaboratively to strengthen safety nets and climate protection to vulnerable populations.   Mr. Abdoulaye Noba, Director of Civil Protection, Supervisor of the ARC Programme in Senegal, says that "ARC Replica is an innovative project that enables ARC Member States and humanitarian partners to respond more effectively to disaster risks through funding mechanisms such as insurance."  ARC and ARC Replica use pre-agreed triggers such as rainfall satellite data which allow for rapid response involving pre-agreed activities such as cash transfers and the distribution of food and nutrition supplements. The aim is to avoid situations where families take children out of school, migrate or sell livestock and seeds before the next agricultural season.   “We will keep working closely with the Government of Senegal, Start Network members in country and their partners to ensure that if a drought is detected, funds become available promptly to deliver support to vulnerable people,” says Anna Farina, Risk Financing Operations Lead at Start.   Pay-outs are made as early as two weeks after a failed harvest – months earlier than traditional humanitarian resources are made available. Typically, aid agencies are reliant on funding that gets provided by donors after a crisis has already taken place. By the time a crisis has been determined and humanitarian appeals have been formulated, many lives and livelihoods can be lost.                                                                                                  #         #         #  ARC and ARC Replica  The African Risk Capacity (ARC) is an institution set up by the African Union to strengthen African countries’ management of climate risk. This is achieved by offering governments drought insurance policies in exchange for an annual premium. ARC Replica is an insurance product offered by ARC Ltd to humanitarian organizations as an innovative approach to expand climate risk insurance coverage to more people and improve the effectiveness of emergency humanitarian response in vulnerable African countries prone to climate risks.  The Partners  ARC Replica in Mali, the Gambia, Burkina Faso and Mauritania is led by the United Nations World Food Programme (WFP). Saving lives in emergencies and changing lives for millions through sustainable development. WFP works in more than 80 countries around the world, feeding people caught in conflict and disasters, and laying the foundations for a better future. For WFP, ARC Replica fits into a wider risk financing portfolio with forecast-based financing and microinsurance programmes, such as the R4 Rural Resilience Initiative.   The Start Network^^[1] is the Replica partner in Senegal and it will sign a policy later this year in Madagascar.  The Start Network (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQB-2B38-2B938RfIQlo-2FOd39R3xQfYXCsm4zgbkf-2BSs7mZvDX_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs1b-2FnJGB44-2FouotZgWz8KEUSJAgGQ3cwKxsBq9IuiB-2BSKaqCJ8DQhi7Y7xf0y3w4JKC989gTQ-2FBifn-2Fo-2ByaXUxalcsE213nrPiPCogxpWQRwExWly-2FkTdP5PsGQz3zP3-2BNjfPg31UKfPGkFnfoCf5NKht95yPurRCtsfS6lAojoETAOISjjqYQSsHRBKZMQMSfdA8j2IyYRIBiJzSDVvfF3TaH9u56iT20qnziZjQwCWGmveCXuACIcW54Q41j33Vk-3D aims to generate evidence from the ARC Replica initiative to inform the development of a ‘family’ of global financing mechanisms for frontline humanitarian responders, set to include a financial tool-box of products such as contingency funds, forecast-based-financing, and loans in addition to macro- and micro- insurance.  Follow us on Twitter @wfp_media @StartNetwork  For more information please contact (email address: firstname.lastname@wfp.org):  Jane Howard, WFP/Rome, Tel. +39 06 65132321, Mob. +39 346 7600521  Michael Goode, WFP/Rome, Tel. +39 06 65133769, Mob.  +39 348 928 8713  Helen James, Head of Communications and Digital, Start Network, helen.james@startnetwork.org  ------------------------------------------------------------  ^^[1] In Senegal the Start Network members involved in ARC Replica are:  Catholic Relief Services, Action Against Hunger, Oxfam, Plan International, World Vision and Save the Children.    ______________________  If you would rather not receive future communications from World Food Programme, please go to https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQBz2p53T0v-2BoEIvbo6vDi8C-2FreQ2koHH0FkxMbYLJVkShKKMlioIzzaulp-2Bo1xyStbNymj8lT5geORzMaL5Prk4-2FX8LQW5nfGKCvch0Mn6wIAPHfEZgviSe9KHjblH7lKnPRbduO-2FJ8kyrZs0ogSwXTg-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs1b-2FnJGB44-2FouotZgWz8KEUSJAgGQ3cwKxsBq9IuiB-2BSKaqCJ8DQhi7Y7xf0y3w4JKC989gTQ-2FBifn-2Fo-2ByaXUxalcsE213nrPiPCogxpWQRwBcaYgpDSvgkC-2B33Yb-2FJ6u-2FaBComd0UNrhsguqvpmvZqskmnUxzoW7B36ME0UbZ2L2mYaEIHsWVU-2F5eTHuXlekU1jqMAyfHvHZHxnFfKtNMCaTR-2B0AgZS67tS-2Fp9qODmZwqIaKCycXL0mFc-2B7GS5Di0-3D  World Food Programme, Via C.G. Subject: Acclaimed artist tackles new topic for kids: managing mental health
Description: Dear Stephanie??,  Featured on Today, FOX, CNN, and other major media, Ruby Roth is a Los Angeles-based artist, author-illustrator, activist, and former teacher whose groundbreaking children's books have received international attention and have been translated into multiple languages.   Glamour called her work “an explosion of controversy,” and Jane Goodall said it’s “...powerful and important.” Ruby has 160,000+ followers and her media clips have over 2 million views.  Her newest and fifth picture book, Bad Day (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQB9cWY-2BGkynoTuCVydZSmJ1StdGXgqtIFfWMWnyfmeHJadYTWU2mpkZXR8S0nlsQakTlonKHB1hMlOc-2BOfHYuLu3sP0cTNTErrajDIAeAPbo1mFkxTYju-2BEbc4Z1AZe3oC4iXQhTJNBw9EHmE1J4-2BDIG5gsPzNJMEcEWLC12boXEH_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs35giT-2BiE36sF2rIjLPGOgDYThq9KtzL3CTpFLIUOEfhVoFCAmj3gmFwqoRpQNs-2Btvu93SxoMONFcQH-2BI1OU1ML4Wkxb9A1qGKQeVYo2C7mGck5W4Jn5B8-2BOixrIBJmtdzHfUrBUToyB86hcSWJo253HxJK4Cw9j-2F2gtZs2NKqnoO-2FD0FLx-2BiOIY3VNLWumsdFUSkP8Qpa-2BV-2BC7cFNlztu6SxK3YNq-2BQsHzGTNbniNXGcg-2FtNl8P41hYiX8gS1r9-2FA-3D (preschool - 2nd grade, September 19, 2019, North Atlantic Books), is her first on issues of emotions and neuro-diversity.  Bad Day is especially timely due to growing concern for mental health and rising incidences of hypersensitivity and even violence in schools. Parents, childcare providers, and communities as a whole have a crucial responsibility to address strong emotions early in children’s lives. Bad Day encourages kids to take responsibility for their own wellbeing, and even further, to find strength and happiness in the process.   Would you be interested in speaking with Ruby or receiving a review copy when books arrive early next month?
