Subject: Putting God Back in Our Culture
Description: What we can do to stop more violence...  View this email in your browser (https://mailchi.mp/caapusa/bill-owens-of-caap-215453?e=f4925dc692) https://secure.anedot.com/coalition-of-african-american-pastors-usa/dream-derailed-sponsors?mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID] http://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fmailchi.mp%2Fcaapusa%2Fbill-owens-of-caap-215453&mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID] Share (http://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fmailchi.mp%2Fcaapusa%2Fbill-owens-of-caap-215453&mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID]) http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Putting+God+Back+in+Our+Culture:&mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID] https%3A%2F%2Fmailchi.mp%2Fcaapusa%2Fbill-owens-of-caap-215453 Tweet (http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Putting+God+Back+in+Our+Culture:&mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID] https%3A%2F%2Fmailchi.mp%2Fcaapusa%2Fbill-owens-of-caap-215453) http://us6.forward-to-friend.com/forward?u=92112f469785e1152be1993c1&id=de8e89edf3&e=f4925dc692 Forward to a Friend (http://us6.forward-to-friend.com/forward?u=92112f469785e1152be1993c1&id=de8e89edf3&e=f4925dc692)   ** Putting God Back in Our Culture ------------------------------------------------------------ Dear Partner,  When Laura Ingraham asked me what we needed to do to stop violence in our culture, all I could think about was why our country isn't talking more about God.  I had been invited on the Ingraham Angle (https://video.foxnews.com/v/6068772140001/?mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID]#sp=show-clips) to talk about my CNN appearance and upcoming book, A Dream Derailed (http://adreamderailed.com/?mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID]) . But the violence in Chicago and the mass murders in Dayton and El Paso were as much on the host's mind as my own.  So when she asked me - as someone who has worked in the inner city - what these cities need, I said:  "Chicago needs spiritual leadership. Politicians cannot solve these kinds of problems. It's our families, and our ministers, and our communities that must come together to address these issues."  (You can watch my interview below or on YouTube (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cEb7-cGxtVM&mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID]) .)  What I wanted people to understand is that looking to politicians to solve such problems is futile. Not only does it pass on both responsibility and blame, but it's unfair. Politicians don't have the power to fix something so fundamental. They can only address things at the edges, once law gets involved. But how to do you stop a problem before it starts? That isn't a political issue. That's a spiritual one.  After my interview with Laura, a dear friend shared with me a few words from other ministers who have been spreading the same message (https://onenewsnow.com/culture/2019/08/07/you-kick-god-out-of-the-culture-this-is-what-you-get?mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID]) . Abraham Hamilton III recently spoke on American Family Radio about how we are "mis-educating" people to devalue life. He said:  "We have a generation [now] that has been force-fed, through their mis-education systems, the message that they're nothing but animals; [that] there's nothing unique or sacred about human life – [and therefore] life has no purpose, no meaning. That is what society has force-fed a generation. ...  You kick God out of society – the God who says 'You were made in My image' and that life is precious – you reject Him [and] expel Him from society; yet want to complain when people act like animals. We can't have it both ways." Dr. James Dobson is a friend and supporter of CAAP who has given us great insight and help. He recently wrote about the growth of socialism in our country and how this political mindset alienates us from God. In a letter that he urged us to share (https://drjamesdobson.org/about/august-newsletter-2019?sc=hpslider1&mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID]) with others, he quoted a sermon from Dr. Jack Graham:  "Socialism is fundamentally contradictory to the Christian worldview. It seeks to suppress all people, especially Christians, in favor of the state. And the way that it does that is by breaking down the institutions that God has established, particularly marriage and the family. When I see the breakdown of our culture, our society, and especially the family, it truly breaks my heart. There is a spiritual war going on all around us. It is a battle for the heart and soul of our nation. We are fighting for the sanctity of life, the sacredness of biblical marriage, sexual identity, religious freedom, and, yes, economic freedom that gives us the ability to prosper within a nation. Socialism opposes each of these cornerstones." https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cEb7-cGxtVM&mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID]  To put it bluntly, we are missing God in our homes, neighborhood, schools, and culture. We are missing both the discipline and hope that come with prayer. We are losing our understanding of the sanctity of all human life and the respect for life that flows from that principle.  We are losing what it means to be a neighborhood or community. These are not ways to describe geographic proximity. They're statements about how we look out for each other, share values, and ensure the betterment of the next generation.  Our country is losing touch with God.  How did this happen? How do we fix it? These are some of the questions I wrestle with in my upcoming book. Though it's not yet on sale, we are giving a "thank you" copy to donors who gift CAAP $30 or become a sponsor of the book for $100. To learn more, visit the book's website (http://adreamderailed.com/?mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID]) , or just go to the donation page. (https://caapusa.org/2019/07/get-a-signed-copy-of-a-dream-derailed/?mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID])  We live in an increasingly secular society, one that has turned away from the lessons of the Bible. If we want to change things, we need to put God back in our culture. Remember Matthew 24:12: Because of the increase of wickedness, the love of most will grow cold.  For faith, family and freedom, Rev. Bill Owens  P.S. Your prayers and financial support will help us put this country on the right path. Please help us as we strengthen our grassroots network and work to educate and inspire pastors, community leaders, and politicians to defend our Christian rights. Donate to CAAP today!  (https://causes.anedot.com/caap-email-appeal?mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID])  The Coalition of African American Pastors, [aka] The Coalition for American Action and Principles, is a grass roots movement of Christians who believe in traditional family values in American public life.  We believe in protecting the lives of the unborn, and defending the sacred institution of marriage. CAAP does not endorse, support, or oppose any candidate for political office. Any mention of public figures herein is purely for discussion and educational purposes and should not be interpreted as a statement of electoral support or opposition.  *The Coalition of African American Pastors is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization.  Your donations to The Coalition of African American Pastors may be tax deductible to the fullest extent of the law.  No goods or services were received in exchange for any contributions.  You should consult a tax advisor regarding any tax deductions.  CAAP does not endorse any politician or political campaign. Make a Donation to CAAP! We welcome clergy (bishops, pastors, ministers, evangelists, every member of the clergy) from any race to join our movement to protect and defend faith and family! CAAP Clergy Membership (http://caapusa.org/membership/caap-clergy-membership/?mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID]) http://caapusa.org/caap-womens-ministry/?mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID] The CAAP Womenâ€™s Ministry is composed of women of faith and conviction, working together to support and serve women. Subject: An Interracial Cast of Talented Teens Sings Songs of the 60s???
Description: This Thursday & Friday - Free!  96  * *  Image  An Interracial Cast of Talented Teens Sings Songs of the 1960s  This Thursday & Friday, 5pm  Prospect Terrace, 54 Congdon Street Providence  Free & Open to the Public!  Image  INTERRACIAL CAST OF TEENS PERFORMS A TRIBUTE TO THE 1960s  A unique ensemble of 8 talented teens will perform some of America’s greatest songs from the 1960s in “Sounds of the 60s: From the Blues to the Beatles” on Thursday and Friday, August 8th & 9th, 5:00pm, at Prospect Terrace, 54 Congdon Street, Providence. The original show is free and open to the public.  The teen ensemble has spent two weeks rehearsing six hours a day preparing the show under the musical direction of internationally acclaimed musicians, Michael Palter and Lynne Jackson, and the artistic direction of Robb Dimmick of Providence, learning songs, developing vocal technique, acting skills and choreography, and the history the turbulent 60s. The show and its cast of Black and White youth give us hope in a divided nation.  Jazz is a Rainbow, now in its eighteenth year, has been acclaimed by the US Department of Education, as well as teachers, music educators, community leaders and musicians throughout the world. It is produced by Stages of Freedom and funded by the Providence Shelter for Colored Children, Opera Providence, Rhode Island School of Design, and the Providence Department of Art Culture and Tourism, Providence Parks and Recreation, Mayor Jorge O. Elorza, and Partnership for Providence Parks.  Photo: Front row: Millie Teague; middle row: Sabrie Pearl Griffin,  James Teague, Ambrose Teague, Beyanca Guilme, Roma Taitwood,  Darius Henderson, Jr.; back row: Miguel Figueroa  More About Jazz is a Subject: Invitation to New GateWay Job Fair 2019
Description: Dear Sir/Madam,     New GateWay would like to invite you to be one of our Featured Employers for our Job Fair on October 23rd 2019, 10am to 1pm. This is our Annual Job Fair, offered every fall, open to job seekers throughout San Diego County including undergraduate and graduate college students. This year, we will host it at The Jacobs Center for Neighborhood Innovation in San Diego. To register please visit https://newgateway.org/career-fair-2019.html.      New GateWay was founded in January 2014 with a primary objective of positively impacting the lives of those who unemployment has affected severely. This is being accomplished by providing career readiness tools and career training among other services, with the intention of assisting our clients out of poverty and, in some cases lifting out of homelessness.     Your attendance at New GateWay's Job Fair 2019 will impact the live of many in San Diego County who are seeking employment while, at the same time, make a difference in the lives of New GateWay's clients. Thank you so much in advance for considering becoming a Featured Employer at our Annual Job Fair.     The registration fee is $150.00 for companies and $100 for nonprofits/governmental organizations. Included in this fee will be a 6ft table, 2 chairs and a snack. If you would like to host a hiring event or offer on-the-spot interviews, there will be more than enough space. Just let us know what your needs are after you register.     If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact us at mjohn@newgateway.org <mailto:mjohn@newgateway.org> . I look forward to seeing you there!        Sincerely,  Tyrion Deng  Volunteer   New GateWay   49 Third Avenue  Chula Vista, CA 91910  (619)272-6017 x5  www.newgateway.org <http://www.newgateway.org>

Subject: You might want to see this - great opportunity to be a part of the Animal Protection Expo in GA
Description: Hello Patrik, We met briefly at an animal related event some time ago and I thought you would like to know about an important event. I would love for you to consider being involved with the 21st Annual Animal Protection Conference & Expo coming up on October 18-20th at The Hotel at Avalon in Alpharetta, Georgia. This is a unique conference gathers all those who are involved in pets, animal protection, and animal services. It is supported by people like you - becoming a Sponsor helps us provide amazing education for those involved in Animal Welfare. We expect 500-700 attendees consisting of veterinarians, attorneys, animal shelter, animal rescue/foster, animal behaviorist professionals, law enforcement, prosecutors, judges, lawmakers, animal advocates, trainers, pet services and business.   We are also partnering, for the first time, with the Georgia Veterinary Medical Association and their Vet South conference at the Hotel Avalon (a destination in itself - eat, work, shop & play complex). By partnering with Vet South, more attendees will be visiting our Expo area and exhibit halls.   You can also become an Exhibitor! We have 6'x3' tables and 10'x10' exhibit space available in our Expo area. Set-up a table or booth and get your organization or business right in front of new potential customers.   Also, you can get in front of this important audience by taking out an ad in our Expo Program Booklet - we have business card ads up to a full page ads available. This Program Booklet will be distributed to each attendee and available to all who visit the Expo all three days. And, have a postcard, business card, flyer or sample product you want these professionals to see - insert your promotional material in our Swag Bag!   You can sponsor one or multi Scholarship tickets for an attendee(s) who cannot afford to come. Budgets are tight so send your local animal control officer(s) or police officer(s), prosecutor (s) or an animal rescue or advocate who will appreciate the gift. It's a great way to support this important cause AND give someone the opportunity to attend this integral conference.   I have been involve with animal protection for almost 30 years and as a former prosecutor, I know change is needed and education is KEY to protecting animals. For the past 21 years, our attendees leave excited and inspired to continue their good work protecting animals. Not sure if I ever sent this to you in the past but I have included my bio for you.   Help us to not only make this year's Conference and Expo a huge success, but also reach this important target audience to help organization or business grow. Visit www.animalprotectionexpo.org for additional information, to sign up to sponsor, exhibit, purchase and ad in the program booklet, partake in the swag bag, and/or buy a Scholarship(s) for a deserving attendee. If you would, please get the word out and feel free post the information below on your social media sites. The information below can be copied and pasted. Make this YOUR Conference and Expo – for the animals!  Sincerely, Claudine Animal Protection Conference & Expo What: 21st annual 3-day educational symposium uniting professionals who work in animal cases, public, safety, animal cruelty, sheltering/rescue, animal care and services. Breakout sessions . Register Now: by clicking REGISTER or visit us on the Events tab at animallawsource.org ? Agenda: Our diverse courses and speakers will be posted soon Where: Hotel at Avalon, Alpharetta, GA When: Friday October 18, 19 & 20, 2019 - 8:30 – 4:30 pm    Hotel Options: Information for reduce rates on hotels can be found on Registration Link Food: Registration includes a continental breakfast on Saturday and Sunday. Lunch is on your own. Choose between 25 restaurants just outside the door or you may purchase a lunch ticket for a buffet served in exhibit hall. Parking: Covered parking deck or valet at hotel is available. Wifi: Available in various parts of conference center and hotel lobby Networking Possibilities: With like-minded professionals & learn from experts in the field. Mock trial offered. Share: Follow us on Facebook Join Now: AnimalLawSource.org for great info & updates on symposium agendas - free to join Need More? : Get information on animal law, cases, best practices, ask at info@animallawsource.org  Continuing Education Credits, pending*:  ·        CLE (Attorney) purchase credits at $5.00 per credit hour (in addition to Expo fee) ·        LEAP for legal education veterinarians, requested (Vets/vet techs), ·        CE for Veterinary General Courses, requested (Vets/vet techs), ·        POST Hours (Police), ·        IAABC & CCPDT, Approved (animal behaviorist/trainers), ·        CEU (general), ·        Certificate of Course Completion (Any attendee). Announcements about continuing education credits will be provided during conference. POST, LEAP, IAABC, CCPDT credits included in conference fee FOLLOW US ? ? ? ? Photos are included for your use. If you wish to interview the U-Haul dealer or a local U-Haul representative, we can assist. Now available at 21,000-plus locations across the U.S. and Canada. Central Ave., 7 South | Phoenix, AZ | 85004  602-263-6842 | VoIP extension 523111  ==================  Storage Plus Comes on Board as U-Haul Dealer  WALTHAM, Mass. (Aug. 8, 2019) — U-Haul Company of Massachusetts and Ohio, Inc. is pleased to announce that Storage Plus has signed on as a U-Haul® neighborhood dealer to serve the Waltham community.  Storage Plus at 37 River St. will offer U-Haul trucks, towing equipment, moving supplies, boxes and in-store pick-up for boxes.  U-Haul Truck Share 24/7 (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQBxn3CMpX-2FbI5-2BaPtScRsxtDpKhmNqU43K-2Fu0-2Bw5ZqLlApm5kMJo1X9Gil7VLYQRijy2taEmz0-2FUDE0CZay4tuT2htJytu04Pkc9dfk5gtysb_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs3kJ7S3dSaQ0X1M-2FYg11Zk-2F17wLLawxzBuRVQS0RuMczUMWqA8u63zd52C8r-2F-2BQTKFLHNrIW-2BcFhCTH7C3xRtbusWfuf6co18Ref984fPdcQb5fq6qEByQ8S98GuqmWpDttc1IuszHlfIxaTd-2FAXzqtfQvlVpqmC-2F4RTUJmQZJFAW3PuvAVYqtL0IP30fV6xDd4P7L3Wx7yx9mhQBVkoqja-2FCtr8W5WgOxSoz3r-2B3vMxOE5iC7wPOuVlKhsh7Y-2Bu2A-3D ® is revolutionizing the moving industry through its more convenient, more secure way to pick up and return a truck. Since 2017, U-Haul Live Verify? technology has allowed customers to conduct transactions entirely on their smartphones at any hour – day or night. There are no membership fees. Create an online account at uhaul.com to start skipping the lines and stop worrying about store hours.  Normal business hours are 9 a.m.-5:30 p.m. Monday-Friday and 9 a.m.-5 p.m. Saturday. Reserve U-Haul products at this dealer location by calling (781) 916-9373 or visiting https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQB9JAbTi-2B-2FtDwPQeWGlSbnHj-2BMVhGPsFl-2FcU0XJcbizhcZC2qq-2FdoV-2Fqg3vlmAnCY7ptOvU3308F8Q9nBAGlvHis8EKf-2FjgFUlkzi5IDaDbny_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs3kJ7S3dSaQ0X1M-2FYg11Zk-2F17wLLawxzBuRVQS0RuMczUMWqA8u63zd52C8r-2F-2BQTKFLHNrIW-2BcFhCTH7C3xRtbusWfuf6co18Ref984fPdcQRA-2FrEMgHcdbxU5wBbpt5ZehCaEW9iFvscLCNkpS6qnsWcxFfaX3cNp2wGXX0LLh5inJXe7oD1G7ypit9swRDI-2BsqJT9IBi7ePhdw8IeEWZ4Gjo6eTBN5QPA1roNsqxAiNvSgY93250H1rQ0t2tqDLM-3D (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQB9JAbTi-2B-2FtDwPQeWGlSbnHj-2BMVhGPsFl-2FcU0XJcbizhcZC2qq-2FdoV-2Fqg3vlmAnCY7ptOvU3308F8Q9nBAGlvHiuE9PECSrY6ymZpANHQHdJLpZgsq-2BZ7RItfAAUIK9Hi-2F7i13sGVrTEYOyhoZE1tH2ACExE42rJPySesc1l9PcgdoCBiyohHNbUfT-2FCabOmzGQ-3D-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs3kJ7S3dSaQ0X1M-2FYg11Zk-2F17wLLawxzBuRVQS0RuMczUMWqA8u63zd52C8r-2F-2BQTKFLHNrIW-2BcFhCTH7C3xRtbusWfuf6co18Ref984fPdcQZTbuJnfCIk2gPm2Mrh8-2FF0EIHU6FjvxGxxlNifhPVF8jrTsMVPcXXad1GURnEv0Yti67A7610ToGkmHWllAXJXpGM8M20fZux-2FfclqLUoFzAO9LxNuZSkJU-2F-2BwTWuCyNalqhIawDrSnX8vRn1mMNSE-3D today.  Storage Plus partners Alyssa Quill, Jay Hoke, Jennifer Barnquiero and Matthew McConkle are proud to team with the industry leader in do-it-yourself moving and self-storage to better meet the demands of Middlesex County.  U-Haul and Storage Plus are striving to benefit the environment through sustainability initiatives. Truck sharing is a core U-Haul sustainability business practice that allows individuals to access a fleet of trucks that is larger than what they could access on an individual basis.  Every U-Haul truck placed in a community helps keep 19 personally owned large-capacity vehicles, pickups, SUVs and vans off the road. Fewer vehicles means less traffic congestion, less pollution, less fuel burned and cleaner air.  Storage Plus is a great place to become U-Haul Famous®. Take your picture in front of a U-Haul product, send it in and your face could land on the side of a U-Haul truck. Upload your photo through Instagram using #uhaulfamous, or go to www.uhaulfamous.com (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=84Em28S1K9SvtzcUtu04El4WPn32Pr3mroiMQJfXlAigZ6Jk2E91sX-2BgRSzX-2Fygx_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs3kJ7S3dSaQ0X1M-2FYg11Zk-2F17wLLawxzBuRVQS0RuMczUMWqA8u63zd52C8r-2F-2BQTKFLHNrIW-2BcFhCTH7C3xRtbusWfuf6co18Ref984fPdcQWYKkgIc8tgSpN74X5pNKWz5iq4cVuBov6PcPFP4yVmq0JLC2gb-2BABGeC68g-2FGB1giIm9F2H7XCi-2BO16F9-2BB2dXyTX94VYEqzAzZRStpTflXWGk-2BjLUldAScDt6wEc3OVqYqVBnndo8eFdaB9Xc7MOg-3D to submit photos and learn more.  About U-Haul  Since 1945, U-Haul has been the No. 1 choice of do-it-yourself movers, with a network of 22,000 locations across all 50 states and 10 Canadian provinces. U-Haul Truck Share 24/7 offers secure access to U-Haul trucks every hour of every day through the customer dispatch option on their smartphones and our proprietary Live Verify technology. Our customers' patronage has enabled the U-Haul fleet to grow to approximately 167,000 trucks, 120,000 trailers and 43,000 towing devices. U-Haul offers nearly 697,000 rooms and 60.7 million square feet of self-storage space at owned and managed facilities throughout North America. U-Haul is the largest installer of permanent trailer hitches in the automotive aftermarket industry, and is the largest retailer of propane in the U.S.  Contact:  Erin O’Connor, External Communications Intern  Jeff Lockridge, External Communications  E-mail: jeff_lockridge@uhaul.com  Phone: 602-760-4941  Website: uhaul.com    ______________________  If you would rather not receive future communications from U-Haul International, Inc., please go to https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=HpRpfK6V2JMw-2F9s8CTslZhO7gEY5ghsqI470r3DrEXAAXpDH6d14uXFDi6m9yTOHPsbSf6lacSreLzQyqd2ota1ng5LrybL-2B5z14rv8LgcpoqV7eoL3Af4BL-2BJswMEfQHHtKZTt0j7CFYvDQLwfb-2BvAXE9FnzOr2bNu3g1aGXHLMR5jM0iTgTlPQ9T6VjgDz_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs3kJ7S3dSaQ0X1M-2FYg11Zk-2F17wLLawxzBuRVQS0RuMczUMWqA8u63zd52C8r-2F-2BQTKFLHNrIW-2BcFhCTH7C3xRtbusWfuf6co18Ref984fPdcQSGx-2FjcazozXWEVFcL2NTwtaUM0tFzt-2FD2USXRHRdYn22KkSRKlZz-2B3OoKVJpLsmUMGnR-2Bj0YRBv0vGHmeiKTgR84nSp-2FEHQsH5EY5vJxRZdOC2WB23EqSCxrChLGKxBZQGK5R7aGAdKyOnC876sbGE-3D  U-Haul International, Inc., 2727 N Central Ave, Phoenix, AZ 85004 United States  --  To unsubscribe from this group and stop receiving emails from it, send an email to customerservice+unsubscribe@csps.com.

Read More  The Ups and Downs of the Worldwide Graphite Electrode Market It is widely known that graphite is used in the automobile and steel industries. Besides the classical markets, there are new and ever-growing markets, such as lithium-ion batteries, being driven by the megatrends of digitalization and the Internet of Things.  Read More  Rugged, Fast Leak Detection The Pfeiffer Vacuum ASM 340 is an easy-to-use, high-performance and durable leak detector providing short cycle times and high throughput for ensuring vacuum furnace integrity. It performs helium and hydrogen leak detection with sensitivity down to 5x10-12 mbar l/s in vacuum mode and 5x10-9 mbar l/s in sniffing mode. Featuring a vibrant color touch-panel display with SD card, the detector is easy to set up and use. A wireless remote control enables operation from a distance of up to 330 feet. Extrusions offer a combination of light weight and excellent thermal and electrical conductivity, along with strength and resistance to corrosion. Subject: Editorial comments and corrections
Description: The following information was collected:  Name: John  Email: robledoint@yahoo.com  Subscriber: No  Subject: Cory Booker Makes Disgusting Statement About Mass Shootings  Product: csmonitor.com  Message: Cory Booker Makes Disgusting Statement About Mass Shootings  (Tea Party PAC) – During an appearance on Sunday’s “AM Joy,” Sen. Cory Booker (D-NJ) had one very strong idea of who was to blame for Saturday’s back-to-back mass shootings in El Paso, Texas, and Dayton, Ohio.  Donald Trump.  And they say that it’s Trump who is repsonsibel for the division in this country?  Please.  This is truly sick.  “I believe in my faith there’s a saying that you reap what you sow,” Booker declared (oh, sure, pretend to be a Christian while blaming POTUS and not the man who actually decided to pick up a weapon and slaugter dozens of people).  “And Donald Trump has been sowing this kind of hatred in our country when he talks about invasions and infestations and shit-hole countries when he tells people to go back, he is responsible and sowing these kinds of divisions to hate mongers, in fact failing to even condemn them where we saw in Charlottesville where he talks about there being good people on both sides,” he went on.  “And so I believe this president is responsible,” Booker declared.  “In fact, I believe presidents should take responsibility, and his words have been fueling white supremacy and giving license to them, and we’re seeing the horrific results of hatred today. I also want to say he’s responsible to do something substantive about this problem in terms of not just his rhetoric but the actions he’s supporting. He’s done nothing to keep these weapons of mass destruction out of people who want to do horrific harm, and that, too, is responsibility that lies at his feet.”  This, coming from a man who is using a mass shooting, less than 24 hours after the gunman pulled the trigger, to draw on his own political talking points on national TV.  “The president has been a moral failure,” Mr. Morality continued.  “He has sown the seeds we are seeing now become this harvest of hate. He is responsible. He is a problem in this nation that is driving so much of this hatred. And if we can’t just clearly say that, I don’t care if you’re Republican or Democrat, when the president of the United States is using that kind of hateful language, if you are silent in that, you are complicit of the problem. If you don’t think, have a prognosis demonize people, calling them invaders, calling people infestation, if you cannot see that that rhetoric is contributing to the violence and hate in our country, then you are unfit to serve,” he declared.  “This is a moral moment in America. It’s not about party. This is about moral clarity. And it is time for us to call it like it is. This president is contributing to a climate of hate in our country, which we see, unfortunately, being punctuated by hateful violence and he has to take responsibility for that. If not, we must remove him from that office,” he continued.

Subject: dépêches du 06 Août 2019
Description: Dépêches du 06²12345 Août 2019  Image  Récapitulatif des dépêches du 06 Août 2019:  1. Le Conseil de l’Entente dévoile sa proposition pour lutter contre le terrorisme dans ses Etats membres; 2. Le HCRRUN met en garde les fraudeurs qui compromettent le processus d’indemnisation; 3. La CNDH lance les activités du Mécanisme national de prévention de la torture au Togo;  Image   Le Conseil de l’Entente dévoile sa proposition pour lutter contre le terrorisme dans ses Etats membres  Lomé, le 06 Août 2019-  La 16ème réunion ordinaire du Comité des experts des 5 pays membres du Conseil de l’Entente (Bénin, Burkina Faso, Côte d’ivoire, Niger Togo) a pris fin le lundi 5 août 2019 à Lomé.  Débutée le vendredi 2 août dernier, cette rencontre a permis aux participants d’examiner les comptes arrêtés au 31 décembre 2018 et définir de nouvelles perspectives pour l’organisation. A cette occasion, le Secrétaire exécutif du Conseil de l'Entente, Patrice Kouamé a présenté son rapport d’activité au Comité des experts dans différents domaines.  Entre autres, dans le secteur de la coopération politique avec l’observation des élections et dans le secteur de la sécurité, avec la proposition d’un nouveau mécanisme dénommé : « Mécanisme d’entente de renseignement », qui vise à lutter contre le terrorisme.  Parlant du compte financier, les Commissaires aux comptes ont estimé que lesdits comptes ont été fidèles à la situation actuelle du Conseil. « Pratiquement, plus de 90% du budget ont été consommés », ont-ils indiqué à cette occasion. A préciser qu’entre le 1er janvier et le 31 mai 2019, il est noté une trésorerie de plus de 3 milliards de FCFA alors que les créances des Etats sont estimées à 2,5 milliards de F CFA.  Selon Patrice Kwame, le comité a aussi pris connaissance du rapport provisoire de l’étude relative à l’élaboration d’une stratégie de promotion des activités génératrices de revenus et créatrices d’emplois pour les jeunes et les femmes de l’espace.  Sa mise en œuvre a-t-il dit, permettra au Conseil de l’entente de disposer de statistiques pertinentes sur la situation de la jeunesse et des femmes et d’appréhender les causes et les conséquences du chômage et du sous-emploi des jeunes, afin de trouver des solutions pérennes.  La future stratégie fera des propositions aux pays en matière de lutte contre la migration des jeunes. La stratégie dont l’étude sera renforcée par deux consultants sera enfin fondée sur le modèle du Centre Régional de Formation pour l’Entretien Routier (CERFER), un établissement de référence aujourd’hui dans la sous-région.  Abordant la question sécuritaire au sein des pays membre du Conseil, le comité des experts a condamné fermement les attaques terroristes perpétrées au Bénin, au Burkina-Faso et au Niger. Il a eu à exprimer sa compassion à ces Etats et présenter les condoléances aux familles des victimes tout en souhaitant un prompt rétablissement aux blessés.  Notons qu’en marge des travaux, des récompenses ont été remises au trois gagnants du concours, meilleur jeune entrepreneur organisé dans le cadre de la 25ème édition de la tranche commune entente dont le tirage avait eu lieu à Lomé. Chacun des lauréats a reçu au cours de la session de Lomé, un chèque de 5 millions de franc CFA.  Image  Le HCRRUN met en garde les fraudeurs qui compromettent le processus d’indemnisation  Lomé, le 06 Août 2019-  Le Haut-commissariat à la réconciliation et au renforcement de l’unité nationale (HCRRUN) a annoncé le lundi 5 août 2019 à travers un communiqué, avoir constaté des fraudes, qui mettent à mal le bon déroulement de ses opérations d’indemnisations.  Ces fraudes sont orchestrées par certains responsables et agents des préfectures et tribunaux qui délivrent, « sur la base de fausses informations, des documents à des victimes moyennant paiement d’un pourcentage variant entre 5 et 10% du montant de l’indemnité », a indiqué le HCRRUN dans son communiqué.  Si les fraudeurs ont pu être démasqués, l’institution présidée par Awa Nana Daboya informe que « désormais, ces stratagèmes délictueux seront portés à la connaissance du public et leurs auteurs répondront de leurs actes devant la justice ».  Cette annonce du HCRRUN intervient alors que le processus d’indemnisation des victimes de 2005 a repris depuis le 22 juillet dernier dans les Régions des Plateaux, Centrale et de la Kara. Jusqu’au 10 août, les victimes recensées par le HCRRUN dans ces régions obtiendront leur part d’indemnisations.  Elles (les victimes) bénéficieront non seulement de la prise en charge médicale et psychologique dont les frais seront entièrement assurés par le HCRRUN, mais également d’une indemnité financière conformément au montant fixé par la Commission Vérité Justice et Réconciliation (CVJR).  Pour rappel, le programme d’indemnisation des victimes des violences sociopolitiques de 1958 à 2005 au Togo est l’une des recommandations formulées par la Commission Vérité Justice et Réconciliation (CVJR). Le gouvernement y a déjà alloué une enveloppe de 5 milliards FCFA pour cette deuxième phase qui a débuté depuis le 27 novembre 2018.  Image   La CNDH lance les activités du Mécanisme national de prévention de la torture au Togo   Lomé, le 06 Août 2019-   Le 20 juillet 2010, le Togo a ratifié le protocole facultatif à la convention contre la torture. Ce traité lui fait obligation de mettre en place un Mécanisme national de prévention de la torture (MNPT). Ainsi, le gouvernement a donc choisi de confier la tâche à la Commission nationale de droit de l’homme (CNDH).  C’est dans cette perspective que la CNDH a procédé le lundi 5 août 2019 à Lomé, au lancement des activités d’un projet d’appui à l’opérationnalisation dudit Mécanisme. Ce projet sera exécuté par la CNDH en collaboration avec le Collectif des Associations Contre l’Impunité au Togo (CACIT). Le Mécanisme consiste à effectuer des visites régulières dans les lieux de détention afin d’examiner la situation des détenus.  Des séances de formation sont aussi prévues pour le renfoncement des capacités des différents acteurs notamment, les agents de la justice, les corps habillés, les organisations de la société civile ainsi que les membres de la CNDH.  L’objectif est d’outiller ces acteurs de la chaine pénales sur les rudiments nécessaires pour mieux prévenir la torture et autres peines ou traitements cruels, inhumains ou dégradants dans les lieux de privation de liberté.  « Le mécanisme consiste à faire des visites régulières et inopinées dans les lieux de détention. Ceci, dans le but de prévenir la torture sous toutes ses formes. Pour ce faire, les participants sont invités à plus d'assiduité afin d'assimiler les thématiques inscrites à l'agenda, notamment, les instruments de prévention de la torture, le MNP et son fonctionnement, la responsabilité des acteurs dans les lieux de privation de liberté », a précisé la présidente de la CNDH, Nakpa Polo.  Le représentant du Ministre en charge des Droits de l'Homme, Komlan Narteh-Messan, n'a pas manqué d'exprimer la reconnaissance du gouvernement à la CNDH. Le gouvernement, a-t-il dit, mesure à sa juste valeur la portée du soutien que chaque acteur devra apporter à la Commission dans son combat contre la torture et autres mauvais traitements, en particulier et pour l'enracinement des droits de l'Homme en général au Togo.  Précisons que la mise en œuvre de ce Mécanisme s’inscrit dans le cadre des engagements pris par le gouvernement devant le Comité des nations unies de lutte contre la torture, d’améliorer les conditions de détention des prévenus au Togo. Subject: Share your comments with the Sentinel Editors [#5275]
Description: Title * The beauty of moderation Author By Geoffrey Hibbs Web Address (URL) of page https:/sentinel.christianscience.com/issues/2019/8/121-32/the-beauty-of-moderation Name *    Consuela Allen Email Address *   consuelacs@yahoo.com Share your Comments: *  I’m grateful for the wonderful weekly and monthly periodicals I get delivered to my mailbox — both postal and electronic. But to use an American baseball metaphor, the August 12th Sentinel is a homerun! Geoffry Hibb’s cover article on “The beauty of moderation” is so helpful in pointing out that we can challenge extreme thoughts about exercise, diet, and life/work balance.  I also loved Mark Swinney’s article “Are we independent thinkers?” and the healing he experienced from challenging matter-based thinking. And George Moffett’s article “Taking the time to listen to his voice” was deeply healing and much-needed in these times of constant distractions. It seems that a theme running though every article was about true Spirit-based thinking.  No wonder that Mary Baker Eddy wrote on the very first page of Science and Health, with Key to the Scriptures “The time for thinkers has come.”  Comment Publication *  I give permission to publish my comment. Subject: Is delaying menopause necessary, or even a good idea?
Description: Stephanie????, I have a story that Modern Parenthood???? may want to cover.  Many women approach menopause with a mixture of dread and relief. As menstruation and ovulation (and the chance of conception) exit, menopause symptoms like hot flashes, night sweats, weight gain and memory loss usually arrive.  So, when it was announced a few days ago that physicians in England performed a procedure that could delay menopause by up to 20 years, many people are asking for clarity on the exact benefits of this bit of modern medicine.  Physicians in Birmingham, England performed this procedure on 10 British women ranging in age from 22 to 36:  · A portion of a patient’s ovaries are removed, and the tissue is then cryogenically frozen. · Later, when approaching menopause, doctors thaw and re-implant the tissue, restoring the patient’s younger, natural hormones.  Board-certified fertility specialist Mark Trolice, M.D. said that ovarian tissue reimplantation has the potential to restore ovulation and extend fertility until the newly implanted ovarian tissue egg number is depleted.  The British physicians say they developed this procedure to delay the onset of menopause-related issues like osteoporosis and heart conditions.  Dr. Trolice said that it could, in theory, prolong fertility well beyond menopause, which occurs on average at age 51.  However, delaying menopause doesn’t mean anyone is aging backwards—the pregnancy risks associated with maternal age remain.  And for women who find menstruating for 30 to 40 years to be long enough, delaying menopause might seem a bit ridiculous.   “While I applaud the investigators in their pursuit for safer and more natural management of hormone regulation in women who will be naturally facing menopause, it is dubious these women will desire 25 to 30 additional years of pregnancy risk, contraception or periods,” Dr. Trolice said.  Mark Trolice, M.D (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQB5XdBYAL3LRYS6ByxFsQrFR1Q2tSoGQ-2BbliHhdkw3zVL_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs3Hindq6qSO1V03Jd-2B9a7so8Pwm052CwQbgUl-2B7J-2BxPbPAx7-2F7HKkwS6zlTlKylKkbMYvsM0-2FNS62F06D4OXAOtBgQ2RamGneeX6cGxyCbWrMUI4pLhTX-2BpYsYEC-2Fk4keZTT3DNn9kSGRtD5VaAGItW-2B-2BU0I-2F57cjlFi4edfWPaJSqXHt8HKEaRPPgTOFAcDefd8NfKUPeU5DIityQkzyiaxALMJ7sF6yvCk9I1K-2Fku6v27ojtUSGob0B1-2BOC46IIY-3D . directs Fertility CARE (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQB-2BfRABnwnYhMjeCCX0kgi0NTRjzAu6v-2FnP4EJvk7-2FLo0_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs3Hindq6qSO1V03Jd-2B9a7so8Pwm052CwQbgUl-2B7J-2BxPbPAx7-2F7HKkwS6zlTlKylKkbMYvsM0-2FNS62F06D4OXAOtBgQ2RamGneeX6cGxyCbWrN-2BOSS6mCwhDwDqSjIwHB5pu0eKnKBdreBgdRlY5kI28axST5Om6Ok6e8Iz7HaHcXgV8EtfsUNqZuBeM50RFEpT1rWwDQwjehPdnx3YYyJ3o7IvAIGUVyp43FrILMNwq4rXGd9zsYdclfuhLPZO973s-3D (Center of Assisted Reproduction & Endocrinology) in Winter Park, Fla. and clinical associate professor in the Department of Obstetrics and Gynecology at the University of Central Florida College of Medicine in Orlando, Fla. Dr. Trolice is author of “The Fertility Doctor’s Guide to Overcoming Infertility: Discovering Your Reproductive Potential and Maximizing Your Odds of Having a Baby (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQB1tCP7lKc3DhBX9U6E5LwPr-2BCqf0xeuUF1BeQRBNcpH81wxE7mVuDaFWUc-2Fv1Hirhaf8BFAFZnrU-2BpqtCOcU9I0-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs3Hindq6qSO1V03Jd-2B9a7so8Pwm052CwQbgUl-2B7J-2BxPbPAx7-2F7HKkwS6zlTlKylKkbMYvsM0-2FNS62F06D4OXAOtBgQ2RamGneeX6cGxyCbWrIUOOCrPfpORhd6wU6q8R-2FjbfINdMwpBwJKQMP-2FXWy1v-2BhjPKlKU1QlH98mhtBvyAX7hv3PL1n-2FL6PQr-2Fli4brIAp9QLGw7crJsq7yTPMF59BitAu5mW4np7c1VU0Ubu3itjgjd-2BSFSkGPOZRR6zoR0-3D ,” which will be released in October. Subject: Editorial comments and corrections
Description: The following information was collected:  Name: John  Email: robledoint@yahoo.com  Subscriber: No  Subject: Ocasio-Cortez Next target.... the democratic party!?  Product: csmonitor.com  Message:  Ocasio-Cortez’ next target… the Democratic Party!? AUGUST 9, 2019 LINKEDIN TWITTER There’s a coup taking place in the Democratic party as radicals like Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez, D-N.Y., seize control — and they’re trying to chase out anyone with even remotely moderate views.  And by next election, the Democrats could be in shambles, wondering what went wrong!  The same far-left socialist “progressives” that helped send Ocasio-Cortez to Washington are hoping to repeat that success.  Sponsored: “Know-it all” scientists EMBARRASSED by Army vet  As with Ocasio-Cortez, that formula doesn’t begin with running against a Republican.  It begins by attacking a fellow Democrat!  The far-left Justice Democrats – which backed Ocasio-Cortez as well as fellow “Squad” representatives Ayanna Pressley, D-Mass., Rashida Tlaib, D-Mich., and Ilhan Omar, D-Minn., in 2016 – just endorsed three new candidates for Congress.  And in two of those cases, they endorsed far-left candidates to take on already seated Democratic members of Congress, just as Ocasio-Cortez did when she unseated longtime Rep. Joseph Crowley, D-N.Y., in a primary challenge.  In this case, the group backed Alex Morse, who is launching a primary challenge against Rep. Richard Neal, D-Mass., and Morgan Harper, who is primarying Rep. Joyce Beatty (D-Ohio).  Neal, in particular, would be a major target; he’s served since 1989 and is chair of the House Ways and Means Committee, often considered one of the most powerful committees in Congress because of its budget control.  Sponsored: However, Neal has angered the far left for supposedly not going far enough or moving fast enough in demanding President Donald Trump’s tax returns.  That’s a weakness the Justice Democrats now hope to exploit.  The third candidate, Kara Eastman, will seek to run against Don Bacon, R-Neb.  And all three have had to embrace the Justice Democrat platform, vowing to support a far-left socialist agenda that includes abolishing the healthcare system as we know it.  Instead of private health insurance and a system incentivized by a free market, they back a “Medicare for all” plan that economists believe could be disastrous to both healthcare in general as well as to the economy as a whole.  They also pledge to back the radical Green New Deal, which could restrict, tax or even ban everything from cars to air travel to hamburgers.  Sponsored: The group’s candidates also want to make college education free, open the borders and even open up prisons to allow many offenders out (as well as decriminalizing many offenses).  But there is also good news for conservatives hidden in this.  Two pieces of good news, to be precise.  First, the party’s internal civil war means it is difficult if not impossible for them to function – which could help ensure the radical agenda fails in Congress.  That’s already visible now as House Speaker Nancy Pelosi, D-Calif. struggles — and often fails – to keep her conference unified.  And second, while leftists may be able to beat entrenched politicians in primaries, where few people turn out, they don’t do quite as well in actual elections, when Americans often reject extremists.  Sponsored: How to restore your memory in 1 hour  In fact, the overall Justice Democrats record is downright dreadful.  In 2018, the group endorsed 79 candidates in primaries. Just 26 of them won, or had a success rate of less than 1 in 3.  But it gets worse: Of those 26, just seven won seats in Congress, a success rate of just 9 percent.  And it gets worse still, as exactly NONE of their endorsed candidates running in essential “swing” districts won, proving that extremist views can’t win in the most important races of all.  That means Republican candidates lining up against far-left Justice Democrats in Congressional races could have an easier time winning their own elections… and help ensure that they take back the House in 2020.  — Walter W. Murray is a reporter for The Horn News. He is an outspoken conservative and a survival expert, and is the author of “America’s Final Warning.”  The Horn News Radio POPULAR Controversial anti-Trump ESPN host scores book deal Family cat defies stereotypes, goes for SWIM Boy calls 911, reports his hunger, officials deliver… Active shooter scare in Times Square causes CHAOS New TV series to explore Clinton impeachment Toilet explodes after lightning strike! Subject: Share your comments with the Sentinel Editors [#5264]
Description: Title * A child’s prayers heal hearing problem Author By Inge Bock Phillips Web Address (URL) of page https:/sentinel.christianscience.com/issues/2019/8/121-32/a-child-s-prayers-heal-hearing-problem Name *    Karen Neff Email Address *   kneff386@gmail.com Share your Comments: * I was so moved by the words of the writer,"Since God is all-harmonious, I decided to honor God by not being afraid anymore." The motive to honor God was so pure and childlike and touched me deeply. I immediately adopted this as my motivation and goal in living ...to honor God by not being afraid anymore. Subject: Encouraging Kids to Be Outdoor Explorers, Like Dora
Description: NWF_Logo Color.png  Contact: Jessica Ordóñez-Lancet, National Wildlife Federation, ordonezlancetj@nwf.org, 202-797-6809       Encouraging Kids to Be Outdoor Explorers, Like Dora ‘Dora and the Lost City of Gold’ Will Debut in Theaters on August 9  WASHINGTON, D.C. (August 8, 2019) — To encourage kids and families to get outdoors and explore nature the National Wildlife Federation is proud to team up with Dora and the Lost City of Gold – in partnership with Paramount Pictures and Walden Media. Featuring a majority-Latino cast, the film represents the vital role that wildlife, nature, and family play in Hispanic and Latino cultures, while inspiring kids from all backgrounds to go outdoors and build a lifelong love of nature and wildlife.  “Dora inspires millions of children to explore nature and connect with wildlife. As parents and caretakers, it is our responsibility to help children appreciate our natural resources and provide them with opportunities to get outside every day and discover the amazing natural wonders all around them,” said Collin O’Mara (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQByFMfRk-2FmqglOdsFdkDuF8un3xtvjMneZ1yQXg7M4F5uv0z5JszWOPVI5EhnDPzHTg-3D-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs2fddw0YacdqQrItOEmHZuh-2B2lirh-2FRRqmOz-2FnQermRWHF0ysaopwuf4TGhm2I59Y21UWjMJ6vh-2FY5DBOAB-2BGJisJ5P8Ew8UQBhpZTfBejgZ9WKMwA5JpBvqcF9TabsyZ6hbvYeCASpXTFUHtuhy0dfMopC8gds6bXbnEMonlFsE-2B-2BbGBm8O-2FSjdJEcX4-2BygkZl2GyfXqcR9xGHElKELANsiUjVeZ1-2B9v99-2FjfpBLNNlWnxZOnsPWWZbrjpRrAM-2Bdo-3D , president and CEO of the National Wildlife Federation. “We at the National Wildlife Federation are thrilled to partner with Paramount Pictures and Walden Media to connect more kids with wildlife and the outdoors through Dora and the Lost City of Gold (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQBya3aKQC15-2BL5bdHuFl280cXXqa3sNGtcyeB-2FRVPo5LG_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs2fddw0YacdqQrItOEmHZuh-2B2lirh-2FRRqmOz-2FnQermRWHF0ysaopwuf4TGhm2I59Y21UWjMJ6vh-2FY5DBOAB-2BGJisJ5P8Ew8UQBhpZTfBejgZ5HaCHI-2FQOD1ntvUui5kbuBiS-2BKZeUXiJi-2Fw-2BexuUeeSdN-2BU6KoZPJYKnRzK-2FLTFcwPtRqfBywOkKfJLSVMbZrTZw-2BF2HR2-2F-2FLq4V37By-2BLMaDB80mvTzMfT-2FOSSZdcDhAqAPwxBFXRUS-2F9SMn0KMjY-3D , an inspiring movie that brilliantly highlights the benefits of nature for our younger generations and their families.”  “Our country has so many places to explore — from neighborhood parks to our National Parks and Forests, Wildlife Refuges, and over 245 million acres of public lands across the United States. These vital outdoor spaces belong to all of us for hiking, camping, viewing wildlife, and so much more,” said Camilla Simon (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQB5XHL-2FJnKhQl8FtuOh0P-2FXV4psbj9-2FOKiZaRXBFcDVuO_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs2fddw0YacdqQrItOEmHZuh-2B2lirh-2FRRqmOz-2FnQermRWHF0ysaopwuf4TGhm2I59Y21UWjMJ6vh-2FY5DBOAB-2BGJisJ5P8Ew8UQBhpZTfBejgZznRoO8JE5gl8-2FtP-2BS0Ddf4M4ZUIxL0oh8ZRtcTBRYb7h07hC1wTGGOY-2BPhXabMgnQVFa3LlKMxsAZtM1mKlmqTq8LbCJr0aGOe-2Bg42WALZdkmkHscIOZfdExafbDMhv-2FpgQVZkE1t5iV8-2F8vF2o6tM-3D , Executive Director of Hispanics Enjoying Camping, Hunting, and the Outdoors (HECHO), a program of the National Wildlife Federation. “Just like Dora, at HECHO we understand the importance of connecting to the land and water that sustains us. That is why we promote and honor centuries-old Hispanic land-based traditions that are intertwined with our well-being.”  Having spent most of her life exploring the jungle with her parents, nothing could prepare Dora (Isabela Moner) for her most dangerous adventure ever – High School. Always the explorer, Dora quickly finds herself leading Boots, her best friend, a monkey; Diego (Jeff Wahlberg), a mysterious jungle inhabitant (Eugenio Derbez); and a rag tag group of teens on a live-action adventure to save her parents (Eva Longoria, Michael Peña) and solve the impossible mystery behind a lost city of gold.   “Like Dora’s family and my family, Hispanic and Latino families have been enjoying the great outdoors for generations, and our ancestral connection to the land should not be lost,” said Eva Longoria (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQB8Py45Kv8f-2BYRfyH7N0ZolPg90fROiA-2F0Ko5Z199YALNL8mNEDq1FReC1mQSwkFlLpwS3WyyqjkpEG2i-2FThUHHs-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs2fddw0YacdqQrItOEmHZuh-2B2lirh-2FRRqmOz-2FnQermRWHF0ysaopwuf4TGhm2I59Y21UWjMJ6vh-2FY5DBOAB-2BGJisJ5P8Ew8UQBhpZTfBejgZ06FLLFmfXzIgJu3Uc4PyJ-2BCWCgpJdgnzqEK00L2VVELwOxSEcVdxzhpcwYfRqv-2FRUFk-2FA0CT6z8X9drJJkxBLIJk1csI3YNmxFY5zMu7bUSltRI9MA5v4IoL322pllTQntEfFQu58QHK5CXOymnFkE-3D Subject: Editorial comments and corrections
Description: The following information was collected:  Name: General Kelly  Email: operation.removal.djt@navy.gov  Subscriber: No  Subject: Is US doomed?  Product: csmonitor.com  Message: US is on the brink of massive civil unrest in 2019 Observe the sequence, the roiling pattern of the American political condition, the descending scale: From unity and consensus, to hard-edged partisanship, to intense polarization, to tribalism. What’s next? Does the continuum lead to widespread unrest, violence in the streets? With an increasingly unmoored President purposely stoking divisions for perceived political gain, the possibility need well be contemplated. The work of Donald Trump was less threatening to the public order when the Democrats were relatively passive. But the resistance to the bottom-feeding Oval Office occupant took on a new fervour this past week with Congresswoman Maxine Waters, rage in her voice, urging followers to confront Republican lawmakers in restaurants, department stores, gas stations. She appeared to be advocating public clashes: “Tell them they’re not welcome any more, anywhere.” In the wake of their policy of separating families at the Mexican border, other top Republicans were denounced in the public square. Mr. Trump responded to Ms. Waters, calling her “an extraordinarily low IQ person.” Of her desire to confront members of his administration, Mr. Trump said, “Be careful what you wish for, Max!” He once advised supporters at a rally to “knock the crap out of” protesters. There are more detonations that could be set off by his push to blow up the international trading system. His preparedness to ignore Constitutional norms is apparent. His willingness to see the system as rigged and wage war against the so-called deep state is clear. A wild President invites any number of wild scenarios. Civil conflict, the likes of which the United States has not seen in decades, is not out of the question.

Description: View this email in your browser (https://mailchi.mp/marianne2020/iowa_8_9_19-248725?e=86750cd953) https://www.marianne2020.com/ FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE August 9, 2019 Juan Rodriguez National Press Secretary juan@marianne2020.com (312) 771-0263   PRESIDENTIAL CANDIDATE MARIANNE WILLIAMSON TO APPEAR AT THE IOWA STATE FAIR AND IOWA WING DING DURING IOWA SWING  Des Moines, IA - Democratic Presidential Candidate, best-selling author, and activist Marianne Williamson returns to Iowa this weekend and will enthusiastically take part in Iowa political traditions of Presidential candidates attending the Iowa State Fair in Des Moines and the Iowa Wing Ding event in Clear Lake, IA on Friday, August 9.  On Saturday, August 10, Ms. Williamson will visit the Meskwaki Settlement Powwow in Tama, IA and will later attend the Passport to Victory event in Central City, IA. Subject: Book Review / Interview Op - WOOF: A Love Story of Dogs, Classic Music, and Life
Description: Dear Stephanie Hanes :  Robert Freeman, musician and retired professor, poignantly weaves together a story of his unwavering love for his wife of 42 years, their 17 canine companions and his tenured career as an educator in his latest book, Woof! A Love Story of Dogs, Music, and Life.  I would be happy to send you a complimentary copy of this touching book in consideration of an interview, review or feature. Please read the following press release, and contact me to schedule an interview. I'd also be happy to send you JPEGs of Freeman and the book cover. Thank you.  Teresa Hinojosa Ascot Media Group, Inc. Post Office Box 2394 Friendswood, TX 77549 832.569.5773 Direct 281.333.3507 Main  teresa@ascotmediagroup.com ascotmedia.com  (This press release may be reprinted in part or entirety by any print or broadcast media outlet, or used by any means of social media sharing)  FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE  Woof! Celebrates Lifelong Love, Music And The Wonderful World Of Canines  **Austin, TX, August 8, 2019** — Retired music professor and accomplished musician Robert Freeman shares reflections of his 42-year marriage, their 17 canine companions and his remarkable career as an educator in WOOF!  A Love Story of Dogs, Music, and Life.  Freeman was a music school director when he fell in love with his assistant, Carol. Throughout their union they created a loving home for 17 dogs, all of which are featured through striking photography between the covers of Woof! This book is a celebration of true love — between people and between people and animals — and beautifully relates the eternal truth that the world would be a better place if everyone simply took good care of each other.  Author Robert Freeman is a musicologist, Steinway artist, and a professional musician. Over 42 years of marriage to his wife, Carol, he has been the proud master of 17 dogs — 11 of them golden retrievers, six of them American dogs. Having made tenure at MIT, he directed the Eastman School of Music for 24 years, presided over the New England Conservatory for three, and served as dean of the College of Fine Arts at the University of Texas in Austin for seven. He is also the author of the highly praised The Crisis of Classical Music in America. For the Eastman School's website honoring Freeman, please visit http://ascotmedianews.com/em/lt.php?c=18339&m=20699&nl=1198&s=f56e244f21aead307c5458b70ab88d81&lid=272658&l=-https--www.esm.rochester.edu/freeman/.  WOOF!  A Love Story of Dogs, Music, and Life Page Publishing Released: April 30, 2019 ISBN-10: 164462673X ISBN-13: 978-1644626733 Direct link to book on Amazon.com at: www.amazon.com/s?k=WOOF%21+by+Robert+Freeman&i=stripbooks&ref=nb_sb_noss_2   ###  TIP SHEET  Q & As available upon request.  Possible discussion topics for Robert Freeman:  1.    How a music school director fell in love with his assistant and went on to provide homes for 17 dogs — 11 golden retrievers and six  American dogs 2.    Today's world of classical music 3.    Baseball  Ascot Media Group is compliant with the can-spam act. Subject: Protect Children's Religious Right to Go to School in MA
Description: Oppose H.3999 - A Discriminatory Bill for a Child's Right to an Education in MA, by Removing Religious Exemptions  https://www.gopetition.com/petitions/oppose-h3999-a-discriminatory-bill-for-a-childs-right-to-an-eductaion-by-removing-relgious-exemptions.html   Target:Massachusetts Public Health CommitteeRegion:United States of America <https://www.gopetition.com/petition-campaigns/united-states-of-america> Website:www.righttoaneducation.com  On 5/31/2019 Representative Andres X. Vargas filed a bill 'An Act relative to vaccinations and public health' which if passed, would remove the right to religious exemption from vaccination for school children.  In Massachusetts, the law provides that every child deserves a public education without discrimination on the basis of race, color, sex, gender identity, religion, national origin, sexual orientation or disability. Andres Vargas’ proposed elimination of the religious exemption for vaccination is deeply discriminatory, unwarranted and unnecessary.  MA has achieved one of the highest rates of vaccination in the country without coercive means and exceeds levels for herd immunity. There is no public health crisis. There is unlikely to be a public health threat from vaccine preventable illness, given the high rates of vaccination. Furthermore, Massachusetts code already provides for protocols to prevent the spread of communicable illness, through the use of quarantine and temporary school exclusion.  So what does Andres Vargas’s proposed legislation accomplish, given that there is no significant public health threat from communicable illness? It will marginalize children based on their parent’s religious beliefs and exclude children from a public education. This will be true, even if a parent declines just one vaccine. Furthermore, it unfairly targets those from socioeconomically disadvantaged communities and those from the special needs community, who do not have reasonable alternatives to public education and who depend on public education to counter institutionalized bias and afford equal opportunity, equity and justice.  Massachusetts should continue to lead the way in creative public health solutions to significant public health problems, like the opioid crisis and the rise of mental health issues. We should not needlessly impinge on religious civil liberties and create more public health issues by excluding children from necessary educational and therapeutic services.  Our country was founded on the premise of universal civil liberties. Massachusetts should continue to be a leader in the defense and preservation of those sacred liberties.  We, the undersigned, call on the Massachusetts Joint Committee on Public Health to vote in opposition of H.3999.     - Sign the petition Subject: Putting God Back in Our Culture
Description: What we can do to stop more violence...  View this email in your browser (https://mailchi.mp/caapusa/bill-owens-of-caap-215453?e=d2b3ef1fec) https://secure.anedot.com/coalition-of-african-american-pastors-usa/dream-derailed-sponsors?mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID] http://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fmailchi.mp%2Fcaapusa%2Fbill-owens-of-caap-215453&mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID] Share (http://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fmailchi.mp%2Fcaapusa%2Fbill-owens-of-caap-215453&mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID]) http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Putting+God+Back+in+Our+Culture:&mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID] https%3A%2F%2Fmailchi.mp%2Fcaapusa%2Fbill-owens-of-caap-215453 Tweet (http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Putting+God+Back+in+Our+Culture:&mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID] https%3A%2F%2Fmailchi.mp%2Fcaapusa%2Fbill-owens-of-caap-215453) http://us6.forward-to-friend.com/forward?u=92112f469785e1152be1993c1&id=de8e89edf3&e=d2b3ef1fec Forward to a Friend (http://us6.forward-to-friend.com/forward?u=92112f469785e1152be1993c1&id=de8e89edf3&e=d2b3ef1fec)   ** Putting God Back in Our Culture ------------------------------------------------------------ Dear Partner,  When Laura Ingraham asked me what we needed to do to stop violence in our culture, all I could think about was why our country isn't talking more about God.  I had been invited on the Ingraham Angle (https://video.foxnews.com/v/6068772140001/?mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID]#sp=show-clips) to talk about my CNN appearance and upcoming book, A Dream Derailed (http://adreamderailed.com/?mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID]) . But the violence in Chicago and the mass murders in Dayton and El Paso were as much on the host's mind as my own.  So when she asked me - as someone who has worked in the inner city - what these cities need, I said:  "Chicago needs spiritual leadership. Politicians cannot solve these kinds of problems. It's our families, and our ministers, and our communities that must come together to address these issues."  (You can watch my interview below or on YouTube (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cEb7-cGxtVM&mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID]) .)  What I wanted people to understand is that looking to politicians to solve such problems is futile. Not only does it pass on both responsibility and blame, but it's unfair. Politicians don't have the power to fix something so fundamental. They can only address things at the edges, once law gets involved. But how to do you stop a problem before it starts? That isn't a political issue. That's a spiritual one.  After my interview with Laura, a dear friend shared with me a few words from other ministers who have been spreading the same message (https://onenewsnow.com/culture/2019/08/07/you-kick-god-out-of-the-culture-this-is-what-you-get?mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID]) . Abraham Hamilton III recently spoke on American Family Radio about how we are "mis-educating" people to devalue life. He said:  "We have a generation [now] that has been force-fed, through their mis-education systems, the message that they're nothing but animals; [that] there's nothing unique or sacred about human life – [and therefore] life has no purpose, no meaning. That is what society has force-fed a generation. ...  You kick God out of society – the God who says 'You were made in My image' and that life is precious – you reject Him [and] expel Him from society; yet want to complain when people act like animals. We can't have it both ways." Dr. James Dobson is a friend and supporter of CAAP who has given us great insight and help. He recently wrote about the growth of socialism in our country and how this political mindset alienates us from God. In a letter that he urged us to share (https://drjamesdobson.org/about/august-newsletter-2019?sc=hpslider1&mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID]) with others, he quoted a sermon from Dr. Jack Graham:  "Socialism is fundamentally contradictory to the Christian worldview. It seeks to suppress all people, especially Christians, in favor of the state. And the way that it does that is by breaking down the institutions that God has established, particularly marriage and the family. When I see the breakdown of our culture, our society, and especially the family, it truly breaks my heart. There is a spiritual war going on all around us. It is a battle for the heart and soul of our nation. We are fighting for the sanctity of life, the sacredness of biblical marriage, sexual identity, religious freedom, and, yes, economic freedom that gives us the ability to prosper within a nation. Socialism opposes each of these cornerstones." https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cEb7-cGxtVM&mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID]  To put it bluntly, we are missing God in our homes, neighborhood, schools, and culture. We are missing both the discipline and hope that come with prayer. We are losing our understanding of the sanctity of all human life and the respect for life that flows from that principle.  We are losing what it means to be a neighborhood or community. These are not ways to describe geographic proximity. They're statements about how we look out for each other, share values, and ensure the betterment of the next generation.  Our country is losing touch with God.  How did this happen? How do we fix it? These are some of the questions I wrestle with in my upcoming book. Though it's not yet on sale, we are giving a "thank you" copy to donors who gift CAAP $30 or become a sponsor of the book for $100. To learn more, visit the book's website (http://adreamderailed.com/?mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID]) , or just go to the donation page. (https://caapusa.org/2019/07/get-a-signed-copy-of-a-dream-derailed/?mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID])  We live in an increasingly secular society, one that has turned away from the lessons of the Bible. If we want to change things, we need to put God back in our culture. Remember Matthew 24:12: Because of the increase of wickedness, the love of most will grow cold.  For faith, family and freedom, Rev. Bill Owens  P.S. Your prayers and financial support will help us put this country on the right path. Please help us as we strengthen our grassroots network and work to educate and inspire pastors, community leaders, and politicians to defend our Christian rights. Donate to CAAP today!  (https://causes.anedot.com/caap-email-appeal?mc_cid=de8e89edf3&mc_eid=[UNIQID])  The Coalition of African American Pastors, [aka] The Coalition for American Action and Principles, is a grass roots movement of Christians who believe in traditional family values in American public life.  We believe in protecting the lives of the unborn, and defending the sacred institution of marriage. CAAP does not endorse, support, or oppose any candidate for political office. Any mention of public figures herein is purely for discussion and educational purposes and should not be interpreted as a statement of electoral support or opposition.  *The Coalition of African American Pastors is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization. Subject: Press Release - Changing how we treat land “vital” in fight against climate change – UN development chief reacts to new climate report
Description: Image       Changing how we treat land “vital” in fight against climate change – UN development chief reacts to new climate report  New York, August, 8 – The UN Development Programme (UNDP) Administrator Achim Steiner today joined international climate experts in calling for action following the release of a UN report on the devastating impacts of current land use practices on the climate.  “Unless we make bold changes in the way we produce our food and manage our land, we will not be able to cut emissions sufficiently and keep global warming below 1.5 degrees Celsius,” says Achim Steiner, UNDP Administrator. “The IPCC (Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change) report clearly demonstrates how critical sustainable land management is for climate action and for human well-being.”  The IPCC Special Report on Climate Change and Land, released Thursday 8 August, cautioned the global community to stop the irresponsible exploitation of the planet’s natural resources, or reach a point of no return in the climate crisis.  Agriculture, forestry, and land use changes are responsible for about 23 percent of global greenhouse emissions. Reducing global emissions therefore requires not only radical changes in the transport and energy sector, but also in land use. Natural land processes absorb carbon dioxide equivalent to almost a third of carbon dioxide emissions from fossil fuels and industry.  “This transformation will not be easy,” says Steiner, “but it is necessary and it is possible. The solutions are at hand. Now we must scale them globally to work towards a zero carbon, climate-resilient future.”  Elsewhere, the report finds that about one third of food production is lost or wasted, and that climate change will increasingly affect food security.  Working to eliminate food waste and eating a balanced diet are essential to reducing emissions from our food system. Coordinated action to address climate change can simultaneously improve land, food security and nutrition, and help to end hunger.   UNDP is working with partners to support 105 countries in protecting and restoring their natural resources. The organization supports nature-based solutions that promote sustainable land management and landscape stewardship, through integrated land use planning and management, adoption of sustainable agriculture practices and land governance approaches that build resilience of landscapes, ecosystems and communities. Subject: Tom Steyer to Stump in Iowa for First Time as Candidate
Description: FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: Friday, August 9, 2019 CONTACT: press@tomsteyer.com Tom Steyer to Stump In Iowa for First Time as Candidate Steyer will attend numerous political tentpole events in Hawkeye State this weekend  (Des Moines, IA, August 9, 2019) — This upcoming weekend, August 9-12th, Democratic candidate for President Tom Steyer will make his first swing through Iowa since announcing his campaign for the Democratic presidential nomination. On Friday August 9th, Steyer will attend a lunch with the Hardin County Democratic Club at The River Tap in Iowa Falls, Iowa, before attending the famous Wing Ding Dinner in Clear Lake at the Surf Ballroom and Museum.  Saturday will include a meet and greet with the Story County Dems at Cafe Diem in Ames, IA and speaking at the Passport to Victory event in Central City Saturday evening. Finally, on Sunday, Steyer will speak at the Des Moines Register’s Soapbox event at the Iowa State Fair.  Along with other meetings with community and local leaders, Steyer will be available for individual press events throughout the weekend.  Below is Steyer’s open press schedule.   Press interested in attending the open events should rsvp to: press@tomsteyer.com   Friday August 9, 2019  Lunch and Discussion with Hardin County Democrats  WHEN: Friday, August 9, 2019 12:30 PM CDT  WHERE: The River Tap 701 Railroad St, Iowa Falls, IA 50126  Wing Ding Dinner  WHEN: Friday, August 9, 2019 5:00 PM CDT  WHERE: Surf Museum and Ballroom 460 N Shore Dr, Clear Lake, IA 50428  Saturday August 10, 2019  Meet and Greet with Story County Democrats  WHEN: Saturday August 10, 2019 9:00 AM CDT  WHERE: Cafe Diem 229 Main St, Ames, IA 50010  Sunday August 11, 2019  Speak at Soapbox rally hosted at the Iowa State Fair  WHEN: Sunday August 11, 2019 1:30PM CDT  WHERE: Iowa State Fair 3000 E Grand Ave, Des Moines, IA 50317  Paid for by Tom Steyer 2020.  ###  About Tom:  Tom Steyer left his successful investing business seven years ago to give his own money and all his time and energy to fighting for progressive causes. He soon became one of the country’s leading forces in registering more young voters and voters of color, fighting climate change, working for racial justice, and helping secure better lives for all Americans. Tom has led a number of people-first, grassroots campaigns that have repeatedly defeated powerful special interests, beating big oil to win clean air laws, forcing big tobacco to pay its share of healthcare costs, and closing a billion-dollar corporate tax loophole to fund public schools.  Tom and his wife Kat Taylor were early signers of the Giving Pledge, a commitment to give the bulk of his fortune to good causes before they die. Tom’s dedication to doing what is right comes from his parents. His father was a lawyer who prosecuted Nazis at the Nuremberg Trials; his mother was a journalist and teacher who volunteered to teach prisoners in New York City jails. Tom says his parents showed him the power of having the courage to do the right thing. Their greatest lesson, he says, was that our actions speak louder than our words – what we do is more important than what we say.  ============================================================ Tom Steyer 2020 | P.O. Box 626 | San Francisco, CA 94104 | USA  Want to change how you receive these emails? You can ** update your preferences (https://tomsteyer.us3.list-manage.com/profile?u=19050e87bef316243d0543d86&id=74b0c16992&e=8cbfa1c52b) or ** unsubscribe from this list (https://tomsteyer.us3.list-manage.com/unsubscribe?u=19050e87bef316243d0543d86&id=74b0c16992&e=8cbfa1c52b&c=a8ff7f23fd) .  --  To unsubscribe from this group and stop receiving emails from it, send an email to customerservice+unsubscribe@csps.com.

Subject: 'Generations'
Description: Your article on Woodstock, and the editorial on the generation gap referred to various "generations." They appear continously in the media.  Me  boomerbaby boomersilentgeneration XMillenials     As a Depression-era reader, I can't keep track of these terms. I urge you, every 3-6 months, to publish a simple chart that delineates the years covered by these so-called 'generations.'    Hugh

Subject: Re: Mensaje de La Junta Directiva de la Ciencia Cristiana
Description: Buenas noches Muy agradecido por el presente correo. Y por supuesto desde ya muy agradecido por su presencia en la fecha indicada. Compartiré con los miembros de nuestra Iglesia el mensaje PARA QUE SEAMOS CAPACES. Nos juntaremos para compartir y coordinar.  En breve respondemos.  Saludos  Jorge T     Enviado desde mi iPhone  El 5 ago. 2019, a la(s) 4:22 p. m., Clerk of The Mother Church <MessageFromClerk@christianscience.com<mailto:MessageFromClerk@christianscience.com>> escribió:   [http://staticapp.icpsc.com/icp/resources/mogile/39945/5facdbb87a6ada6141b4d6b075d2e5c4.jpeg]    Queridos amigos:    Con gran alegría comparto con los secretarios de las iglesias filiales y sociedades de la Ciencia Cristiana de Perú la siguiente carta de La Junta Directiva de la Ciencia Cristiana. Tenemos la esperanza de que ustedes trabajen con sus miembros para considerar la información contenida en ella. Una vez que se hayan definido los detalles, enviaremos otra carta a los miembros de La Iglesia Madre de Perú.    Con afecto, Barbara Fife, C.S.B. Secretaria de La Iglesia Madre  _______________________________________________________________  Estimados amigos:    El tema de nuestra Asamblea Anual “para que seamos capaces”, una oración de posibilidades siempre crecientes, ha abierto el pensamiento más ampliamente a lo que Dios nos ha dado para servirnos unos a otros y para servir a toda la familia humana, viendo a cada individuo bajo la verdadera luz de la Ciencia del Cristo.    Nos encantaría seguir considerando este tema con ustedes para saber cómo piensan que esto está sucediendo en el lugar en el que viven. Además, nos gustaría saber si hay algo más que La Iglesia Madre pueda hacer por ustedes para ayudarlos a cumplir esta misión.    Con este propósito, La Junta Directiva de La Iglesia Madre y su Presidente, Fabián Smara, están pensando en reunirse con los miembros y asistentes de las iglesias, las sociedades y los grupos de la Ciencia Cristiana de Perú el día sábado 2 de noviembre. Nos gustaría asistir al servicio dominical en Lima a la mañana siguiente.    Gaby Mejía, Asistente Ejecutiva de Rich Evans, Presidente de la Junta Directiva, y de Fabián Smara, Presidente de La Iglesia Madre, coordinará con ustedes los detalles de la visita. Por favor pónganse en contacto con Gaby, quien habla español, escribiendo a mejiag@csps.com<mailto:mejiag@csps.com> y dígannos si tienen interés en tener esta reunión y qué horario y lugar resultaría conveniente para ustedes y sus miembros. Gaby les enviará más información acerca de los planes futuros del Presidente para las visitas a Perú.    Tenemos la expectativa de compartir con todos ustedes la provisión del Amor.    Con mucha gratitud,    Rich Evans, Presidente de La Junta Directiva de la Ciencia Cristiana    Sign up for emails from Clerk<https://click.icptrack.com/icp/relay.php?r=1061302589&msgid=6558872&act=48E8&c=39945&destination=http%3A%2F%2Fchristianscience.com%2Fmember-resources%2Fchurch-news%3Futm_source%3DiContact%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_campaign%3DMessage%2520from%2520Clerk%26utm_content%3DDON%2BNOT%2BDELETE%2BAM%2Breminder> | Other news from the Church<https://click.icptrack.com/icp/relay.php?r=1061302589&msgid=6558872&act=48E8&c=39945&destination=http%3A%2F%2Fchristianscience.com%2Fmember-resources%2Fchurch-news%3Futm_source%3DiContact%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_campaign%3DMessage%2520from%2520Clerk%26utm_content%3DDON%2BNOT%2BDELETE%2BAM%2Breminder> [http://files.icontact.com/templates/v2/CleanAndSimple/images/facebook.gif]<https://click.icptrack.com/icp/relay.php?r=1061302589&msgid=6558872&act=48E8&c=39945&destination=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fworldwidechristianscience%3F_rdr> [http://staticapp.icpsc.com/icp/resources/mogile/39945/e7110bf41c22f9ff6031ade3561cf79a.png] <https://click.icptrack.com/icp/relay.php?r=1061302589&msgid=6558872&act=48E8&c=39945&destination=https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fprayerandhealth>  Privacy policy<https://click.icptrack.com/icp/relay.php?r=1061302589&msgid=6558872&act=48E8&c=39945&destination=http%3A%2F%2Fchristianscience.com%2Fterms-of-service%3Futm_campaign%3DMessage%2520from%2520Clerk%26utm_content%3DDON%2520NOT%2520DELETE%2520AM%2520reminder%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_source%3DiContact> | We welcome your comments and may publish some of them anonymously, unless you state otherwise. Subject: Subscription  Account 22991
Description: My annual subscription is set for renewal on October  25, 2019.  I am writing to be certain that the subscription is NOT auto-renewed and is cancelled on that date.  I have read the Monitor off and on for several years and finally decided to subscribe.  I had found the reporting, for the most part to be "fair and balanced", to borrow the tagline from a news source that  most certainly is not.  I have found though that the tone of the articles in the Monitor have become increasing liberal, even progressive, in their tone and presentation.  Clearly, the many of the writers have viewpoints that is creeping into their writing.  Sometimes it is nuanced, sometimes not.  I think of myself as a Libertarian but, I will admit I lean towards conservatism.  I do though,  try hard to see all sides of a discussion.   I had just finished reading the articles "Why America's big cities have become the President's punching bag" and "Why El Paso is determined not to roll up the welcome mat".  I found these articles to present a one-sided view with meager attempts to present differing viewpoints.  I found myself sitting here repeating " but, but"   in my head.  That is when I decided I do not need to subscribe to a publication that writes with a clear bias.  I can find that anywhere without paying for it.  I guess that finding a source that is truly fair and balanced is just  too much to hope in this day and age.  My account information is below.  I would appreciate an acknowledgement that my subscription will be cancelled in October.  Sincerely,  Stephen Wood  22991 Stephen Wood 457 Windy Hill Ln Straw Plains, TN 37871-3217 United States sewood@att.net  --  To unsubscribe from this group and stop receiving emails from it, send an email to daily+unsubscribe@csps.com.
