Subject: Current Issues class
Description: Hello, I’m writing as a Social Studies teacher at the Principia Upper School. This semester I’m teaching a Current Issues course and I would like the students to focus primarily on articles from The Christian Science Monitor. I notice that the students would only be able to access 3 articles unless they have a digital subscription. I’m wondering if there are reduced rates or free subscriptions for students? I have less than 10 students in the class and it is only one semester, so the access would be for September-November. My hope would be that the deep dive into news through the CS Monitor would encourage them to be subscribers on their own in the future. Thank you for letting me know the subscription options for the CS Monitor use in class. Sincerely, Beth Pomeroy 570-369-3070   Beth Pomeroy Principia US Social Studies  --  To unsubscribe from this group and stop receiving emails from it, send an email to daily+unsubscribe@csps.com.

Subject: Tom Steyer to Address Presidential Gun Sense Forum via Video
Description: FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: Saturday, August 10, 2019 CONTACT: press@tomsteyer.com Tom Steyer to Address Presidential Gun Sense Forum via Video  (Des Moines, IA, August 10, 2019) — Today, in a prerecorded address (https://youtu.be/B-3SwHqrKdo) , Democratic presidential candidate Tom Steyer joined the Presidential Gun Sense Forum organized by the Everytown for Gun Safety Action Fund, in Des Moines, Iowa. In the video Steyer directly addressed the complicit role of the NRA and GOP in the most recent tragedies.  “When we see tragic events like the ones we saw in El Paso, Texas, and Dayton, Ohio, it can make us sad. It should make us feel sympathy for our fellow Americans, but we shouldn’t be surprised,” said Steyer in the video. “This is the absolute result of political corruption. The gun manufacturers through the NRA control the Republican Party and this president and they’ve prevented common sense gun legislation."  Steyer is not attending the forum due to a scheduling conflicts, but he wholeheartedly believes in the work several organizations are doing in trying to achieve sensible gun reform, especially those seeking to ban assault weapons and restricting high-capacity magazines.  In the past, a Steyer-founded organization, NextGen America, partnered with Giffords, Everytown for Gun Safety, and ACRONYM to launch Our Lives, Our Vote, a program that empowered high school-aged Americans to vote out politicians beholden to the NRA by registering their peers to vote.  Tom Steyer supports universal background checks, red flag laws, banning assault weapons, and restricting high-capacity magazines. He supports prohibitions on 3D firearm printing, and banning gun possession for those who have been convicted of domestic violence. Tom thinks that gun manufacturers should not be immune from civil liability, and would support funding to study gun violence as a public health issue. He also supports federal databases to track gun sales, and opposes concealed carry reciprocity.  Paid for Tom Steyer 2020.   ###  About Tom:  Tom Steyer left his successful investing business seven years ago to give his own money and all his time and energy to fighting for progressive causes. He soon became one of the country’s leading forces in registering more young voters and voters of color, fighting climate change, working for racial justice, and helping secure better lives for all Americans. Tom has led a number of people-first, grassroots campaigns that have repeatedly defeated powerful special interests, beating big oil to win clean air laws, forcing big tobacco to pay its share of healthcare costs, and closing a billion-dollar corporate tax loophole to fund public schools.  Tom and his wife Kat Taylor were early signers of the Giving Pledge, a commitment to give the bulk of his fortune to good causes before they die. Tom’s dedication to doing what is right comes from his parents. His father was a lawyer who prosecuted Nazis at the Nuremberg Trials; his mother was a journalist and teacher who volunteered to teach prisoners in New York City jails. Tom says his parents showed him the power of having the courage to do the right thing. Their greatest lesson, he says, was that our actions speak louder than our words – what we do is more important than what we say.  ============================================================ Tom Steyer 2020 | P.O. Box 626 | San Francisco, CA 94104 | USA  Want to change how you receive these emails? Subject: The Old Schoolhouse® Magazine Is Coming to Walmart
Description: The Old Schoolhouse® Magazine Is Coming to Walmart   Display problems? View this newsletter in your browser. ( https://mychristiandaily.com/?email_id=793&user_id=93437&urlpassed=W3ZpZXdfaW5fYnJvd3Nlcl9saW5rXQ&controller=stats&action=analyse&wysija-page=1&wysijap=subscriptions )  The Old Schoolhouse® Magazine Is Coming to Walmart, bringing 120 pages of homeschooling help for families  FAITH NEWSWIRE ( https://mychristiandaily.com/?email_id=793&user_id=93437&urlpassed=aHR0cDovL3d3dy5mYWl0aC1uZXdzd2lyZS5jb20v&controller=stats&action=analyse&wysija-page=1&wysijap=subscriptions ) – Shoppers will soon discover homeschooling’s premiere publication gracing the shelves of another major retail chain. The Old Schoolhouse® is pleased to announce that it has accepted an invitation to partner with Walmart, which will carry the quarterly publication The Old Schoolhouse® Magazine. Walmart joins a growing list of retailers selling the homeschooling community’s go-to trade magazine. Other vendors include Barnes & Noble, Books-A-Million, Target, Walgreens, and Kroger grocery stores. The Old Schoolhouse® Magazine ( https://mychristiandaily.com/?email_id=793&user_id=93437&urlpassed=aHR0cDovL3d3dy50aGVvbGRzY2hvb2xob3VzZS5jb20&controller=stats&action=analyse&wysija-page=1&wysijap=subscriptions ) (TOS) is published by homeschoolers for homeschoolers. Most of the people working for TOS are homeschooling moms and dads living in various parts of the United States and Canada. They work from home, communicating via computer and phone, to produce a product that helps and encourages families around the world. Publishers Paul and Gena Suarez are the homeschooling parents who started The Old Schoolhouse® as a newsletter nearly two decades ago. “We are happy to be working with Walmart!” says Gena, who believes this will help to increase the number of home educating families. “When Mom picks up our magazine, she will see that she can do this! Outstanding resources are available to help her be a successful homeschool teacher.” One such resource is SchoolhouseTeachers.com ( https://mychristiandaily.com/?email_id=793&user_id=93437&urlpassed=aHR0cDovL1NjaG9vbGhvdXNlVGVhY2hlcnMuY29t&controller=stats&action=analyse&wysija-page=1&wysijap=subscriptions ), the curriculum division of The Old Schoolhouse® Magazine. One membership to SchoolhouseTeachers.com gives a family unlimited access to over 400 online courses, plus streaming videos and numerous teaching tools. During the August BOGO sale (on now), new members are purchasing their first two years for less than the price of one! The company that publishes these print and digital resources to help parents teach their children “at home where they belong” is delighted to have a new home for its print magazine—Walmart! About The Old Schoolhouse®  The Old Schoolhouse® (www.theoldschoolhouse.com ( https://mychristiandaily.com/?email_id=793&user_id=93437&urlpassed=aHR0cDovL3d3dy50aGVvbGRzY2hvb2xob3VzZS5jb20&controller=stats&action=analyse&wysija-page=1&wysijap=subscriptions )) is a privately held corporation that publishes the industry-leading homeschool education print magazine, The Old Schoolhouse® Magazine, as well as hundreds of books and planning support tools for homeschooling families. SchoolhouseTeachers.com, a division of The Old Schoolhouse® Magazine, supports over 7,000 member families, with more than 400 courses for preschool through high school, as well as educational videos, World Book Online, transcripts, report cards, planning tools, and recordkeeping. Established in 2001, The Old Schoolhouse® Magazine is focused on providing high-quality, encouraging, affordable solutions for homeschooling families. Publishers Paul and Gena Suarez are available for radio interviews. Contact: Paul and Gena Suarez  888-718-4663  publisher@theoldschoolhouse.com ( mailto:publisher@theoldschoolhouse.com )  Unsubscribe ( https://mychristiandaily.com/?email_id=793&user_id=93437&urlpassed=W3Vuc3Vic2NyaWJlX2xpbmtd&controller=stats&hash=9628bbb4ecf2217df32ca4ebf0d94f93&action=analyse&wysija-page=1&wysijap=subscriptions ) - Edit your subscription ( https://mychristiandaily.com/?email_id=793&user_id=93437&urlpassed=W3N1YnNjcmlwdGlvbnNfbGlua10&controller=stats&hash=088fe43862520d7ad44fedf086acdf97&action=analyse&wysija-page=1&wysijap=subscriptions )

Subject: Libby's 2018 healing.docx
Description: Hello, my friend Libby Weir has tried and tried to submit this via the  submit a testimony via  https://jsh.christianscience.com/submit/manuscript-submission several  times as I have as well and it drops out. So here it is. If you could  please forward it to the jsh for publication we would be most grateful   Sancy Nason, +61 409 465 531    Libby Weir/ +61 403 629 625 libbywei@yahoo.com.au    I would like to submit this testimony for consideration for  publication, as it was so meaningful for me.   I have studied this life transforming Science my entire life. During  that time, I have witnessed and experienced countless proofs of  healing. Many  of these have come about quickly. Others  have required  persistence, and have compelled spiritual growth before being  realised.   However it was not until late in the year 2017, that I was challenged  in a way I have never been before.   On Christmas Day of that year, I was aware of persistent pain in my  right arm. I did nothing about it, expecting it to pass. However  during the following week, the pain spread to my other arm, my hips,  and then to both of my legs. Before long I was experiencing extreme  pain, in all my muscles and joints and bones, and I was forced to  severely curtail my activities.   I gave up my morning run, and before long I was having trouble  climbing the stairs in my home, getting in and out of bed, and even  sitting in any chair that was below a certain height. Getting in and  out of the car became challenging, and even raising my arms to the  steering wheel, required much exertion. All this was accompanied by an  extreme weight loss.   I initially felt no fear, as I was so confident in the power of God  to overcome any adverse condition. However as the weeks dragged in to  months, and there was no improvement, I began to feel anxious.   Despite knowing intellectually that I was not dealing with a real  condition, rather a false belief, I found myself wondering what  “it” was, and what  had caused it.  Someone very close to me had battled with very similar symptoms and  had subsequently passed on, and I found myself remembering this  vividly, as I had nursed him during much of this time.  I knew it was essential that I overcome both the fear, and the vivid  images of this loved one’s suffering, images that I had not realised  I was still harbouring.  I was able to continue working, and did not tell anyone of my  challenge, except two practitioners who, lovingly worked with me at  different times.   Whilst not working, or being with my family, my entire time was spent  nurturing a sincere desire to feel closer to God, and to better  understand my relationship with Him.   I had to learn much needed lessons in humility. I had always prided  myself on being fit and energetic, and even felt a little smug, when  friends and acquaintances around me were undergoing hip and knee  replacements, being thankful that I would never have to succumb to  either. I was compelled to see that these people were also,  in their  true being, intact and free from all sense of decline.   I pondered deeply, a much loved statement from Science and Health,  page 283, line 4, which reads “Mind is the source of all movement,  and there is no inertia to retard or check it’s perpetual and  harmonious action.” This assured me that movement had its source in  Mind, not in muscles, therefore it could not be impaired.   Whilst driving, or simply trying to climb the stairs I clung to  another favourite passage from the same textbook. “ All that God  imparts moves in accord with Him, reflecting goodness and  power.”  (Pg 515, line 22.) I constantly challenged the insidious suggestions  of deterioration  and incapacity. I affirmed that power was not a  personal possession, rather it was a reflected attribute.   Nights were very difficult, due to the pain,  and my sleep was often  disturbed. However, I slowly progressed from dreading the long   wakeful nights, to learning to really appreciate the stillness and  solitude as I became so aware of God’s presence and His intimate  care for me.   Many nights I would have only four or five hours sleep, but  I was  always able to rise the following morning feeling rested and  untroubled.   After several months, I found myself becoming very discouraged. I  would have periods of such clarity and spiritual assurance, followed  by disappointment when I failed to see physical improvement. Again and  again I needed to remind myself that I did not need to look to matter  to determine my wellbeing. I also knew that when my trust  in my  oneness with God became unshakeable, I would have no need to look to  matter to have my soundness verified.   In May of the same year I was due to fly to Africa, to resume aid  work which I have been undertaking for many years. This deadline  loomed large in my thought. I simply could not imagine how I could  undergo such a long flight, let alone accomplish  the physical work  demanded of me there.   Many times I felt I should postpone the trip, but I knew the work was  important, and felt strongly that I should be there. I prayed for  boldness and courage.   As the date approached there was still very little physical  improvement. A practitioner lovingly supported me during the flight,  and I was conscious of leaning on God, every step of the way. On  several occasions, strangers offered to help with my luggage, and I  was given a seat which allowed me to get up easily, and move around  when I needed to.   As I settled in to my new routine in Africa, I felt a shift taking  place in my thought. All sense of discouragement had given way to a  certainty that I would be healed. Impatience gave way to trusting ‘  God’s disposal of events’. I was aware that I had finally  conquered all fear.   My biggest challenge was climbing the steep and rough track to the  rural village where I was working, and then descending the same track  at the end of the day. However, there was always a little child, or  someone around to assist. For many years they had been watching me  running up and down that track, but no one ever commented, or  questioned me.   One day while reading a Christian Science Journal article, I came  across this statement. “ The great Way- shower Illustrated  Life  unconfined, uncontaminated and untrammelled by matter.”   I looked up the meaning of untrammelled as I was not familiar with  it. One definition of it read “not deprived of freedom of action or  expression, not restricted or hampered.” This statement was so  relevant to me, and became uppermost in my thought daily.   The healing came slowly, almost imperceptibly. I became aware that I  was moving more freely. I was able to raise my arms to brush my hair.  I could sit in chairs that were a normal height, and then rise out of  them normally. I could turn over freely in bed, bend over, and pick  things up from the floor. By the time I had completed my three months  voluntary work in Africa, I was almost entirely free.   On returning home, other symptoms, such as swollen feet, and extreme  thirst disappeared. I also naturally regained my normal weight.   This healing required much mental discipline. I was forced to hold to  the truth vigorously, and at the same time refuse to be distracted by  the severity of the physical condition. I now look back on this as a  time of growth in grace and humility. I learnt needed lessons in  patience and persistence.  Above all, I took away from this  experience, the necessity for courage and boldness, and an unwavering  trust in the incontestable power of God.   Libby Weir. NSW, Australia.  libbyweir@yahoo.com.au

Subject: The Return of the Russian Leviathan, by Sergei Medvedev  -  (REVIEW COPY? INTERVIEW REQUESTS?)
Description: Publishing November 8, 2019   ** ------------------------------------------------------------  Russia’s relationship with its neighbours and with the West has worsened dramatically in recent years. Under Vladimir Putin’s leadership, the country has annexed Crimea, begun a war in East Ukraine, used chemical weapons on the streets of the UK and created an army of Internet trolls to meddle in the US presidential elections. How should we understand this apparent relapse into aggressive imperialism and militarism?  In this lively and well-informed account, the Russian sociologist and political scientist Sergei Medvedev sets out to explain the unexpected transformation of the country during Putin’s third term in office, from 2012 to 2018. He argues that this new wave of Russian nationalism is the result of mentalities that have long been embedded within the Russian psyche. Whereas in the West, the turbulent social changes of the 1960s and a rising awareness of the legacy of colonialism have modernized attitudes, Russia has been stymied by an enduring sense of superiority over its neighbours alongside a painful nostalgia for empire. It is this infantilized and irrational worldview that Putin and others have exploited, as seen most clearly in Russia’s recent foreign policy decisions. In the annexation of Crimea, Medvedev shows how patriotic rhetoric served to trump considerations of political or human cost. Inciting nationalist fervour may have been an effective way to consolidate Putin’s power within the Kremlin but it fractured relations with the West and it can only mask for so long the inability of the state to address the myriad of social and economic challenges facing Russia today.  This sharp and insightful book, full of irony and humour, shows how the archaic forces of imperial revanchism have been brought back to life, shaking Russian society and threatening the outside world. It will be of great interest to anyone trying to understand the forces shaping Russian politics and society.  The Author:  Sergei Medvedev is Professor in the Faculty of Social Sciences at the Higher School of Economics in Moscow. The host of several history and current affairs programmes on TV and radio and a regular commentator in the print, broadcasting and online media, he is one of Russia’s most in-demand public intellectuals. Subject: Inspirational Show Guest / Review Request - One Arm But Not Unarmed
Description: Dear Stephanie Hanes :  One Arm But Not Unarmed is an empowering look at how one woman turned her own personal tragedy into a calling to help other trauma victims begin anew and ultimately become better versions of themselves. Suzan Nguyen was just 22 when she lost her right arm in a tragic accident. She spiraled downward and made a series of bad decisions before finding a way out of the darkness. Through One Arm But Not Unarmed, she shares her transformative five-step process for overcoming bitterness and adversity, and choosing to live your best life.  Here is a video that shows how to drop the draining depression and bounce back and enjoy life. As you can see, this author inspires! http://ascotmedianews.com/em/lt.php?c=18316&m=20677&nl=1198&s=f56e244f21aead307c5458b70ab88d81&lid=271958&l=-https--www.khou.com/mobile/video/news/give-mia-a-minute-july-3-2019-suzan-nguyen/285-af8fcd78-05af-4951-8413-57d73dd7da51     I would be happy to send you a complimentary copy of this deeply insightful book in consideration of an interview, review or feature. Please read the following press release, and contact me to schedule an interview. I'd also be happy to send you JPEGs of Nguyen and the book cover. Thank you.  Mike Dempsey Ascot Media Group, Inc. Post Office Box 2394 Friendswood, TX 77549 news@ascotmedianews.com ascotmedia.com 281.333.3507 Phone 800.854.2207 Fax  (This press release may be reprinted in part or entirety by any print or broadcast media outlet, or used by any means of social media sharing)  FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE  One Arm Shares Powerful Message Of Triumph After Tragedy  **Houston, TX, August 6, 2019** — Suzan Nguyen couldn't move her body. Couldn't open her mouth. Couldn't even blink her eyes to signal to those standing over her. She could hear the sirens. See the flashing lights. But she felt nothing. In the end, she would awake from her nightmare without her right arm, which had been severed above the elbow in a car accident. The trauma of the event proved life-altering for Nguyen, who was 22 at the time. She went on to make a series of bad decisions that affected herself, her family and her friends in ways she regretted for years to come.   In time, Nguyen realized that one day she would have to create her own change or her life would not get better.   "When one day became my day one, I took responsibility for my life and decided to be better, not bitter,” Nguyen relates. "I realized that focusing on losing my arm was keeping me from focusing on the good things in my life. I took action using a five-step process, which I now use to help others discover how to be better versions of themselves.”  One Arm But Not Unarmed is Nguyen's empowering look at how she overcame bitterness and adversity, and eventually emerged with renewed determination to live her best life. This insightful book aims to help other trauma victims navigate life's peaks and valleys through strategies for making good decisions, transforming their emotional responses to life's inevitable ebb and flow, and ultimately knowing and living their purpose. Are you ready for one day to become day one?  Author Suzan Nguyen was born and raised in Port Arthur, Texas. She now lives in the Houston area and enjoys life with her husband, Phu, who is a talented chef. Nguyen is a transformative speaker and life coach who began the #bebetter movement in 2017. She completed classes at the Institute of Professional Excellence in Coaching, is a certified Happiness Chief Encouragement Officer, and is deeply fulfilled by helping others through telling her story, transforming perspectives, and shedding light on the journey all trauma victims experience.   To learn more about Nguyen, please visit www.bbnbcoaching.com. Connect with her on Instagram at @suzan_nguyening and on Facebook, LinkedIn and Twitter at Suzan Nguyening.  One Arm But Not Unarmed Publisher: WSA Publishing Released: March 28, 2019 ISBN-10: 1948181355  ISBN-13: 978-1948181358 Available from numerous online retailers, including Amazon.com, BarnesandNoble.com and Walmart.com  ###  TIP SHEET  Q & As available upon request. Finished in one sitting. Engaging from beginning to end, and even though I didn't go thru a traumatic experience in life, I learned a lot from the book. Definitely recommend.”  "This book is an honest, down-to-earth portrayal of a life-altering event. It is one of those true stories that makes you want sit down with the author and ask questions because you just want to know more.”  Possible discussion topics for Suzan Nguyen:  1.    Peeling back the layers to create joy from within  2.    -#bebetter 3.    Gradient shades of pain  Ascot Media Group is compliant with the can-spam act. Subject: Become a Charter Member of the Guastavino Alliance
Description: Because Rafael Guastavino, father or son, created part of your site you are eligible to become a Charter Member of the Guastavino Alliance.  View this email in your browser (https://mailchi.mp/0f07b55ba8a1/become-a-charter-member-of-the-guastavino-alliance?e=2783a28ad4) First Church of Christ Scientist  Because Rafael Guastavino, father or son, created part or all of your site we would like to invite your organization to become a Charter Member of the Guastavino Alliance.  Please help us make sure this email reaches the correct person by forwarding it to the appropriate contact within your organization.  Join the Alliance (https://gmail.us3.list-manage.com/track/click?u=9a58e2cc8e26fb5162a68e7a0&id=fa032ae37d&e=2783a28ad4) The Alliance was recently formed by a group in Asheville, North Carolina, the location of the first two major sites to join the Alliance: Biltmore Estate (https://gmail.us3.list-manage.com/track/click?u=9a58e2cc8e26fb5162a68e7a0&id=446832fd1a&e=2783a28ad4) and the Basilica of St. Lawrence (https://gmail.us3.list-manage.com/track/click?u=9a58e2cc8e26fb5162a68e7a0&id=37ada13fd0&e=2783a28ad4) . Also here is the site of the Guastavino family home and tile production kilns as well as the senior Guastavino’s grave. The mission of the Guastavino Alliance is to champion the history and preservation of the Guastavinos’ over 1,000 works of vaulting and domes, which feature their unique structural tile method.  There are more than 600 extant Guastavino sites in 35 states and six countries. Our goal is to connect these sites in an alliance so that we may all work together in preservation, research, education, and advocacy of the Guastavinos' large body of work. We are anxious to share our experience and expertise with other sites and facilitate mutual sharing in many areas, including interpretive materials, publicity, social media, fundraising strategies, exhibits, grant opportunities, special events, conferences, lectures, etc.  A seminal event that led to the creation of the Guastavino Alliance was the donation by Dr. John Ochsendorf of the digital files for Palaces for the People (https://gmail.us3.list-manage.com/track/click?u=9a58e2cc8e26fb5162a68e7a0&id=da136eb99c&e=2783a28ad4) , an exhibit organized in 2012 as part of the Massachusetts Institute of Technology's Guastavino Project. All members of the Alliance are eligible to use these files for their own exhibits. Locally, we mounted an exhibit at the Swannanoa Valley Museum & History Center in Black Mountain, NC, which will will move to Pack Memorial Library in Asheville, NC, in September 2019. We are also designing a permanent outdoor exhibit in downtown Asheville.  Other benefits of membership in the Alliance include a periodic newsletter and the ability to purchase at reduced cost copies of Ochsendorf’s Guastavino Vaulting: The Art of Structural Tile. At this time we are not charging fees to join the Alliance, but welcome any donations to our 501c3 non-profit organization, which can be made online here (https://gmail.us3.list-manage.com/track/click?u=9a58e2cc8e26fb5162a68e7a0&id=7d9b4e4e3a&e=2783a28ad4) .  We are in the process of creating a website, which can be viewed in its beta form at https://gmail.us3.list-manage.com/track/click?u=9a58e2cc8e26fb5162a68e7a0&id=190929d040&e=2783a28ad4. It will include a full directory of Guastavino sites in the Alliance, a listing of resources available to Alliance members, and a news feed of Guastavino-related information.  I hope that your site will become a member of the Guastavino Alliance. I am happy to answer any questions you may have. Thank you for your consideration.  Sincerely, David Madden, Chair david@davidmadden.net (mailto:david@davidmadden.net) 828-419-0730  Join the Alliance (https://gmail.us3.list-manage.com/track/click?u=9a58e2cc8e26fb5162a68e7a0&id=b54b61366e&e=2783a28ad4)  ============================================================ Copyright © 2019 Guastavino Alliance, All rights reserved. Subject: Story / tips (Boston author): How to become resilient, not bitter, when life is challenging
Description: When her husband was arrested under shocking circumstances, author Diane Cook spiraled. Then she got MS. Here’s how she cut through the bitterness and grew resilient  Hi Stephanie? -  I thought you might be interested in the following story. Diane (a Boston-area resident) has penned an article and is also available for interview. Or let me know if you’d like to see a copy of her new book, So Many Angels (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQB9NiEmIXEWfdxPVBJGgLxaLXmCEu0yb-2FCXq7Ugo1COsPisWzUdi-2B730r5ZBLi-2Be8sRcrncy7JMcaODLR9uEqYZk-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs04I21YFduxE-2B8dkNLBpy8m8CLoOIU6HBz4Afn9ZyMR0Ap2OJvZiNrWVyuZ3V16eAsDadpFrQKryKKqazvt16fUH-2Boq1n-2BT8RE60rJkzIWt4Zec0gi63Gl3HlGabC-2FT5j9WBZqhBqbvOSQLVNZo1Xx0dL7cIOwKcBddCoSJkg7Qt0zE6eZGKpq-2FX3x6e5Cv0HG7s26Z16iU1TLB600ToU-2BxruvzZfyvyUYuytvAkvc0-2B423FxNZT70ku1WUA2IeXEE-3D , which tells her story in detail:  Over the past five years, words like “grit” and “resilience” have become trendy buzzwords that aim to provide a map for how to be successful, grow and change for the better.  But if resilience is the key to success, how do you cultivate it from scratch when something truly awful, something that demands the utmost resilience, happens out of nowhere?  Author Diane Stelfox Cook found herself staring this question dead in the eyes when her husband was arrested, leaving her and her two boys stunned, alone and unsure of what to do next.  Bitterness began to take hold. Until a friend suggested she focus on “choosing resilience”.  In her new article “How to become resilient, not bitter, when life is challenging”, Diane explains the methods she used to beat bitterness and strengthen her grit and resilience, even amid total life chaos.  Her tips include:  · Seek professional help. Not tomorrow, today. · Find something that you can do to help someone else. · Count your blessings.  Let me know if you’d be interested in seeing the article, speaking with Diane, or checking out a complimentary copy of her book.  - Emily    ______________________  If you would rather not receive future communications from BSPR, please go to https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=mAHw-2B8ZZluKmvldupnv96uLo9Y9fajlVzzV3E2AQMMy3o0jRx7vDS35Oho-2BRYwxVM-2F-2BL7LaoyWUUZGT3ACwSPGOnAmMJC-2BvGShXYnXoOxH5mwugzpHk8bzUlL7pdM6V6PGDiF7P8dTVS8BJV5IoVu-2BY769nbQ9u9f6U11s-2BeHbI-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs04I21YFduxE-2B8dkNLBpy8m8CLoOIU6HBz4Afn9ZyMR0Ap2OJvZiNrWVyuZ3V16eAsDadpFrQKryKKqazvt16fUH-2Boq1n-2BT8RE60rJkzIWt4axd1hBMDaHMkmFiUfQuP6-2BUws0zKw9OTAD16C1vo7MQiAbbiS94cMrmte5S0gNDEIDZfVW7lxOWxsfiegW9tFkEA1JYZAnEfgsxVfJcc0SEdLEx9wQSb-2BXvjMqCFQqki3uTKUMYy6q0eXpQpuPRfPk-3D  BSPR, 18 Main Street, Extension, Suite 409, Plymouth, MA 02360 United States  --  To unsubscribe from this group and stop receiving emails from it, send an email to customerservice+unsubscribe@csps.com.

Subject: Average Credit Card Debt By State, Revealed
Description: For Immediate Release   ChamberofCommerce.org Publishes Report Detailing Average Credit Card Debt by State   August 6, 2019 – ChamberofCommerce.org has released a report breaking down the average credit card debt that Americans owe by state. Rather than harp on the often-cited national figure of $1 trillion, the report aims to help by focusing on particular states, specific dollar amounts, startling statistics on interest and minimum payments, and revealing correlations regarding the credit card vice that’s currently gripping Americans – some worse than others.  The following are the three states with the highest credit card debt, followed by the three with the lowest.  Highest Average Credit Card Debt Alaska: $10,685      Virginia: $9,120 Texas: $9,100  Lowest Average Credit Card Debt Iowa: $6,726 Wisconsin: $6,737 North Dakota: $7,068  See every state’s average credit card debt, as well as descriptive graphics and analyses: https://www.chamberofcommerce.org/credit-card-debt-by-state  The over-use of credit cards has caused seemingly insignificant minimum payments to take thousands of dollars from unwitting (or financially-helpless) Americans in the form of interest. ChamberofCommerce.org found that individuals in several states are spending an extra $10,000 on their credit card purchases by only paying the minimum each month, something the Federal Reserve confirms is the norm for over 40% of debt-carrying Americans.  ChamberofCommerce.org created this report by compiling and analyzing data from the Federal Reserve (total credit card balances) and the U.S. Census Bureau (median annual household income). Interest payments and other related statistics were calculated separately using the aforementioned data.  # # #   About ChamberofCommerce.org ChamberofCommerce.org is a website dedicated to helping small business owners and entrepreneurs start, market, finance, and grow their businesses. By creating in-depth guides, how-tos, and reviews covering relevant business products, ChamberofCommerce.org hopes to help readers move past the pitfalls that are often to blame for small business failure.   Contact Rob Lora Media Outreach Manager Rob@ChamberofCommerce.org

Subject: Scientists crack the code to Improve stress tolerance in plants
Description: Hi,  My name is Ritwika, I represent the Public Relations team of Tokyo University of Science, Japan. Link: https://www.tus.ac.jp/en/  I am reaching out to you because we recently completed a research news article on a paper published in Plant Physiology<http://tx.bz-mail-us1.com/1/l/e63d07ea578f45488647fc5b801e87ef?rl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.plantphysiol.org%2Fcontent%2Fearly%2F2019%2F07%2F31%2Fpp.19.00530>. This study reveals one possible mechanism by which epigenetic regulation can improve the DNA damage response in plants. Plants are more susceptible to DNA damage than animals, therefore the findings of this study will be useful in creating resistant varieties of crop plants with improved growth and longevity and better characteristics, thus contributing to global food security.  Would you be willing to take a look and see if it's a good fit for your publication? If not, we understand. Here it is: Press Release article<http://tx.bz-mail-us1.com/1/l/79f13af2df9747698af7247cfc714e6d?rl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tus.ac.jp%2Fen%2Fmediarelations%2Farchive%2F20190802002.html>.  Below is the release, for your ready reference.  Tokyo, 6 August 2019  PRESS RELEASE   Scientists crack the code to improve stress tolerance in plants Novel epigenetic regulation mechanism underlies improved stress response in plants, which can be exploited for global food security  Epigenetic regulation—modification of gene expression from the “outside”—is an important part of the overall genetic processes within a cell. A group of scientists from Tokyo University of Science now reveals a novel epigenetic regulation mechanism that is involved in DNA damage repair in plants, thereby suggesting a possibility of reinforcing global food security.  In any eukaryotic organism, the DNA in a cell exists not as a loose strand, but as a highly condensed complex that consists of DNA and other proteins known as histones. Overall, this condensed structure is referred to as chromatin, and this packaging is important for maintaining the integrity of DNA structure and sequence. However, as chromatin restricts the topology of DNA, modification of chromatin (via modification of histones) is an important form of regulation of genes and is referred to as epigenetic regulation. Now, a group of scientists, led by Prof Sachihiro Matsunaga from Tokyo University of Science, has uncovered a novel epigenetic regulation mechanism, at the center of which lies a histone demethylase enzyme called lysine-specific demethylase 1-like 1 (LDL1). Prof Matsunaga states, “The novel mechanism of epigenetic regulation that we found is related to DNA damage repair in plants, and we believe that it has a lot of real-world applications.” This study is published in Plant Physiology.<http://tx.bz-mail-us1.com/1/l/9c3ec54230704165bd2eff693e8a81fa?rl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.plantphysiol.org%2Fcontent%2Fearly%2F2019%2F07%2F31%2Fpp.19.00530>  An organism’s genome is constantly subjected to various stresses that cause instabilities or errors in it, resulting in damages or “breaks” in the sequences. These breaks are repaired autonomously by a process called homologous recombination (HR), and thus, HR is essential for maintaining the stability of a genome. Like for all other genetic regulatory processes, the chromatin structure needs to be modified for HR to occur smoothly. Prof Matsunaga and team had previously discovered a conserved protein called RAD54; they found that RAD54 is involved in chromatin remodeling in the model plant Arabidopsis and thus aids in genomic stability and response to DNA damage. However, both the recruitment of RAD54 at the site of HR and the proper dissociation of RAD54 from the site are important for it exert its effects. When asked about their motivation for this study, Prof Matsunaga candidly states “Our previous study identified that RAD54 aids HR but the mechanisms of recruitment and dissociation were poorly understood. Our new study attempts to shed light on these mechanisms.”  Using techniques such as co-immunoprecipitation and mass spectrometry, the scientists first identified and shortlisted proteins that interact with RAD54 and regulate its dynamics with chromatin during HR-based DNA damage repair in Arabidopsis. They then identified, for the first time, that the histone demethylase LDL1 interacts with RAD54 at DNA damage sites. They found that RAD54 specifically interacts with the methylated 4th lysine amino acid on one of the four core histones in the chromatin, H3 (H3K4me2). The scientists then found that LDL1 suppresses this interaction by demethylating H3K4me2. They concluded that LDL1 removes excess of RAD54 from DNA damage sites via the demethylation of H3K4me2 and thus promotes HR repair in Arabidopsis. Thus, LDL1 ensures proper dissociation of RAD54 from the HR repair site in the DNA.  Hailing this exciting result, Prof Matsunaga says, “This finding is an important addition to plant science as well as basic molecular biology. This is an extension of our previous research that showed that RAD54 accumulated in damaged sites in Arabidopsis and that excessive RAD54 suppresses damage repair, which could be dangerous to the plant. Our new study shows that LDL1 aids and improves DNA damage repair by removing RAD54 from the damaged site.”  So, why are the findings of this study so important? Prof. Matsunaga explains this, too. “Unlike animals, plants are stationary and, therefore, more vulnerable to environmental stresses such as high temperatures, dryness, pathogens, parasites, and poor soil conditions,” says Prof. Matsunaga, “and these stresses suppress the development and growth of plants by causing DNA damage. Therefore, an efficient DNA damage response is crucial to ensure optimum growth and survival of plants. Our study reveals one possible epigenetic regulation mechanism that can improve the DNA damage response in plants.”  Finally, Prof Matsunaga touches upon the most important application of this group’s research. “Plants can be treated with LDL1 to artificially control epigenetic modification so that they become more tolerant to stresses such as infections, environmental stresses and mechanical stress,” says Prof. Matsunaga. “We think that this will be useful in creating resistant varieties of crop plants with improved growth and longevity and better characteristics, thus contributing to global food security.”  Reference  Titles of original paper:  LSD1-LIKE1-mediated H3K4me2 demethylation is required for homologous recombination repair  Journal:  Plant Physiology  DOI:  https://doi.org/10.1104/pp.19.00530  About The Tokyo University of Science Tokyo University of Science (TUS) is a well-known and respected university, and the largest science-specialized private research university in Japan, with four campuses in central Tokyo and its suburbs and in Hokkaido. Established in 1881, the university has continually contributed to Japan's development in science through inculcating the love for science in researchers, technicians, and educators.  With a mission of “Creating science and technology for the harmonious development of nature, human beings, and society", TUS has undertaken a wide range of research from basic to applied science. TUS has embraced a multidisciplinary approach to research and undertaken intensive study in some of today's most vital fields. TUS is a meritocracy where the best in science is recognized and nurtured. It is the only private university in Japan that has produced a Nobel Prize winner and the only private university in Asia to produce Nobel Prize winners within the natural sciences field.Website: https://www.tus.ac.jp/en/mediarelations/  About Professor Sachihiro Matsunaga from Tokyo University of ScienceDr Sachihiro Matsunaga is a Professor of Applied Biological Science in the Faculty of Science & Technology at the Tokyo University of Science. A respected and senior researcher, he has more than 150 research publications to his credit. He is also the corresponding author of this paper. His chief areas of interest include epigenetics, plant genetics, plant stress tolerance, agricultural science, and plant biotechnology. Subject: A healthy sex life is not wrinkle free
Description: Stephanie?,  With recent attitudes shifting about aging, it’s worth exploring how to shatter the myth that a healthy sex life is wrinkle free.  With women feeling vital longer, taking the taboo out of talking about issues like vaginal dryness and menopausal sex has never felt more relevant or worthy of a silver lining.   Leah Millheiser, MD, OBGYN at Stanford University is available to talk about how women aged 40+ and entering midlife can have their best sex ever and address common issues with intimacy with practical & easy-to-access solutions.   Let me know if you'd like to chat with Dr. Millheiser.   Thanks,  Lindsay   Lindsay Gross  646.964.4446    ______________________  If you would rather not receive future communications from Global Communication Works, please go to https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=JI3XGwl6BvjKk-2FipdOLyJRqWBmlRgMQWinaiZ-2BLdpTdLppdtFJkbzPlQbksQElRPywxtm2A4agRgmy7Eh9JNnP-2BbGqSrkqL-2FiPvdyxyCufifw8ehXN4-2FqZdJXk9MzSvRs7BWuw7YalUervp4-2Fo0P419oKBU1mWmWQIFki0BL-2F5jBESD8MnMJ4E8oyz7um4fQ_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs3l3SEcNPtunJZdbD-2FHCJ4zTo-2B0O56FgDxIwSb8wBgphz0lAfAAhDyY8ANdYKsAsl2JKHF5MwqXR-2BATfQuZDsu7zzc5z2DLo3l5U6meO-2Bbf78aIEeFn5-2Fzhf6QkCren4Yn5QkC0s1XXDqiEBVfa-2BZlGjQ9qLW6wVee71Zp-2B-2BIuK-2F1ORjalTCkHUSdnzpeXLddfwTjLj0QjphRxdce254zH4liFBuifg8g0T1UR4HZdhvK7epCj4685BsME1VbLW4KI-3D  Global Communication Works, 261 Madison Avenue, New York City, NY 10016 United States  --  To unsubscribe from this group and stop receiving emails from it, send an email to customerservice+unsubscribe@csps.com.

Subject: Home Pregnancy Test 101: Know The Basics
Description: Stephanie?,  You pee on a stick and then a few minutes later the answer to one of the biggest questions in a woman’s life appears, seemingly almost by magic, in a small window. But how does it all work? Not by magic, of course. There is a researched and exact science behind it all.  But, to break it down: What do you need to know about pregnancy tests when you think you might be pregnant?  Lakeisha Richardson, MD, OBGYN is available to offer her list of tips when taking a home pregnancy test--including what to look for in a test, what to do if your test is inconclusive, and what to do after a positive pregnancy test.   Let me know if this is something you'd like to chat with Dr. Lakeisha about.   Thanks,  Jaimie  Jaimie Weiner  646.964.4446    ______________________  If you would rather not receive future communications from Global Communication Works, please go to https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=JI3XGwl6BvjKk-2FipdOLyJRqWBmlRgMQWinaiZ-2BLdpTdLppdtFJkbzPlQbksQElRPywxtm2A4agRgmy7Eh9JNnDu5aSpZoZh3sCPGA5lsr9gAfkEATOGxoAppxla59k529-2B9didHuTI5Vx-2F8zBYXENR1x59ab-2BwHmXebi-2FkGiyPWoNALc0BcTlGgVXldxOWC7_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs150hDInzNvYv49XvNxnFfA8r2IDaCCUKZMDN6tN2XahNyi1qAlN9HqMvP5TJq06R6SvJ7JtS71HxOVzN9TdaRPMgWpXEEwdbe9Sov6Wv5e7OpR6FAwrdzydBf4sjE0r5ncXHLYE5WVGZm3qrGlvaJKo06-2FmQk9V7IT3lo5fU1imi64DOcTD-2FOs6pN-2BKArlOmMJvbZTkVZPaY3bg4-2BeOsY0QiuTg0CnhQpt0ErltDA-2Fxy88zGioTtbzdeu7AgUKM-2B0-3D  Global Communication Works, 261 Madison Avenue, New York City, NY 10016 United States  --  To unsubscribe from this group and stop receiving emails from it, send an email to customerservice+unsubscribe@csps.com.

Waterstone at the Circle Hosts Lifelong Learning & Entertainment for Older Adults  Concert: Pat Gaulin Trio to Perform at Waterstone at the Circle (August 11)  BOSTON — Waterstone at the Circle will welcome the Pat Gaulin Trio on Sunday, August 11 at 2 p.m. Drummer Pat Gaulin will lead his trio in an energizing musical performance influenced by Afro-Cuban and Brazilian Rhythms, Hip Hop, Jazz, Funk, and good old Rock & Roll.  This concert is complimentary and open to the public, but space is limited. For more information or to RSVP, call ?617-564-4395 or email Living@WaterstoneAtTheCircle.com. Waterstone at the Circle is a premier senior living community located at 385 Chestnut Hill Ave.  Lecture: Behind the Curtains with The Opera Lady (August 13)  BOSTON — Helen “The Opera Lady” Sagan returns to Waterstone at the Circle to discuss Pagliacci, Ruggero Leoncavallo’s operatic tale of love, jealousy and revenge, on Tuesday, August 13 at 2 p.m.  This lecture is complimentary and open to the public, but space is limited. For more information or to RSVP, call 617-564-4395 or email Living@WaterstoneAtTheCircle.com. Waterstone at the Circle is a premier senior living community located at 385 Chestnut Hill Ave.   Seminar: Therapeutic Benefits of Music at Waterstone at the Circle (August 19)  BOSTON — On Monday, August 19 at 1:30 p.m., Waterstone at the Circle’s Life Enrichment Director, Greg Lazzaro, MT-BC, will discuss how music and other creative arts can improve quality of life for people suffering from trauma.  This seminar is complimentary and open to the public, but space is limited. For more information or to RSVP, call 617-564-4395 or email Living@WaterstoneAtTheCircle.com. Waterstone at the Circle is a premier senior living community located at 385 Chestnut Hill Ave.  ArtMatters Presents: Start Spreading the News! at Waterstone at the Circle (August 20)  BOSTON — Art educator Jane Blair returns to Waterstone at the Circle on Tuesday, August 20 at 2 p.m. to discuss the undeniable love affair between artists and New York, New York, home of possibilities, impossibilities and dreams that sometimes come true.  This lecture is complimentary and open to the public, but space is limited. For more information or to RSVP, call 617-564-4395 or email Living@WaterstoneAtTheCircle.com. Waterstone at the Circle is a premier senior living community located at 385 Chestnut Hill Ave.   Lecture: A Judicial Review at Waterstone at the Circle (August 26)  BOSTON — Waterstone at the Circle will welcome Dan Urman to present a judicial review of U.S. Supreme Court Chief Justice John Roberts on Monday, August 26 at 4 p.m. Professor Urman is a former criminal prosecutor for the Commonwealth of Massachusetts and the current head of Northeastern University’s Law and Public Policy minor.  This lecture is complimentary and open to the public, but space is limited. For more information or to RSVP, call 617-564-4395 or email Living@WaterstoneAtTheCircle.com. Waterstone at the Circle is a premier senior living community located at 385 Chestnut Hill Ave.  Open Houses at Waterstone at the Circle (Tuesdays & Thursdays)  BOSTON — Waterstone at the Circle is hosting Open Houses every Tuesday from 10 a.m. to 12 p.m. and every Thursday from 4 to 6 p.m. Guests are invited to explore luxury senior living in the heart of Boston. Tour the modern, open-concept apartments with stunning city views and the indoor pool and fitness center staffed by Train Boston®. Learn how Waterstone at the Circle’s 24-hour concierge services and vibrant cultural, recreational and educational opportunities will help older adults enjoy a rewarding, urban lifestyle.  For more information or to RSVP, call 617-564-4395 or email Living@WaterstoneAtTheCircle.com. Subject: Editorial comments and corrections
Description: The following information was collected:  Name: gregory reed sargent  Email: gregorysargent@hotmail.com  Subscriber: No  Subject: Debtors Prison USA  Product: Other  Message: 3 years of continued attempts to get proper authorities involved in public corruption has left me with emails to read like the one below, all stating that the format, not the content, is improper.  If one would take the time to view the evidence of corruption in Salem Oregon and my place at the center of their concern to cover the facts with format complaints, we would begin to see how many poor people are treated when it comes to official business.  In short, the government caters to the rich and leaves the poor people of the United States in virtual debtors prisons all over, my case being a corner stone for the people with common sense to see if one is left in a rural setting and expected to afford for support the state declares in constitutional then why cut the access off by suspending the license of these people  again, no sidewalks, no bus stops, where I live and the only place to find employment the Stock manager just happens to wear a T-Shirt from the Florida Counties Fire Department where I owe child support.  a Florida to Oregon coincidence?  Gregory Reed Sargent 11093 71st ave NE,  Salem,  Oregon USA Civil Action based on being charged 419$ a month with no way to find employment State took license away 17years ago and continiued to charge me 419$ a month till it amounted to 86, 000$  Case in Brief: Natisha Davis and Gregory Sargent got pregnant,  decided on an abortion that Gregory Sargent paid for,  Gregory Sargent returned from work to Natisha Davis doing cocaine stating,  "I will do the abortion this way." This is the sworn statement of the record,  this has been repeated several times in court after being arrested for the child support. Gregory Sargent has never seen Gabriel Davis,  the child Natisha Davis attempted to kill with cocaine she purchased with Gregory Sargent's money. Gregory Sargent was so upset after she did cocaine with his money he intended not to ever give any more money to repeat the attempt,  he has never seen Gabriel Davis or Natisha Davis since the abortion,  she did,  her way.   17 years and still fighting on the good moral high ground that Salem, Oregon hasn't found through their unending red-tape that is afforded for.  Fighting a debtors prison in Salem, Oregon, hope you respond to my email about it and I can find relative safety outside of the United States, sadly this country I live in caters to the rich and uses the poor like toys, sexual in many cases, but slaves none the less.  The corner stone of this case is a question anyone should be able to answer,  "Does a lawyer paid 2000$ an hour and a lawyer paid nothing provide the same defense?"  There are many people that experience this find of poor plight every time they are jailed or hampered in their quest for freedom by restrictions because of the debt they owe.  Good Day.  Sincerely,  Gregory Reed Sargent  gregorysargent@hotmail.com

Subject: A Late Summer Sneak Peek
Description: View our web version   Long summer afternoons and star-studded nights are upon us, the hint of fall and Labor Day is on the horizon, but there is only one place to be: the present, and what a time it is to be present. This August, we're looking at innumerable opportunities to bring new music into the world, from our upcoming Call for Scores (read on for a sneak peek!), the next China Tours, and more.  Read on to explore the latest news, and join the discussion on Facebook , Twitter , and Instagram .  http://parma.acemlnb.com/lt.php?s=de51d59a4853b201ff2fcb5d81422b07&i=746A1632A113A12349  PARMA Recordings Summer 2019 Call for Scores: An Introduction  Our Call for Scores program has been bringing countless selections of music to life over the years. This summer, for the first time ever, we're offering a full pre-submission period sneak peek into who is a part of the Call this year.  READ ON for the rest of the story....     http://parma.acemlnb.com/lt.php?s=de51d59a4853b201ff2fcb5d81422b07&i=746A1632A113A12197     THE ARC IN THE SKY  Kile Smith; The Crossing  Professional chamber choir The Crossing and composer Kile Smith present THE ARC IN THE SKY with choral works elevating the texts of 20th-century intellect Robert Lax in this compelling Navona Records album.     http://parma.acemlnb.com/lt.php?s=de51d59a4853b201ff2fcb5d81422b07&i=746A1632A113A12203     http://parma.acemlnb.com/lt.php?s=de51d59a4853b201ff2fcb5d81422b07&i=746A1632A113A12203 QUADRANTS VOL. 3  Altius Quartet  The series that brought both traditional and genre-defying collections of string quartet works is back with QUADRANTS 3, the latest from Navona Records featuring the acclaimed Altius Quartet and eight contemporary composers.     http://parma.acemlnb.com/lt.php?s=de51d59a4853b201ff2fcb5d81422b07&i=746A1632A113A12198     http://parma.acemlnb.com/lt.php?s=de51d59a4853b201ff2fcb5d81422b07&i=746A1632A113A12198 RESONATING COLOURS 5  Hong Kong Composers' Guild  Seven composers, seven takes on contemporary composition: With RESONATING COLOURS 5, the Hong Kong Composers' Guild presents a compilation featuring some of the most remarkable voices in chamber composition the autonomous city-state has brought forth.     http://parma.acemlnb.com/lt.php?s=de51d59a4853b201ff2fcb5d81422b07&i=746A1632A113A12204     SOLI FOR TUBA, ZHENG, HORN, WITH PERCUSSION  The McCormick Percussion Group  The McCormick Percussion Group are recognized by composers and aficionados throughout the world for their creative interpretations and recordings that are decidedly out of the mainstream of percussion literature. This is all present on Ravello Records' SOLI FOR TUBA, ZHENG, HORN, WITH PERCUSSION.        http://parma.acemlnb.com/lt.php?s=de51d59a4853b201ff2fcb5d81422b07&i=746A1632A113A12136     CLASSICAL HEAR AND NOW  Always be on top of what's new in the classical music world with our rotating new music  Spotify playlist. Click here  to discover and follow our playlist for new music every month.  http://parma.acemlnb.com/lt.php?s=de51d59a4853b201ff2fcb5d81422b07&i=746A1632A113A12200     MOTO QUARTO  Trio Casals  Acclaimed international piano trio Trio Casals makes a triumphant return with the fourth installment of Navona Records' MOTO series, zestfully interpreting contemporary works from nine composers.     http://parma.acemlnb.com/lt.php?s=de51d59a4853b201ff2fcb5d81422b07&i=746A1632A113A12201     http://parma.acemlnb.com/lt.php?s=de51d59a4853b201ff2fcb5d81422b07&i=746A1632A113A12201 THREE SCENES  Elliott Miles McKinley  Composer Elliott Miles McKinley explores diverse musical territory on Navona Records' THREE SCENES. Featuring many notable ensembles, the album's three selections emphasize the depth and breadth of McKinley's compositional prowess.     http://parma.acemlnb.com/lt.php?s=de51d59a4853b201ff2fcb5d81422b07&i=746A1632A113A12202     FOR THE PEACE OF CITIES  Philip Koplow  During his lifetime, late composer Philip Koplow composed music that commemorated tragedies of violence and the work done to create peace. His works, alongside other similarly-inspired modern orchestral pieces, are celebrated in Ravello Records' FOR THE PEACE OF CITIES.     http://parma.acemlnb.com/lt.php?s=de51d59a4853b201ff2fcb5d81422b07&i=746A1632A113A12199     http://parma.acemlnb.com/lt.php?s=de51d59a4853b201ff2fcb5d81422b07&i=746A1632A113A12199 BIRTH OF A CITY  David Haney  Those who prefer to think outside the written score will enjoy making the acquaintance of jazz pianist David Haney, who habitually blurs the line between notation and improvisation, most recently in his newest release BIRTH OF A CITY.              http://parma.acemlnb.com/lt.php?s=de51d59a4853b201ff2fcb5d81422b07&i=746A1632A113A12205        The Inside Story: Gary Smart  In Memory: Philip Koplow  July 26 New Releases  Composer Conversations: Kile Smith  The Inside Story: Nora Morrow  The Inside Story: Clare Shore  The Inside Story: David Nisbet Stewart  The Inside Story: James Shrader  The Inside Story: Elliott Miles McKinley  The Inside Story: Robert McCormick  July 12 New Releases  Collaboration with The Crossing Takes Off  Composer Conversations: Edie Hill  "...purely and compellingly orchestral. Very good sound."  Gramophone  on PARALLEL REALMS  "SUSTAIN works surprisingly well as an album. Each piece is somehow enhanced by its distance from the work it follows."  Sequenza 21  on SUSTAIN  "The piece is a significant American music drama that deserves to be heard."  Opera News  on THE MASK IN THE MIRROR  "A PATH OF LIGHT exemplifies small-group playing at its finest, with the four members, even if augmented by guests, presenting an uplifting 'World Music' capable of global appeal."  Textura on A PATH OF LIGHT  "The Crossing performs these works in stunning sound."  Cinemusical  on EVOLUTIONARY SPIRITS  Discover more reviews here     July 3-4, 2019: Ostrava, CZ PARMA recorded works for solo clarinet with strings and for orchestra by composers Ahmed Alabaca and Audun G. Vassdal, respectively, with the Janá?ek Philharmonic Orchestra and clarinetist Karel Dohnal.  July 8, 2019: Roslindale MA PARMA recorded male and female vocal overdubs for works for orchestra by composer Michael G. Cunningham at Futura Productions.     http://parma.acemlnb.com/lt.php?s=de51d59a4853b201ff2fcb5d81422b07&i=746A1632A113A12158         July 20, 2019: Trio Casals at Weill Recital Hall at Carnegie Hall Piano trio Trio Casals performed works by composers David Nisbet Stewart, Emma-Ruth Richards, Joanne D. Carey, Allyson B. Wells, L Peter Deutsch, Christopher Brakel, Clare Shore, Keith Kramer, and Mathew Fuerst at Weill Recital Hall at Carnegie Hall. This performance was in conjunction with the release of the same program on Navona Records' MOTO QUARTO.  July 25-August 5, 2019: Hornyanszky-Roemer Duo China Tour Oboe and guitar duo Zoltán Hornyánszki and István Römer will be performing in various locations around China as part of PARMA's China Tour program.  *secured via PARMA's Performance Outreach Program  August 14, 2019: Matej Meštrovi? in Šibenik, Croatia Matej Meštrovi? will have music from his Navona Records release 3 RHAPSODIES South Czech Philharmonic and conductor Miran Vaupoti? at the summer stage of St. Michael's Fortress in Šibenik, Croatia.        http://parma.acemlnb.com/lt.php?s=de51d59a4853b201ff2fcb5d81422b07&i=746A1632A113A12159      http://parma.acemlnb.com/lt.php?s=de51d59a4853b201ff2fcb5d81422b07&i=746A1632A113A12160      http://parma.acemlnb.com/lt.php?s=de51d59a4853b201ff2fcb5d81422b07&i=746A1632A113A12161      http://parma.acemlnb.com/lt.php?s=de51d59a4853b201ff2fcb5d81422b07&i=746A1632A113A12162      http://parma.acemlnb.com/lt.php?s=de51d59a4853b201ff2fcb5d81422b07&i=746A1632A113A12163      Unsubscribe from our newsletter   PARMA Recordings , 223 Lafayette Rd , North Hampton , NH 03862, United States

Subject: From a mom: New video helps parents baby-proof their home and prevent tip-overs
Description: Good afternoon,  The Consumer Product Safety Commission’s Anchor It! (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=84Em28S1K9SvtzcUtu04EmzOtnAoQpzj96ReJumy2HcKSeQFXlYzKfSk13Mx6WS3_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs1FQNdS7X0aB5x5Lh0YFCuu52GnqkoyrSCwtzwQV1dnHPLc1lMWkhwo5TZoz1CVCDJhH4y-2FAn3IqeujtcosrWhuA2Y8ljQZnXSDnqbZgBKBuyv21zZGQ4y5PPBKkye4zh-2ByoRkDP7RtOPF5lRSb1JMdSlUo9xYk580fiiZbn0Xz1VwUejfF7iy-2FG1oU6rU4KyS54lSHsYt45RoEnbAyp5HxGWiKziWaOibFxffA-2B660OizKILQLhnJ7lECHb2g6Fs4-3D campaign just released a new video (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQB8Py45Kv8f-2BYRfyH7N0ZolOgQWpyQrzdkLj-2FMi1fh6srIKsNpMlmaap1JnOVBEN-2BDA-3D-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs1FQNdS7X0aB5x5Lh0YFCuu52GnqkoyrSCwtzwQV1dnHPLc1lMWkhwo5TZoz1CVCDJhH4y-2FAn3IqeujtcosrWhuA2Y8ljQZnXSDnqbZgBKBuzohd2544y4SZT6rYHW4-2Fnlb915WDisirvptM4m18gM6Dnru6vDL1HanAH6m66oE-2FViUrmY15f-2F19nqky9E0ElHY61bkwVF-2BhAwW8bJ1OI-2Bad5GGM5EPp-2FFdvRaVlJeDic8mu4540wVze1RKW3EI5JU-3D that highlights the importance and simplicity of anchoring furniture and TVs to prevent tip-over injuries and deaths. As a new mom to an almost one year old, I found myself a bit overwhelmed when I researched babyproofing check lists and saw “anchor your furniture.” I wondered if anchoring was really necessary, and if it was even something I was capable of doing.  But then I learned that a child dies about every 11 days when a TV, furniture, or appliance falls on them, and 14,000 children are injured ever year according to CPSC’s newest report (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQB-2FdNz06aGPPnTbOTf9cWpmpvoAsr6ulsQRPlxY-2BP-2FkFt83h6vgwn5TbwFrG5KszVsC478IzMQjZ0437uSoY055MzVIGCLpUmccaKJKgy2a4JCtQ5vDHE1q5ksOl4LO-2BqoAtPl3GfkecFncq0SPIagrc9l3StRJ0KDbF-2Bz1UK-2FQoo4DhjvIc39BHy3kvdA-2FvsxQ-3D-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs1FQNdS7X0aB5x5Lh0YFCuu52GnqkoyrSCwtzwQV1dnHPLc1lMWkhwo5TZoz1CVCDJhH4y-2FAn3IqeujtcosrWhuA2Y8ljQZnXSDnqbZgBKBu9vyFr5QzEwMZe-2BFVaO1D-2FVI5ORQkmkKbQz7Av0-2BNTfnZCarJEoNzmgf-2BcI2hu8yqtD1ASm5zHRBbngYpdv-2BepttP519E4PqPfZofx9JoTpL2lmg9Ip4aW4YFj3FLnOPY-2F6qpTPHInrjhzrym30peA4-3D . About 70 percent of tip-over fatalities involve children ages 1.5 to 3. These incidents are preventable.    In addition to the new video showing how simple it is to install anti-tip devices (also known as anchors), mothers who have lost a child due to a tip-over incident and CPSC spokespersons are also available for interviews, and would love the chance to educate your audience on the importance of anchoring.  There is also a new poster (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQB8X502EdyGcXbDkorDqaPFPqoui-2B-2B4Uu-2BMkRwDcXNrqGkW3Zkd5oBex1HmRU-2F-2FUrj14OMPbgwn-2FUnZE1anBhL6710K7hQThlLLcjR1DGaSS-2F_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs1FQNdS7X0aB5x5Lh0YFCuu52GnqkoyrSCwtzwQV1dnHPLc1lMWkhwo5TZoz1CVCDJhH4y-2FAn3IqeujtcosrWhuA2Y8ljQZnXSDnqbZgBKBu9nn27IS8zsXiNnHUkO4MlL2i2nKn2jZASqS-2Fa-2FMQW7kvvbj3KxseJJc1APDTT54Olshco1uK4R-2Bgq8CInRptqTkqooY6MWN1UjEPgD57-2FwGL-2BLApveZhC846H29Os-2BP16xy487jVIgvE6-2BhZT16KrQ-3D and a new tip sheet (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQB8X502EdyGcXbDkorDqaPFPqoui-2B-2B4Uu-2BMkRwDcXNrqGkW3Zkd5oBex1HmRU-2F-2FUrjycej-2BAHgf9P4C5lmKuWuzuoKeZckHhzdEKnHs3ErgIp_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs1FQNdS7X0aB5x5Lh0YFCuu52GnqkoyrSCwtzwQV1dnHPLc1lMWkhwo5TZoz1CVCDJhH4y-2FAn3IqeujtcosrWhuA2Y8ljQZnXSDnqbZgBKBu8pUFKEjpp7yroskCObIZp6oPuoGu-2BiglHVX99Xh4TT0iGDSf-2FfFDzBxeKXdqGugumlAq-2F5bB7SmcvIxAP2l8AI-2BXwt5g3Y9ZL5q7llwKOAj91pY0d-2BzzVbHMgI-2BTT8jWK8cQZh1Y0L0sPHQ7uArsvQ-3D available on the campaign website. Subject: Changing Compensation Costs in the Boston Metropolitan Area- June '19
Description: [cid:image001.jpg@01D18B3C.987EA3F0]  New England Information Office For Immediate Release August 5, 2019 Phone: 617-565-2327, select option '0' Email: BlsinfoBoston@bls.gov<mailto:BlsinfoBoston@bls.gov>  New BLS Data: Total compensation costs for private industry workers increased 2.7 percent in the Boston-Worcester-Providence, Mass.-R.I.-N.H.-Conn. metropolitan area for the 12-month period ending June 2019. Nationally, total compensation costs rose 2.6 percent.  The New England Information Office of the U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics (BLS) has released data on changing compensation costs in Boston for June 2019. The data are derived from the Employment Cost Index (ECI) program which is a quarterly measure of changes in labor costs. Some highlights from the attached press release are listed below.    *       Wages and salaries, the largest component of total compensation costs, increased 3.0 percent in Boston from June 2018 to June of 2019. Nationwide, wages and salaries increased 3.0 percent.    *       Total compensation costs in Boston (2.7 percent) was below that of New York (3.9 percent) but above that of Philadelphia (1.4 percent). Boston's 3.0-percent gain in wages and salaries during June 2019 was also below that in New York (3.9 percent) but above that of Philadelphia (1.9 percent).   *       Over-the-year growth rates in the cost of total compensation ranged from an increase of 3.9 percent in New York to a decrease of 0.4 percent in Seattle during June. Wage and salary annual growth rates ranged from 4.3 percent in Los Angeles to 1.5 percent in Houston. [cid:image003.jpg@01D54B95.B464E8A0] Please call 617-565-2327 and select option '0' if you have questions for BLS or need a comment on this story.  Stay informed with the latest BLS reports and data. [Final signature look] If you would like to be removed from this list, please click UNSUBSCRIBE<mailto:blsinfoboston@bls.gov?subject=Remove%20from%20weekly%20notification%20list>

Subject: Share your comments with the Journal Editors [#2541]
Description: Title * Pregnancy complications healed and a harmonious childbirth Author By Jessica Raflo Web Address (URL) of page https:/journal.christianscience.com/issues/2019/2/137-02/pregnancy-complications-healed-and-a-harmonious-childbirth Name *    susan self Email Address *   susanlself@gmail.com Share your Comments: *  Hi, I'd be very grateful if you would forward this email to Jessica Raflo, the author of this testimony Susan Self  Dear Jessica, Thank you so much for sending in that testimony; it was wonderful and assures women that painless childbirth is indeed possible and should be expected. On that note,  I like to read early editions of the Journal, especially the testimonies, to learn how people initially heard about CS. Many women testifiers in the 1890's mentioned hearing about these (alleged)  painless childbirths and naturally wanted to investigate. You might find the  testimony of Mary Simpson from 1912 interesting as her birth experience closely resembles your own. https://journal.christianscience.com/issues/1912/12/30-9/twenty-years-ago-by-a-strange Susan Self  Comment Publication *  I give permission to publish my comment. Subject: The Latest!
Description: Volume 3 | August 5, 2019 Freedom To Believe The Latest The Freedom to Believe team travelled to Chicago, Illinois to take part in the International Kurdish Studies Conference. We met with leaders of different organizations like Zahra Institute to find opportunities to collaborate. The Freedom to Believe team held a meeting with Neighborly Faith, an organization devoted to helping Evangelical Christians become good neighbors to people of other faiths. We sat down with their fellows and discussed how we can work together to build bridges across communities. Visit our Website Follow us on Twitter! Our latest: Turkey's Support for Uyghurs is a Sham Diliman Abdulkader argues in The Jerusalem Post that "Erdogan is not concerned about human rights, religious freedom or the Uyghurs." Subject: Consumer Alert from the Federal Trade Commission (FTC) -- Worshipers targeted by gift card scam
Description: Dear Colleague,  The Federal Trade Commission<ftc.gov>, the nation's consumer protection agency, is alerting religious leaders around the country about a gift card scam targeting worshipers.  The FTC alert, Worshipers targeted by gift card scam<https://www.consumer.ftc.gov/blog/2019/07/worshipers-targeted-gift-card-scam>, explains that scammers pretend to be a pastor, rabbi, priest, imam, or bishop and then ask worshipers for gift card contributions for a worthy cause. Appeals are often made by email, but we've heard people are also getting texts and phone calls, too.  The imposter asks people to buy a popular gift card - frequently, iTunes, Google Play, or Amazon - and then asks for the gift card number and PIN on the back of the card. Those numbers let the scammer immediately get the money people loaded onto the card. And once that's done, the scammer and peoples' money are gone, usually without a trace. But, as outlined in the alert, there are things people should do if they paid a scammer with a gift card<https://www.consumer.ftc.gov/articles/paying-scammers-gift-cards#Paid>.  The FTC would appreciate your help in getting the word out about this scam through your network.  Want to avoid the latest rip-offs? Sign up for free consumer alerts from the FTC at ftc.gov/subscribe<https://www.ftc.gov/stay-connected#_blank>. If you spot a scam, report it at ftc.gov/complaint.<http://www.ftc.gov/complaint>  Thank you,  Colleen Tressler Senior Project Manager Division of Consumer and Business Education <http://www.ftc.gov/about-ftc/bureaus-offices/bureau-consumer-protection/our-divisions/division-consumer-business> (DCBE) Federal Trade Commission 600 Pennsylvania Ave, NW<https://maps.google.com/?q=600+Pennsylvania+Ave,+NW+%0D%0A+Washington,+DC+20580&entry=gmail&source=g> CC-10402 Washington, DC 20580<https://maps.google.com/?q=600+Pennsylvania+Ave,+NW+%0D%0A+Washington,+DC+20580&entry=gmail&source=g> 202-326-2368 Web<http://www.ftc.gov/> I Facebook<http://www.facebook.com/federaltradecommission> I Twitter<https://twitter.com/ftc> I YouTube<http://www.youtube.com/FTCvideos> I Consumer Center Blog<http://www.consumer.ftc.gov/blog>

Quite A Feat!                                                                                                                                                              Based in Southern California, SMILE! SOX™ is independently owned and part of the Keepers International family. Founded in 1954, Keepers is a pioneering wholesale distributor of premium-quality, high-fashion socks that began by serving independent apparel and shoe stores along with larger regional department and sporting goods stores located on the West Coast. Today Keepers’ socks are sold in Dress, Casual, and Sport styles for men, women and kids at stores all around the world.    Commenting on the launch of the new SMILE! SOX^™ brand, Paul Hockley, President of Keepers International, said, “For more than 65 years we’ve dressed your feet with fashion, comfort and function but we wanted to do something more – something FUN. That’s where the idea of SMILE! SOX^™ was born. Why not make socks that bring joy to people and inspire happiness? If putting on your socks in the morning brings a smile to your face, what better way to start the day and make the world a happier place? SMILE! SOX^™ lift your spirits, promote happiness and brighten everyone’s day. In a world that isn’t always rosy, we all need more reasons to SMILE!”  ###  READY TO WEAR A SMILE!? — SAMPLES UPON REQUEST! Subject: Future and Faith-Stories of Those Who Lived to Tell
Description: https://www.hatcheryla.com/registration-page-6ae50d2f-0ca7-429c-9cba-4b20304a3ba3 Hi Everyone,  Hatchery LA is pleased to invite you to the latest in our Future and Faith online conversation series, The Stories of Those Who Lived to Tell. (https://www.hatcheryla.com/registration-page-6ae50d2f-0ca7-429c-9cba-4b20304a3ba3)  This time I'm sitting down with Nathan Banks, a tech exec for one of the leading software companies in the world.  Listen in as Nathan and I talk over his move away from Christianity and why.  What is it about modern Christianity that completely disinterests so many people, not least of which 30-40 something young professionals, as they take inventory of their core values and what they want for their young and budding families?  As an American living in London and working for one of the most famous tech companies in the world, listen in as he tells the familiar story of why he left fundamental Christianity in his dust for an agnostic and material understanding of life and what's it's all about.  Hear the conversation right from the heart of London's iconic Soho neighborhood as we have friendly and thoughtful dialog on his thoughts on church and why this future-thinking tech exec left it all behind.  Join us as we speak openly, candidly and frankly about some really tough issues that the church must sit with if we have any hope of moving into the future.  Listen as Nathan and I explore in this very unplugged, yet on the record, conversation where nothing is off limits.  Click below to sign up, reserve your spot and get your link.  Friday, August 9th at 10am PST.  Hope to see you there!  Maria French and the Hatchery LA Team  REGISTER FOR FREE HERE (https://www.hatcheryla.com/registration-page-6ae50d2f-0ca7-429c-9cba-4b20304a3ba3)  ============================================================ Want to change how you receive these emails? Subject: Another Weekend, Two More Mass Shootings in the U.S. – Expert Avail.
Description: Hi Stephanie?  As you may have heard, over the weekend, two mass shootings (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQB0AhWq289cy9ZkSlF1KjslrlUrFz5HpLdsjld4Cn3IWCojB5ywnUZnhh3qVQv9J1kPAlU6nHjzKftLAONaGLE8znY91JFNUKwYPF9r8UJrE-2B_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs2-2FsOSv-2Ba27jli1lub-2FM9Njrvz7tOF7EuOe06CtxykUHZzdK2I3RUNtp-2F-2BfW8hjwA8c9aVhEbaY9J3s74UcKaAhPFhhjgjUvfM1O4uUyD0SOpbRy-2BmFG-2Fz5Vlqv5kL-2Fd1QBO-2F1kNc5BLqfBlxySrAlNEbE2Zr1jykGVMfNMwyh73nabPmfkM3ec0GEwrhKntIuk3vanjjq0p-2F3wKWqtZpYv4EOrBZb9wjjAAhJMgPnmv7l9vWXCy8qphxLEOtTBEV4-3D occurred within 24 hours of each other, claiming the lives of 34 people and leaving and more than 50 wounded. According to a gun violence research group, the number of mass shootings (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=G62jSYfZdO-2F12d8lSllQB5zbLdWhb7jQ8Mjjc5c7pr1GnW6-2BYZ2rDKrm-2FaAvftpZ_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs2-2FsOSv-2Ba27jli1lub-2FM9Njrvz7tOF7EuOe06CtxykUHZzdK2I3RUNtp-2F-2BfW8hjwA8c9aVhEbaY9J3s74UcKaAhPFhhjgjUvfM1O4uUyD0SOg8e4x4cxi0pzEIggj-2Fb8uCoKIwwC-2Bcd10DBmzmxd2QgADBb9XEpvcm1R5ozN8a7YYenQ6pq88gqJwCEwFGwGuOXCuh6V-2BIrepnBAfSAiK9ElZx0uq7JxLc8mGxPxciYBK2joiHmvYpG1ThXHWuyrmM-3D across the U.S. so far in 2019 has outpaced the number of days this year.  To weigh in on the topic, I’d like to offer up Leading Mental Health Specialist, Dr. Neeraj Gandotra, MD, Chief Medical Advisor from Delphi Behavioral Health Group (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=84Em28S1K9SvtzcUtu04EhKhZsSZb2-2B8Sm7TGYtcO9n2oqq2cIzY2YqLNYPi8HJJ_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs2-2FsOSv-2Ba27jli1lub-2FM9Njrvz7tOF7EuOe06CtxykUHZzdK2I3RUNtp-2F-2BfW8hjwA8c9aVhEbaY9J3s74UcKaAhPFhhjgjUvfM1O4uUyD0SOp-2BwpDXTHiYS7VC1siytIqNTPz2WX-2Fn88i3oZg0bxtcp7h4aIuZX1a-2BeoThOw7KxMrmGy2TKDRhrA45r-2B5u8oUGMf8U-2FeBwd86tSJwPewpHdVHdCmt5moMmQPnlLFTxt-2BDM6RwYqhWcdwiM2KKglRzA-3D , a leading nationwide provider of addiction and detox treatment programs, who can speak to the following and more:  · The Role Of Mental Health in Mass Shootings · Motivations That Often Drive Mass Shooters · Mental Health Repercussions That Will Be Felt By Victims · How The U.S. Government Can Better Address Mass Shootings  If you’re interested in speaking with an expert from Delphi please let me know, and I’d be happy to coordinate.  Warmest,  Nandi  About Delphi Behavioral Health Group  Delphi Behavioral Health Group was created in 2016 with the goal of creating long-term recovery from addiction for individuals suffering from substance abuse and chemical dependence. Addiction and medical professionals use proven methods to heal individuals with the disease of addiction through a variety of detox and residential options designed to address the core issues behind the disease. With over 350 inpatient beds available currently, we are able to extend our services across the country, offering much-needed programs and services to those suffering and seeking help with their addictions. For more information visit www.delphihealthgroup.com (https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=84Em28S1K9SvtzcUtu04EhKhZsSZb2-2B8Sm7TGYtcO9k-2Bj6fqXuLKCWKUFFZNL1gt_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs2-2FsOSv-2Ba27jli1lub-2FM9Njrvz7tOF7EuOe06CtxykUHZzdK2I3RUNtp-2F-2BfW8hjwA8c9aVhEbaY9J3s74UcKaAhPFhhjgjUvfM1O4uUyD0SOn-2B4Xwuqe2UDbsn2iO2kO0wmKYywHAKaA8vHEBhVAkE5LA24COYI-2FqzfVPxPpNk-2Bm4kBdTLcJcTgJYwete7vqvdPLyZOihbTIXmaGXpYeiG1PNsXeo7AGD-2BsNOCA8yathnad10RnsA3C0pe6ncsi2FA-3D .   Nandi Millett  Account Executive  5W Public Relations  D (646) 763-8297  nmillett@5wpr.com (mailto:nmillett@5wpr.com)    ______________________  If you would rather not receive future communications from 5W PUBLIC RELATIONS, please go to https://u7061146.ct.sendgrid.net/wf/click?upn=NBhTsVIXpTHrhf0NvhZzDd-2BIuOQfkp6rENL5eiggmwgjfXorV-2Bb730JV2hl5MB8DjhBUsc015erDsBEZpEFXBFIzAeJwpEhVqzYh-2BV50FDwhFfsWiy0Eh7dVmgY48rG4cDMDRYVgH-2BpTSCNSbnG2RIsT4YitgYKflVeWFJR3n30-3D_6pchHAirW10eM8b14ZAlkZkRllITHdt0G4CIxpgEX-2FYMT-2FVtvkhkoxOwXdc140hQDKip1v9w6NG6f4yMNdzd3I0JbBoOspHl9BOjIgd0xs2-2FsOSv-2Ba27jli1lub-2FM9Njrvz7tOF7EuOe06CtxykUHZzdK2I3RUNtp-2F-2BfW8hjwA8c9aVhEbaY9J3s74UcKaAhPFhhjgjUvfM1O4uUyD0SOmhH51zSLHBv98quxkanf7kLKubkCpE4boJBGmRLOZS17n2shVgf1dPsVeWDYclMtcOVzBDGRIpqMu3mdFbsaycjf9gsKeo2pCJBtoYe3koATxopXa2Z7AXN6sLCaw7L0NQYU5HoRQkU9MiweGDjVIg-3D  5W PUBLIC RELATIONS, 230 PARK AVENUE, 32ND FLOOR, New York, NY 10169 United States  --  To unsubscribe from this group and stop receiving emails from it, send an email to customerservice+unsubscribe@csps.com.
